title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and cocoa together. Add sugar and mayonnaise and mix well.
Add water and vanilla.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350° (preheat oven).

title: summertime slush
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Transfer into freezer containers.
Freeze for at least 24 hours.
When ready to serve, scoop frozen slush into a tall glass (about 1/2 full) and fill rest of glass with 7-Up, ginger ale, Mountain Dew or lemon lime soda.

title: banana peanut butter muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°. In a large bowl, combine the flour, oats, and baking powder. In a small bowl, mash the bananas, then blend them with the milk and egg. Combine the peanut butter, corn oil, vanilla extract, and honey in a medium bowl. Stir in the banana mixture. Pour the peanut butter mixture into the flour mixture, mixing just until the dry ingredients are moistened. Fill greased muffin tins.

title: pepperoni loaf
directions: Let bread thaw and rise.
Cut in half.
Mix egg and cheese. Roll out each half.
Spread half of egg mixture onto dough.
Lay out pepperoni and 1/2 of cheese.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Roll dough up jelly roll style.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichokes.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a 1-quart casserole at 350° unti hot and bubbly (20 to 30 minutes).
Use as a hot dip with your favorite crackers.

title: punch for 100
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: texas barbecue sauce
directions: A zesty sauce to pour over 3 pounds ribs during the last 45 minutes of baking or mix together and simmer with 1 1/2 to 2 pounds ground beef as sloppy joes.

title: lady penelope(frothy, cadillac-pink yogurt drink)
directions: Put all ingredients into a bowl and whiz up with a mixer until bubbles form and
it looks light and frothy.
Pour into a glass and serve immediately.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup and cream cheese until cheese has dissolved.
Mince shrimp, celery and onion and mix with mayonnaise, lemon juice and seasonings.
Mix water and gelatin and mix in soup and cheese mixture.
Add other ingredients and pour into mold and chill.

title: cookies made with bananas
directions: Sift flour, sugar, soda, spices and salt into large bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender.
Add banana and eggs.
Stir in chocolate chips and rolled oats.
Drop on cookie sheet; flatten out.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: red beet jelly
directions: Cook red beets; take 3 cups of the water they were cooked in. Bring red beet water to a boil.
Mix gelatin and Sure-Jell. Quickly add to the boiling juice to dissolve.
Take from heat; add sugar immediately and stir well.
Put into jars and seal.
Makes 4 to 5 cups.

title: cough medicine
directions: Mix all together and take 3 times a day.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix altogether and serve immediately.
Use fresh strawberries or lime slices on top.

title: vegetable pasta
directions: In a large pan, combine the oil, water, broccoli and garlic. Cook, covered, over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms and black pepper.
Cook until tender.
Remove from heat and stir in tomatoes, basil, pasta and cheese.
Makes 3 servings.

title: orange sherbet jello
directions: Prepare jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Cool slightly.
Beat in sherbet.
Add pineapple and oranges.
Stir well.
Cool and allow to jell in refrigerator.

title: janet's cabbage slaw
directions: In a food processor shred cabbage.
In a bowl place shredded cabbage, parsley and onions; mix and let stand in refrigerator 1 hour.
Then add sugar, salt and vinegar.
Sprinkle with celery seed and mix thoroughly.
Keep refrigerated.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix by hand.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake for 60 to 70 minutes at 350° or until done. Can be frozen.

title: zesty zucchini
directions: Slice zucchini 1/4-inch thick.
In skillet, saute butter and onion; add zucchini, salt, mushrooms and water.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add tomato sauce; cover and simmer for 5 more minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top and simmer 5 more minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Wilt leaves of cabbage.
Mix beef, pork, boiled rice, salt, pepper, allspice and onion and form into patties.
Roll patties in cabbage leaves and fasten with toothpicks.	Butter skillet and put rolls in.
Brown; remove and place in baking dish.	Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Mix 1 tablespoon flour, cream and juice in skillet.	Cook until thickened.
Pour over cabbage rolls and serve.

title: quesadilla casserole
directions: Slice cheese about 1/4-inch thick by 4-inches long and 2-inches wide.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Oil 9 x 13-inch casserole or pan. Prepare quesadillas by stacking one of each kind of cheese near the edge of tortilla; top with rounded teaspoon each of onion and chilies.
Roll tortillas up around cheese, folding ends under to form 12 little packages.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape dough into small balls.
Mix 3 tablespoons sugar with 3 teaspoons cinnamon.
Shake dough balls in cinnamon sugar.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes (cookies don't brown) at 375°.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, milk, salt, corn, eggs, soda and bacon drippings; set aside.
Saute ground beef; drain and set aside.
Prepare and set aside onion, cheese and jalapeno peppers.
Grease skillet. Heat, sprinkle with a thin layer of cornmeal and let brown slightly.
Pour half of batter in skillet, then sprinkle evenly one at a time, meat, onion, peppers and cheese.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: easy chili
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Simmer on stove 3 to 4 hours or 4 to 5 hours in crock-pot.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook beef and seasoning as package directs.
Let it cool.
Wash and cut up vegetables into a large bowl in the order listed.
Add the beans and the seasoned ground beef.
Crush the Doritos and add them.
Pour in the dressing and mix the salad thoroughly.
Sprinkle Cheddar on top.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix uncooked rice, meat and seasonings.
Shape into balls. Place in deep baking dish and cover with tomatoes.
Bake in a moderate oven (350° to 375°) for 60 to 80 minutes.

title: cucumber sandwich spread
directions: Combine all ingredients well and mix with enough mayonnaise to make a good spreading consistency.

title: dill cucumber pickles
directions: Scrub cucumbers; rinse well and dry on paper towels.
Pack in 7-quart jars and add 1 or 2 heads dill to each jar.
Bring remaining ingredients to boil in 3 quarts water (preferably distilled).
Fill jars to within 1/2-inch of top.
Seal as manufacturer directs and process in boiling water for 10 minutes.

title: blueberry butter
directions: Combine all ingredients, blending well.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: spoon bread
directions: Stir 2 cups milk into cornmeal and cook until the consistency of mush.
Remove from heat; add 1 cup milk, butter, baking powder and salt.
Stir a moderate amount into beaten egg yolks.
Return to mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in greased 2-quart casserole at 325° for 55 minutes.
Serve with butter. Serves 6.

title: crunchy chicken rolls
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese together in bowl.
Add chicken, mixing well.
Spoon 1/4 cup chicken mixture into each roll.
Wrap dough to enclose filling, sealing well.
Dip each roll into melted margarine.
Coat with stuffing mix.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: carrot tea bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil until well blended.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir into egg mixture; add carrots.
Spray 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Beat oleo, egg and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Ice with powdered sugar icing.

title: deviled swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Sprinkle mixture over round steak and pound into meat with a meat mallet.
In heavy skillet, brown steak slowly on both sides in hot oil.
Drain off excess fat.
Drain mushrooms.
Keep liquid.
Add water if needed to 1/2 cup.
Add mushroom liquid and Worcestershire sauce to meat in skillet.
Cover tightly and cook over low heat for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
During the last few minutes, add mushrooms and heat through.
Skim any fat from pan juices before serving.
Garnish with parsley, if desired. Serves 6 to 8.

title: cinnamon pull apart bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Lightly grease bundt pan (or tube pan). In a small bowl combine sugar, cinnamon and a dash of salt. Open the biscuits and cut each biscuit into four pieces; set aside. Put the pieces of biscuit into the mixture, a few at a time, until they are all completely coated. Arrange the biscuit pieces in the pan in layers. Heat the butter in a small saucepan over low heat, stir the remaining sugar mixture and the pecans into the hot butter. Pour the butter mixture over the biscuit pieces. Bake in preheated oven for 45 minutes, until top is golden brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped dried beef.

title: asian salad
directions: Set aside flavor packets from Ramen noodles. Crush noodles and put in bowl. Add cole slaw mix. Sprinkle cole slaw mixture with almonds, sunflower seeds and onions.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix well and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 325° for 25 to 28 minutes. Cool and ice with icing.

title: raspberry angel food cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir gelatin into hot water.
Continue stirring until dissolved.
Stir in raspberry jam.
When partially set, whip the cream and fold into jam.
Adorn with fresh raspberries for a summer birthday.

title: carrot cake with coconut and pineapple
directions: Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and put topping on cake.

title: pinwheels
directions: Spray (2 to 3 short sprays) an 8 or 9-inch square pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Spread on bottom and sides of pan with a paper towel.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture. Drop by rounded teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with back of floured fork to make crisscrosses.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining 2 ingredients.

title: home style ribs
directions: Place half the ribs in a slow cooker. Top with half of the onion. Repeat layers. Combine the remaining ingredients; pour over all. Cover and cook on low for 8 to 9 hours or until ribs are tender. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: crab casserole
directions: Separate the eggs. Add beaten yolks to white sauce. Mix all ingredients and fold in egg whites. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: Mix
eggs,
cottage
cheese,
yogurt, soup, spinach and carrot.
Spread mixture
on
bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.
Place
lasagne
noodles on top, then layer on more sauce, then
sprinkle
Mozzarella
cheese.
Repeat
layers: lasagne, sauce, cheese, lasagne, sauce and end with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry delight
directions: Beat whipped topping mix and milk together.
Add sour cream and sugar until mixture becomes well beaten.
Pour mixture into crust and top with cherries.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef with taco seasoning. This is the only thing to be cooked.
Pour off all oil. Add all of the other ingredients. Everything will be added in one bowl.

title: chicken divan
directions: Simmer chicken breasts until tender.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Lay broccoli in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish; cover with cut up chicken and top with soup, mayonnaise mixture and then grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Serves 6.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Dilute soy sauce with water to your taste.
Add sugar to desired sweetness. Mix other ingredients.
You may use steak chuck roast, cut in 1/4-inch strips, pork chops or chicken.
Soak just 2 hours before cooking. Cooking on the grill is the best.

title: kentucky spoon bread
directions: Separate 3 eggs.
Scald milk and add meal gradually.
Cook until thick.
Pour a small amount over beaten egg yolks.
Then add that mixture to the corn meal.

title: christmas cheese soup
directions: Combine
water,
bouillon
cubes,
potatoes, celery and onion. Boil for 25 minutes.
Then add the vegetables and boil for 10 to 12 minutes.
Add soup to cubed cheese and heat until melted, stirring
so
that	it
won't
stick.
Then simmer all together until
ready
to
serve.
Can be kept in refrigerator for several days or in the freezer.

title: hot rolls or sticky buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Scald milk on low; add butter, salt and sugar, then cool to lukewarm.
Add 2 1/2 cups flour and beat well.
Add yeast and egg and potatoes.
Add remaining 2 cups of flour.
Put on board and knead lightly.
Put in greased bowl and cover.
Let rise until double in size.
Shape into rolls or buns and let rise about 1 hour.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. For sweet rolls, cut with a round cutter, spread with butter, brown sugar and cinnamon and seal.

title: granny's good ole hominy
directions: Build a fire around the kettle.
Put corn into kettle and fill full of water above corn; then add lye and cook until husk comes off corn.
Take it out and wash it; then return to kettle and cook until done.

title: easy tangy red punch
directions: In large pitcher or punch bowl, combine concentrates and water.
Just before serving, add ginger ale; stir to blend. Garnish as desired.
Makes 24 (4 ounce) servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except blueberry pie mix.
Put half of batter on bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cover with pie filling. Top with remaining batter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Other pie fillings may be used.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Melt butter; cool.
Add sugar mixture. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add buttermilk and vanilla; beat well.
Pour into two 8-inch pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, or until done.

title: cooter pie(the hunter's delight)
directions: First you take a live cooter and wait for him to stick his head out from under his shell.
When he does, you grab it and whack it off.
Take a hatchet to the underside so you can get to the meat and remove it along with the liver, tripe and eggs (if he has any?).
Set aside.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.

title: old fashioned pot pie
directions: Combine flour, lard and enough water to make a soft dough. Roll thin, cut into strips and drop in hot broth.
Cook uncovered over low heat 10 minutes.
Cover and cook 10 minutes longer.

title: mexican dish
directions: Layer in a pan and cook about 30 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: In buttered baking pan (9 x 9 x 1 3/4) layer broccoli, chicken, bread cubes and cheese.
Combine gravy, milk and pepper; pour over mixture.
Bake at 375 degrees for 40 minutes; let stand 5 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine ingredients and chill slightly.
Make into a ball and roll in chopped walnuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: steamed rutabaga, broccoli and cauliflower
directions: Steam at medium-high heat in a steamer, or use colander to put vegetables, using a pot to place under colander with about 1/2 a pot of water to steam.
Use a cover over colander and steam until vegetables are tender but not too soft, about 30 to 45 minutes. Stir occasionally.

title: pasta in a pot
directions: Brown the hamburger meat with the onions and garlic salt. Boil macaroni shells until tender; then combine meat mixture with the shell macaroni.
Add spaghetti sauce, tomatoes and mushrooms together with half of each of the cheese and the rest of the cheese to go on top.
Bake until cheeses melt at 350°.

title: herbed chicken over pasta
directions: In a large, heavy skillet, melt margarine over low heat.
Dust chicken with flour, shaking off excess.
Brown chicken in margarine over medium-high heat, stirring constantly.
Add garlic, basil, oregano, parsley, salt and pepper and stir 2 minutes.
Add sherry and bring to a boil.
Cover skillet and cook over low heat until sauce thickens, about 10 to 20 minutes.
Remember to keep stirring occasionally.
Serve over cooked pasta.

title: no peek pie
directions: Beat eggs
well,
add
melted oleo, sugar, milk, flour, salt, baking
powder,
vanilla
and desired amount of coconut. Mix all this together and pour into two 8-inch pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 35 minutes.
You can also use chopped pecans instead of coconut.

title: one dish chicken
directions: Wash and skin chicken.
Roll chicken in crushed corn flakes. Place in baking dish.
Pour melted butter over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Mix cheese and mushroom soup; pour over chicken. Return to oven until cheese and soup are hot.

title: seasoned sweet potatoes
directions: Peel yams and cut into 1/2-inch thick circles.
Spray glass baking dish with Pam.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°, tossing every 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with turkey and stuffing meat loaf.

title: cream cheese pastry shells
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese together.
Work in flour.
Chill if very soft.
Roll into 48 balls.
Press into 1 3/4-inch muffin tins as tarts.
Fill and bake.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat the first 7 ingredients until smooth.
Add the water, flour and baking soda.
Pour into 3 loaf pans or 1 pound coffee cans sprayed with nonfat cooking spray.
Bake for 55 minutes at 350°.
Serve with Dream Whip on top.
Yields 3 loaves or 3 coffee cans (36 slices).

title: apricot brandy pound cake
directions: Have eggs, butter and sour cream at room temperature.
Grease and flour bottom of a large tube pan.
Preheat oven to 325°. Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly.
Sift together the flour, baking soda and salt. Combine sour cream, flavorings and brandy.
Add alternately the flour and sour cream mixture to the sugar mixture.
Mix just until blended.
Pour into prepared tube pan.
Bake for 70 minutes, or until done.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain; while hot, mix with margarine, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Mix well.
Spread and press in 10-inch pie pan, well buttered.
Cook crumbled beef until browned.
Spread cottage or Ricotta cheese over crust.
Spoon meat mixture on top of spaghetti crust.
Cover with sauce.
Bake uncovered for 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Cover with Mozzarella and bake for 5 minutes more. Let stand for 5 minutes; cut in wedges, then eat and enjoy.

title: frijoles negros(black beans)
directions: Soak beans overnight in enough water to cover.
Next day, place onions and green peppers in blender until pureed.
Saute until liquid is consumed.
Add 1 can pimentos which has been blended and 1/2 of olive oil.
Saute well; add to beans.
Add salt, pepper and sugar.
Allow to cook on low heat for 3 hours, until thickened. During last hour, add remaining olive oil, vinegar and can of pimentos, which have been chopped in small pieces, along with water of same.
Makes 15 to 20 servings.
May be refrigerated.
Can freeze for future use.

title: blitzen cuken
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten egg yolks.
Add baking powder to flour and add alternately with milk.
Spread on 2 buttered round cake tins.
Beat egg whites until stiff, adding cream of tartar.
Add sugar gradually.
Place meringue on top of cake batter; sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Spread layer with whipped cream (strawberries may be added to whipped cream).
Top with second layer and enjoy!

title: perky porcupines
directions: Combine ground beef, rice, egg, pickles, celery, onion, pepper and paprika in a bowl.
Mix lightly, but well.
Shape meat into 1 1/2-inch meatballs.
Place in an 8 x 12 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and lemonade.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into a graham cracker pie crust.
Cover with foil and put in the refrigerator.
Let chill. Cut into slices and serve.

title: vera mae franklin's unbaked nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in pan of choice.
Chill overnight or freeze.

title: cantaloupe preserves
directions: Cut cantaloupe into 1/2 to 3/4-inch size pieces.
Mix with sugar and let set overnight or all day.
Add lemon juice and cook until clear and thick.

title: egg roll
directions: Fry chicken or pork in oil until light brown.
Add shrimp, garlic and
green onions.
Saute until all looks light brown.
Add carrots; saute until crisp.
Add cabbage, soy sauce, salt and bean sprouts.
Stir for a few minutes.
Set aside.

title: boil cookies
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients, then remove from stove and add oats and peanut butter.	Mix well and drop on wax paper or foil to cool.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix these ingredients thoroughly and make into balls.
Freeze for 20 minutes.
Remove from freezer and dip in melted almond bark. Refreeze.

title: chicken continental
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine salt and pepper with 1/2 cup flour.
Rinse chicken and roll in flour.
Fry in margarine until brown and then remove from skillet.
Add to drippings in skillet: soup, onion, dried parsley flakes, dried celery flakes, thyme and 1 1/3 cups water.
Heat in skillet until hot.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, grease with margarine and then add Minute rice.
Pour mixture from skillet over rice.
Make sure rice is covered by mixture.
Put chicken on top.
Cover and bake 30 minutes in oven.
Yields 4 servings.

title: tiger tea
directions: In a large kettle, bring 1 qt. water to a boil.
Add tea bags and steep for 5 minutes.
Discard the tea bags and stir in lemonade and orange juice concentrate.
Add sugar and remaining water.
Serve over ice.
Yields: about 3 qts.

title: harvest time stuffed peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In 3-quart saucepan bring water to a boil. Add peppers; return water to boil.
Cook peppers in boiling water 5 minutes; drain.
In 10-inch skillet, melt 2 tablespoons butter and add onion.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until tender (3 to 4 minutes).
Stir in tomato, corn, salt and basil. Cook until heated through (3 to 5 minutes).
Stir in cheese.
Place peppers in 9-inch square baking pan.
Fill each pepper with about 1/2 cup vegetable mixture.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Heat cream cheese, mayonnaise, mustard and white wine.
Add other ingredients and cook over low heat for 1 hour.
Serve in chafing dish or small crock-pot to keep warm.
Serve with crackers, Melba toast or use miniature pastry shells.

title: yaki tori
directions: Debone chicken and cut in bite-sized pieces and put on skewers.
Soak chicken in sauce for 2 hours and broil.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Sprinkle top with more chocolate chips and nut meats. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sausage cocktail balls
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients except sauce; mix well. Shape into bite-size meatballs.
Place on rack of broiler pan. Bake in preheated 425° oven for about 15 minutes; drain well. Place browned sausage in lightly greased crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low setting for 5 to 6 hours.
Serve on wooden picks for dipping in sauce.

title: hot olive cheese puffs
directions: Blend butter and cheese.
Mix in flour, paprika and salt. Shape about 1 tablespoon of dough around each olive.
Wrap in foil and freeze.

title: greek beef stew
directions: Blanch onions in boiling water for 1 minute.
Drain; peel. In a kettle, melt butter over moderate heat.
Add the beef; toss to coat it with butter, but do not let it brown.
Add wine, stock, tomato paste, vinegar, sugar, cumin, garlic, allspice, bay leaf and salt and pepper to taste.
Bring mixture to a boil; simmer stew, covered, for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Add onions.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.

title: indian summer casserole
directions: Brown meat; add onions and green peppers and cook a few minutes; add liquid from corn and the can of mushroom soup.
Cook 10 minutes.
While the meat is cooking, cook noodles in separate pot until tender; drain.
Add corn and cheese soup to meat.
Bring to boil.
Add noodles to meat and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Garnish with pimentos.
Cover and bake until thoroughly heated 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients with a little water.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix and heat through.
Serves 4.
Almonds or cashews may be substituted.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients in a 4-quart saucepan.
Bring to boil exactly 15 minutes.
Remove from fire.
Add the next 3 ingredients.
Beat until thick.
Pour into greased container.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Combine ingredients. Beat with wire whisk or mixer on medium speed until thoroughly mixed. Cook as thin pancakes on a medium heat setting. Brown on both sides. Roll or fold in quarters and serve with favorite topping.

title: easy lemon chicken
directions: In a large skillet, brown chicken in vegetable oil.
Pour off fat.
Add gravy, lemon juice, thyme and vegetables to skillet. Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes or until done.
Spoon into pastry shells.
Serve.
Serves 6.

title: poppy seed delight loaf
directions: Combine all of the ingredients; mix for 1 to 2 minutes with electric mixer.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool in pan about 5 minutes, then glaze.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Add sour cream slowly.
Beat egg whites until stiff, set aside.
Add egg yolks to butter and sugar mix.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt and mix with eggs and butter.
Add vanilla; fold in egg whites.
Grease Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Bake 1 hour or a little more at 325°.

title: chicken breast with stuffing
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place a piece of cheese over each breast.
Pour soup over cheese; sprinkle dressing mix over soup.
Pour melted butter over top of dressing mix.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fried corn
directions: Cut the kernels off the cobs with a sharp knife being careful not to cut too close to cob.
Melt bacon drippings in a skillet; add corn and saute lightly for about 10 minutes.
Scrape the milk from each cob into the skillet.
Add sugar, salt and pepper.
Cover with just enough water to cover corn and cook for about 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well.
Roll into balls (about 1 teaspoonful).
Place balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press tops with fork.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: date pecan cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients 2 times. Remove small amount to mix with pecans and dates. Set aside. Beat egg whites, set aside. Beat egg yolks and sugar gradually, mix well. Add dry ingredients, vanilla, nuts and dates. Fold in egg whites. bake 350° in tube pan for 1 hour.
Soak lint-free cloth in blackberry wine. Wrap cake when cool. Store in airtight container 2-3 weeks. If cloth gets dry add small amount wine.

title: mandarin chicken with noodles
directions: Stir fry bite size strips of chicken in oil.
Break up noodles.
Add noodles to 1 c. water in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add celery and garlic and cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 3-5 minutes until noodles and
vegetables are tender.
Stir in chicken flavor packet, sweet and sour sauce, and peanuts.
Heat through.
Garnish with Mandarin oranges.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, pecans and vanilla.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on greased baking sheet and flatten slightly.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while warm and again when cool.

title: ice cream from snow
directions: Some people also whip an egg or two in the snow cream.
Dish comes out like a thick soda.

title: range-top roast
directions: Preheat 10-inch skillet over medium heat for 3 minutes.
Add roast and brown on both sides.
Sprinkle roast with salt, pepper and onion soup mix.

title: corn pudding
directions: Put milk, corn and butter in a pan; heat until hot, but not boiling.
Put eggs, sugar, flour, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Pour and stir corn mixture slowly into eggs.
Put in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, until a knife stuck in center comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings, about 2/3 cup each.

title: cheese and sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Shape in small balls.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: k's baked cauliflower
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil cauliflower; drain and set aside. In a saucepan, melt margarine and gradually add flour and milk, stirring constantly.
Slowly add cheese, pepper, salt, sour cream, green pepper and cauliflower.
Mix well and cool.
Beat 2 eggs and add into cauliflower mixture.
Grease a 9 x 11-inch baking dish. Pour mixture into dish and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Cover lightly with foil and bake 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes more or until golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: snickers cake
directions: Melt candy bars with margarine.
Cool slightly.
Stir to combine but don't overdo the stirring.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 300° to 325° until toothpick inserted comes out clean, about 35 to 40 minutes. Frost with any moist chocolate frosting.

title: mom's no bake cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar until smooth. Then gently stir in cool whip. Pour into crust. Refrigerate overnight. Top with a can of cherry filling.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until creamy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Sift flour.
Add baking soda to sour cream.
Add flour and sour cream alternately to the butter-egg mixture.
Blend well after each addition.
Add vanilla and almond extract.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into a lightly greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°. Cool and remove from pan.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix cake by directions on box, then add sour cream. Mix together cinnamon and sugar. Pour half of cake batter into Bundt cake pan. Sprinkle cinnamon mix over batter. Then pour rest of cake batter into pan. Bake at 350° until done.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Bake in large greased pan (10 x 15) at 350°.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend in a blender until creamy. Pour into a covered dish and refrigerate overnight.
Serve cold with any raw vegetable.
This recipe makes 1 pint and will last in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: lemon loaf cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Add milk and flour alternately; add flavoring.
Beat well.
Bake in a Bundt or tube pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until tests done.

title: tortilla chip dip
directions: Layer ingredients on platter.
Allow to set at least 4 hours. Garnish with unsalted tortilla chips.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all but eggs and oil in small bowl.
Mix well.
Beat eggs and oil together.
Add all ingredients together and mix well. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in greased and floured tin cans.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar; add water and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour and pecans.
Chill 3 to 4 hours. Shape into balls or fingers.
Bake in ungreased cookie sheet in slow oven (325°) for about 20 minutes.
Cool slightly; roll in confectioners sugar.

title: meatballs in tomato sauce
directions: Soak cracker crumbs in milk.
Add hamburger meat, egg, onion, salt and pepper and mix well.
Form into 2-inch balls.
Brown in a frying pan, then place in a baking dish.
Mix the soup, water and Worcestershire sauce and heat through.
Pour over balls.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; serve over spaghetti.

title: microwavable cheesy-tuna potatoes
directions: Pour hot water over potatoes and margarine in 2-quart microwavable dish. Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High for 4 minutes. Stir in remaining ingredients, except cheese. Cover with waxed paper and microwave until hot and bubbly, 2 to 3 minutes longer. Sprinkle with cheese.
Microwave until cheese is melted, 1 to 3 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix together the cabbage, soup and cheese and pour into casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, chili sauce, egg, salt and pepper, mixing thoroughly.
Shape beef mixture into an 8 x 4 1/2-inch loaf.
Place on rack in open roasting pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Prepare gravy.
Serve meat loaf with mashed potatoes and gravy.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour with salt and soda.
Combine cocoa, food coloring and enough strong coffee to make a paste.
Cream Crisco and sugar. Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Stir in cocoa mixture and beat well.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk alternately, mixing well after each addition.
Pour into two 8-inch layer pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Heat oil in skillet and fry vegetables over high heat 3 to 4 minutes (stirring).
Add broth, ginger, soy sauce and chicken; cover and cook 2 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with 3 tablespoons of orange juice; add this to hot mixture.
Cook, stirring until slightly thick.
Add oranges and serve with almonds on top.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling water for 5 minutes and drain.
Combine soup and sour cream in mixing bowl.
Add carrots. Fold in squash and onion mixture.
Add salt and pepper.
In separate bowl, combine stuffing mix and butter.
Spread 1/2 of this mixture in bottom of pan.
Spread squash mixture on top. Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix over squash.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: overnight coffee cakefort collins, colorado
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs, then flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and buttermilk.
Mix well.

title: chocolate pie
directions: After measuring, sift sugar, cocoa and flour into double boiler.
Beat egg yolks in small bowl with fork.
Add eggs and milk to cocoa mixture.
Add butter.
Cook, stirring, until very thick.
Pour into cooled baked pie shell.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream and cream cheese until all lumps are gone.
Put in a pizza pan (like pizza crust).
Layer, starting with hamburger.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes before serving.

title: elephant stew
directions: Take one large elephant, kill, clean and cut meat into small cubes.
This will take about 2 months.
Put into large kettles. Cover with water and simmer over kerosene heat at 465° for 14 weeks, or until tender.
This will feed about 3,685 people.
If more meat is needed, add 2 rabbits, but use rabbits only if necessary, as few people care for hare in their stew.
Good any time.
April Fool!

title: ruthie wagner's green bean casserole
directions: Mix eggs, milk, flour, salt and pepper.
(Batter will be thick.)
Heat water to boiling.
Press batter through the holes in a colander (preferred one with large holes), a few tablespoons at a time, into the boiling water.
Stir once to prevent sticking. Cook about 5 minutes or until Spaetzle rise to surface and are tender.
Drain.
Toss Spaetzle with butter or margarine.
Serve with gravy or just plain.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat chicken with taco seasoning, taco sauce and salsa.
Heat and blend.
In a 9 x 13 pan (sprayed with Pam), layer tortillas (cut to fit), meat mixture, sour cream and cheese.
Continue layers to fill pan, about 3 layers.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes until bubbly.

title: cold macaroni salad(summer salad)
directions: In large boiling pot, cook and drain noodles as directed. Rinse noodles under cold water to stop cooking.
In large bowl, blend the rest of ingredients, then add noodles.
Blend and refrigerate.
Serve cold.
Makes 8 servings.

title: wedding punch
directions: *The color of Jell-O determines final color of punch.

title: butternut pecan popcorn
directions: Spray roasting pan with nonstick spray.
Place the popped corn and pecans in the roasting pan and keep warm in 300° oven while making the syrup.

title: captain jim's cortez italian grouper
directions: Dip finger size grouper fillets in the melted butter.
Roll fillets in a mixture of the bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Place fillets on cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for 7 to 10 minutes.
Turn fillets over and bake for an additional 7 to 10 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: chicken spaghetti royale
directions: Melt butter or margarine; add mushrooms, onion, green pepper, parsley and thyme; cook until vegetables are tender.
Blend in flour, soup and salt, stirring until thickened.
Add chicken, pimentos and lemon juice and keep at serving temperature.
Prepare spaghetti as directed; toss with chicken mixture and serve.
Makes 8 to 10 hearty portions.
Good with green salad, garlic bread and light dessert.

title: oven spaghetti
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add green peppers.
Pour off fat when brown.
Add rest of the ingredients, except cheese.
Do not cook spaghetti.
Bake at 375°, covered, for 45 minutes.
Add cheese and bake 5 minutes more.

title: triple treats candy
directions: Melt over hot (not boiling) water, chocolate morsels and shortening.
Stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth. Remove from heat.
Pour 1/2 of melted chocolate into a 8-inch greased foil-lined square pan.
Spread chocolate evenly. Refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Return remaining chocolate mixture to low heat.
Melt caramels and butter with water over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Stir in Planters walnut pieces until well blended.
Pour into chocolate-lined pan.
Spread evenly. Refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Top with remaining melted chocolate. Spread evenly to cover caramel filling.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen candies.

title: turkey creole(low-fat)
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Shape into patties.
Place in Teflon skillet.
Cover; cook on low heat until golden brown on both sides, turning once.
Add juice, Worcestershire, 1/2 cup water and sugar.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and water.
Add to sauce, while stirring, until thick and bubbly. Serve with cooked rice.
Serves 4.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix meat well.
Add next seven ingredients and mix well.
Soak bread in milk.
Add eggs and beat with hand beater.
Mix bread and meats together.
Form into 1 or 2 loaves.
Pour 1/2 cup boiling water around loaf.
Cover with chili sauce.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: squash pie
directions: Wash, slice and cap 7 medium squash (do not peel).
Put in crock-pot and cover with 1 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon. Cook until tender, 2 or 3 hours.
Put in blender and puree.
Mix next 5 ingredients with 1 cup of the squash.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: swiss bacon quiche
directions: Bake shell at 450° for 7 minutes.
Sprinkle bacon and cheese on bottom of shell.
Slightly beat eggs, milk and salt.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 250° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes. Serves 3 to 4.

title: creamy potato puffs
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and potatoes.
Mix, blending well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in 1-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cruncha moca madness
directions: Bake brownies set aside, when cooled cut into mall cubes. Set aside. In large mixing bowl mix coffee, pudding powder and cool whip. Layer in clear bowl, brownies, whip mix then sprinkle Score crumbs. Repeat until bowl is filled then stick halves into top for garnish.

title: cheddar-dill scones
directions: Position rack in top third of oven and preheat to 375°. Lightly butter two 9-inch pie pans.
Beat eggs, buttermilk and dill in medium bowl to blend.
Combine flours, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder, pepper and salt in large bowl.
Add butter to flour mixture and cut in until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add egg mixture and grated Cheddar cheese.
Stir to mix well.
(Dough will be stiff and crumbly.)
Knead gently until dough just holds together.
Divide dough in half.
Pat each half into prepared pans to 1-inch thickness.
Using long knife or pizza wheel, score each round into 6 wedges.
Bake until tester inserted into centers comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Transfer pans to rack and cool scones slightly.
Cut into wedges.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 scones.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer in order as appears in recipe. Crumble bacon on top. Refrigerate 8 hours.

title: 14 carat cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Add carrots, pineapple (drained) and nuts.
Bake in two 9-inch greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clear. Cool a few minutes in pan. Turn out on wire rack.

title: corned beef ball
directions: Mix together, adding just enough mayonnaise to get it to stick together.
Roll in parsley.
Make it at least 24 hours before serving.
Great on pumpernickel or rye bread.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place potatoes in a greased 9 x 13 dish. Season with salt and white pepper. Mix together sour cream and soup. Pour over potatoes. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Top with corn flakes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In a 3-quart shallow baking dish, mix hot cooked elbows with soup until well mixed.
Add 2 soup cans of milk; mix well.
Add American cheese, mixing it in well; the chunks will melt into sauce while baking.
Cover with tinfoil.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes until bubbly.

title: chocolate truffle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Butter sides and bottom of 8-inch spring-form pan.
Line the bottom with a round of waxed paper, cut to fit.
Butter the paper and dust it lightly with flour.

title: king mackerel sauce
directions: Mix sauce ingredients and cover mackerel fillets.
Marinate for at least 30 minutes.
Then place fish in a baking pan or broiler and broil until brown and appears done.
Baste with sauce if it appears to be dry.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart dish.
Combine 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk and stir until mixed.
Pour batter in dish.
Do not stir.
Combine peaches and 1 cup sugar and spoon over batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour..

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Combine and then add the pumpkin mixture to the flour mixture; mixing well.
Spread on a 10 x 15 greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Lay on dry towel covered with powdered sugar.
Roll and chill.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables, water chestnuts, mayonnaise and cheese in large mixing bowl.
Put in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Add margarine to crumbs and sprinkle over top.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 10 or more servings.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Beat until creamy the sugar, oil and eggs.
Add Choco-bake. Add flour, soda and salt alternately with buttermilk and vanilla. Add 1 cup water; beat well.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cream cheese mexican dip
directions: Finely chop tomatoes, peppers and scallions.
Spread cream cheese in pie plate.
Mix all vegetables with salsa and taco sauce.
Spread over cream cheese.
Sprinkle shredded cheese.

title: chocolate crunch ice cream pie
directions: Line large cookie sheet with waxed paper.
Melt chocolate with oil in top of double boiler set over simmering water, stirring until chocolate is smooth.
Transfer to medium bowl.
Mix in cookie crumbs.
Spread chocolate mixture over prepared cookie sheet.
Freeze until chocolate mixture is firm, about 10 minutes. Chop chocolate crunch into pea-sized pieces.
(Can be made one week ahead.
Store in airtight container in freezer.)

title: spinach quiche
directions: Mash cream cheese and gradually add cream. When mixture is smooth add bread crumbs, cheese, salt & eggs. Beat well, stir in uncooked spinach. Set aside. Meanwhile melt butter in skillet and saute onions and mushrooms until soft. Add spinach mixture. Pour into pie shell and bake for 25 minutes at 400.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix seafood with vegetables in Pyrex dish; put aside.
Mix heavy cream, flour and 1/2 stick melted butter; add to seafood. Then add 1 stick of butter to crushed Ritz crackers.
Place on top. Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until golden.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten eggs.
Sift flour and soda. Add dry ingredients alternately with bananas.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Grease and flour a tube pan or use 2 loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients with crisco. Add slightly beaten egg and milk. Mix well. Powdered egg mix works well. Yield 36 fried pies.

title: chicken barbecue
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Put in large skillet and cover with a mixture of the remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes to an hour.
Remove cover before serving to let sauce thicken.

title: jello cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add juice and cranberry sauce.
Chill until slightly thickened, about 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Put in greased mold.
Butter mold slightly.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cut up sausage, ham or chicken.
Mix all together and cook in oven 30 minutes at 300°.

title: italian spinach
directions: Wilt fresh spinach and drain.

Heat olive oil in skillet until hot. Add lots of garlic powder mixing into spinach. Cook spinach stirring constantly. Beat 2 eggs and add to mixture; add Parmesan cheese to taste while eggs are cooking. Turn off heat and top with Parmesan cheese.

title: master brownie mix
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Cut in Crisco with pastry blender and mix well.
Store at room temperature or fridge.
When you want to make brownies, combine 2 cups brownie mix, 2 eggs, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1/2 cup nuts. Bake in greased 9-inch square pan for 15 minutes at 425°.

title: jumbo oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together butter, peanut butter and sugars until smooth and creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; blend well.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Blend in oats and raisins.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased baking sheets for about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until done.
Makes 36 (3-inch) cookies.

title: impossible broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie pan.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Stir
in pineapple. After this mixture is mixed well, fold in containers of Cool Whip. Add pretzel mixture right before serving.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve cherry Jell-O in boiling water. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into 2-quart dish and chill until set.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Cook chops and onion in oil until brown, about 10 minutes. Spoon off excess fat.
Stir in soup and water.
Cover and simmer about 10 minutes or until tender.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Drain cans of fruit and mix all ingredients together.
Chill.

title: quick and easy creole dinner
directions: In 10-inch skillet, saute celery, green pepper and onion in oil until crisp-tender.
Add remaining ingredients except rice. Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexic-allie dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and spread in bottom of 9 or 10-inch glass pie plate.
Cover cream cheese with chili, spreading evenly. Sprinkle grated cheese to cover chili completely.
Cover plate with plastic wrap, leaving loose to vent.
Microwave on High, approximately 6 minutes or until cheese melts evenly.
Serve with chips.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine flour, sugar and salt; add yeast mixture and mix until well blended.
Knead on floured surface until smooth.
Cut dough into 18 pieces and roll each into a ball.
Roll each ball to form a rope about 14 to 16-inches long and about 1/2-inch around.
Twist into pretzel shape.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Beat egg white until frothy and brush on each pretzel.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with mustard, if desired.

title: baked squash casserole
directions: Cook
squash,
just
long enough to separate with fork. Drain very,
very well.
Saute onions and green peppers until done.
Do not
brown.
Put
all
ingredients
(except
bread crumbs) in baking
dish.
Mix	well
(but
easy, so as to not break up squash).
Add
bread
crumbs over top.
Add a little grated cheese with bread crumbs.	Dot with a little margarine. Bake approximately 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tasty turkey casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer rice, turkey, broccoli, mushrooms, water chestnuts and cheese.
Pour chicken broth over top.
Cover with a mixture of mushroom soup and Miracle Whip. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Spread onion rings on top of casserole for the last 10 minutes of baking.

title: kids in the kitchen super fruit slushy
directions: Blend in a blender or with a food processor until smooth. Drink chilled.

title: boston baked bread
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and sugar.
Add whole wheat flour; mix well.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add combined egg, milk and molasses to dry ingredients.
Mix only until flour is dampened.
Turn into 2 greased loaf pans or round tins.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: spanish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the soup.
Form 2 inch balls.
Place in baking dish.
Dilute soup according to directions on can.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into 1/4-inch strips.
Coat with salt and pepper. Drop in pot with onion.
Mix garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce, bouillon and catsup.
Pour over meat, cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Turn to high.
Add wine and mushrooms.
Dissolve flour in small amount of water.
Add to meat, stir until blended. Cook on high for 15 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Stir in sour cream, turn off heat.
Serve with rice or noodles.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour and confectioners sugar.
Cut in margarine until crumbly. Press into bottom of slightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine eggs, granulated sugar, 3 tablespoons flour, baking powder and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Pour over crust.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Store covered in refrigerator.
Serve at room temperature.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in small amount of water.
Drain.
Saute celery, green peppers and onions in small amount of fat.
Add to cabbage. Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Combine cheese, milk, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Pour over cabbage mixture. Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: old fashion stack cake
directions: Mix flour, salt, soda and baking powder; set aside.
Cream shortening.
Add sugar and molasses and beat well.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk alternately.
Pour batter 3/8-inch thick in greased and floured pans.
Makes 4 to 5 layers.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
When cool, stack, using cooked dried apples or thick applesauce between layers.

title: light blue cheese vinaigrette dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Chill thoroughly.

title: chicken puffs
directions: Bring Butter and water to boil.
When butter is melted, beat in flour with a fork over very low heat.
When mixture forms a ball, remove from heat and beat in eggs one at a time.
When mixture is smooth, drop tsp. size balls on cookie sheet.
Bake in 425 oven until brown and dry.
Fill with Chicken Salad.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain and rinse; add tomatoes, sauce and water.
Cover top of sauce with all seasonings.
Bring to a boil; then simmer for 1 hour or more.
Serve over noodles.

title: pinto beef casserole
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Cook until tender.
Blend in tomato sauce, chili powder and salt.
In
a greased 2-quart baking dish, arrange in layers, beginning and ending with meat sauce.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup cheese and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat for 1 hour. Mix the remaining ingredients with a little water; add and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Pour into bottles.

title: vanilla ice cream(refrigerator method)
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl until foamy; gradually add sugar and syrup.
Beat until thick.
Stir in cream, milk and vanilla flavoring.
Pour into freezer tray for 1 hour or until firm. After 1 hour in freezer, put into chilled bowl.
Cut apart and beat until smooth.
Return to tray and freeze again until firm. Yields 1 quart.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients
together.
Roll small meatballs and fry.
Add drippings to beef gravy.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: exquisite pie
directions: Mix together and bake in crust at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: In a saucepan, melt oleo and stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Allow to boil 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat; stir in soda and vanilla.
Gradually pour over popcorn, mixing well.
Pour in buttered baking pan and bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cool completely.
Break apart and store in covered container.
(Be sure to separate popped corn from unpopped kernels.)
It's also best to use a large shallow pan or 2 (11 x 13 x 9-inch) cake pans.

title: orange filling
directions: Mix all items together and cook in double boiler for 10 minutes.
Add coconut and spread over cake.

title: applesauce meatballs
directions: Mix all together, shape into small balls. Put into open roasting pan. Pour 2 (8 ounce) cans tomato sauce or 1 can tomato soup over them. Bake for 1 hour at 350 degrees. Good served over rice.

title: salad dressing for macaroni and potato salad
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and vinegar.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Cool.
Add mustard and salad dressing.
Mix well.
Pour over your favorite ingredients for Potato Salad or Macaroni Salad and stir in.

title: pickled over pickles
directions: Drain 1 quart kosher pickles. Cut in half lengthwise and put back in jar. Add remaining ingredients. Shake occasionally until all sugar is dissolved. Leave overnight before eating.

title: jan's lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Soak the poppy seed in milk for 2 hours.
Mix all ingredients for 5 minutes.
Bake in greased Bundt pan for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Heat crushed pineapple with sugar.
Add gelatine which has been soaked in cold water for 5 minutes.
Stir until melted; add lemon gelatin and cherry juice and cool.
Mix cream cheese with cherries (cut fine).
Then add to pineapple mixture.
Chill until slightly thick.
Fold whipped cream into mixture.
Mold and chill.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix and bake at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees about 40 minutes or until set.

title: mom's best cranberry mold
directions: You will need a jello mold.

title: andy jones meat loaf
directions: Mix all together and pack into baking dish.
Bake at 350°. (For extra flavor, lay 2 slices of bacon on top before baking.)

title: punch
directions: Pour Kool-Aid and sugar in large pan.
Add 1 qt. hot water. Stir until dissolved.
Add remaining water and juice.
Freeze. When ready to use, thaw slightly.
Add 2 - 2 liter bottles of Cherry 7-Up.

title: cheese ring
directions: Mix well and pack into ring mold at leave overnight.
Serve with strawberry preserves and crackers (Townhouse or Waverly). Put preserves in center of cheese ring after removing from mold. Spread cheese and preserves on crackers together.
Delicious flavor.

title: white salad
directions: Stir Fruit Fresh through the bananas.
Drain the pineapple, but save the juice.
Mix sugar and flour in a pan together.
Add the pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool overnight in refrigerator.
Then whip the cream and fold in.
Pour over pineapple and bananas.
Mix together and chill.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Place ingredients in pan and heat through.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Mix sugar and flour in bowl.
Slowly add milk and vanilla; beat well.
Melt butter; add to batter.
Pour fruit and juice into baking dish.
Dump batter into fruit; do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cheese, sour cream, lemon juice and milk.
Spread on large platter.
Chop onion and tomato finely and shred lettuce and cheese.
Spread these ingredients over top.
Sprinkle with taco sauce.
Serve with Doritos.

title: banana cream sandwiches
directions: In a small bowl, combine pudding and milk.
Mix on low speed until thickened, about 2 minutes.
Chill until set; about 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on graham crackers and top with additional graham cracker to make a sandwich.
Wrap individually in plastic wrap.
Freeze.
May be served when firm.

title: sourdough starter
directions: To begin, mix all ingredients together; let stand in your refrigerator for 3 days.
Before making your bread, add the same ingredients again, stirring with a wooden spoon.
Let stand on the cabinet for 8 to 12 hours.
Ready for use.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix all together, cook until thick. Put in 9 in. baked pie shell. Beat egg whites for top of pie, add 6 tbsp of sugar and brown in oven.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine all ingredients and turn in buttered casserole dish. Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Cream margarine until soft.
Put raisins in small amount of hot water to soften; drain.
Mix and sift dry ingredients, fruit and nuts.
Beat egg until fluffy and add sweetener.
Add flour mixture in thirds and stir until just combined.
Drop spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until done.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Cook ground beef and sausage until well done.
Break up into a fine texture while cooking.
Drain fat.
Crumble crisp bacon over meat mixture.
Drain juice off of beans.
Mix meats, beans and all other ingredients together.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes. This dish also does great in a crock-pot.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium bowl.
Cover with equal amounts of oil and vinegar.
Marinate overnight.
Strain off oil and vinegar.
Season as desired.
Serve cold.
Yum!

title: peanutty chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and salt in heavy-duty saucepan. Bring to a boil (rolling) over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil 4 to 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add marshmallows, morsels, peanuts and vanilla. Stir until melted. Pour into pan and refrigerate 2 hours. Lift from pan. Remove foil and cut into pieces.

title: graham pralines
directions: Break crackers along perforated lines.
Line bottom of a cookie sheet with crackers.
Set aside. Mix pecans, margarine and sugar in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat and boil 3 minutes.
Pour mixture over crackers.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes. Cool slightly.
Break apart.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Combine boiling water and oats.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Mix yeast and warm water and let stand 5 minutes.
Mix oats, yeast, salt, honey, butter and about 4 cups of the flour in a very large bowl.
Knead in remaining 2 cups flour.
(It will be hard work.) Let rise until doubled, 2 to 3 hours.
Punch down dough.
Divide in half and stretch each portion to cover bottoms of 2 greased loaf pans.
Let double again, 1 to 2 hours.
Bake at 325° for about 50 minutes.
(Is faster to use RapidRise yeast.)

title: glazed ham loaf
directions: Combine ham, pork, bread crumbs, onion, eggs, milk and catsup; mix well.
Shape into a loaf in a lightly greased baking pan. Combine brown sugar, vinegar and mustard in saucepan; bring to a rolling boil.
Spoon 1/3 of glaze over ham and return to oven. Bake 30 minutes longer and glaze every 10 minutes.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese broccoli soup
directions: Cook chopped broccoli as directed.
Mix potato soup as directed on can.
Mix leek soup mix as directed on box.
Add cheese and broth last.
Mix well.
I use a crock-pot.
Cook about 1 hour.
If you do not have crock-pot, you will need to watch it, so it won't stick to boiler.

title: cream cheese patties(easy and fun)
directions: Form into 1/2-inch
balls,
then flatten with a fork on wax paper surface.

title: sprig o' spring soup
directions: Blend all ingredients 2 minutes in an electric blender, or chop watercress very fine and combine with other ingredients in a saucepan.
Heat; stir now and then.
Garnish with sprigs of watercress.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Put 1/4 cup juice in small pan or microwave dish.
Sprinkle on gelatin.
Wait 1 minute for gelatin to soften, then heat and stir in remaining juice and sweetener.
Chill gelatin mixture just until syrupy.

title: aloha chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except lettuce leaves in a large bowl; toss until well mixed.
Chill and serve on lettuce, if desired. Serves 8.

title: creamed corn "ma dear style"
directions: Preheat stove to medium-high.
Stir flour into 1 cup of water. Empty contents into heated frying pan.
Wait until contents bubble before adding the canned corn.
Once the corn is added, stir occasionally for 5 minutes.
Add butter and sugar.
Stir until contents are dissolved.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix warm molasses and shortening.
Add milk and egg; mix well. Add dry ingredients that have been sifted together.
Bake in a moderate oven for 30 minutes.

title: oven stew
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in covered dish.
Cook in oven 6 hours at 250° until meat and vegetables are done.

title: pineapple coconut cake
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Add baking powder and salt; sift together.
Cream shortening and sugar, then add egg yolks, milk and flour.
Blend thoroughly.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Add beaten egg whites.
Pour into two 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Cut kielbasa into small half wafers and brown in skillet.
Cut onions in eighths and cook down in skillet.
Add whole tomatoes diced (with liquid), green pepper and hot peppers with seeds and veins.
Cook down for 2 to 3 hours.
Better the second day.
Serve with rye bread.

title: golosh dessert
directions: Stir together all ingredients and mix well.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown celery, pepper, onion and meat in Mazola oil.
Mix in separate bowl other ingredients and add to the meat mixture.
Let cook slowly until thick, stirring occasionally.
Serve on buns.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cover bottom of pan (9 x 11-inch) with a thin layer of sauce. In a large bowl, combine approximately 1/2 of sauce with cottage cheese, 1/2 Mozzarella cheese, parsley, egg, oregano, garlic, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Mix together; then add ziti and mix. Spread in pan.
Top with remaining sauce and Mozzarella cheese. Bake, covered, at 375° for approximately 60 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Lightly grease 10-inch pie plate. Cook and stir ground beef onion in 10-inch skillet until beef is brown. Drain. Stir in taco seasoning mix.
Spread in plate.
Sprinkle with chilies.

title: barbecue chicken with a twist
directions: Boil chicken with onion on stove for 20 minutes.
Lightly season with salt and lemon pepper.
In a separate pot add can of stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Stir.
Add honey, oregano, basil, thyme, pinch of black pepper and salt.
Season to taste.
Let simmer for 15 minutes, then put chicken in a lasagne pan and cover with sauce.
Cook in oven (350°) for 15 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serve with cabbage and brown rice.

title: cranberry salad supreme
directions: Wash cranberries, then grind in food processor using a coarse blade.
Let cranberries stand overnight and drain.
Combine cranberries, marshmallows, pecans and pineapple; chill.
Just before serving, whip cream until stiff and fold into fruit.
Serve in bowl garnished with greens if desired.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: meat marinade
directions: Marinate meat 6 hours.
Good on steak, pork chops, venison, etc.

title: hot cheese and sausage dip
directions: Cook sausage and onions in a saucepan over medium heat for 4 minutes or until browned.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in soup and water.
Heat until hot and bubbling, stirring occasionally.
Pour into hot dish or fondue pot.
Garnish with green onions.
Serve with celery, carrot sticks, or tortilla chips.

title: incredible peach pie
directions: This is a peach custard pie that makes its own crust.

title: spiced pineapple punch
directions: Boil sugar, water, cinnamon and cloves for 10 to 15 minutes. Strain and add to pineapple juice.
Mix well and pour over crushed ice.
Serves 50.

title: oat-fruit muffin surprise
directions: Combine cream cheese and egg yolk; add a little sugar.
Mix and set aside.
Mix flour, oats, brown sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
Mix egg, milk and fruit bits together, then add to flour mixture just until mixed.
Put some batter in cupcake papers, then add cheese and top with batter. Bake at 400°
for 15 minutes.
Then let cool.
Then brush with 1 tablespoon water and sprinkle with sugar.

title: creamy chicken soup
directions: Drain all vegetables before adding to the mixture.

title: strawberry butter
directions: Combine strawberries and softened butter with electric blender or mixer until smooth and creamy.
Place in attractive mug or crock and cover.
Yields 1 3/4 c.
Store in refrigerator up to 2 weeks.
Spread on bread, toast, or bagels.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon crisp, and then crumble.
Save 3 tablespoons of fat.
Cook onion in fat until golden.
Add potatoes and carrot and cook 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and heat.
Serve with hot garlic rolls.

title: holiday potato dish
directions: Remove skins from potatoes. Shred into bowl. Saute onion in 1/2 cup melted butter until tender. Remove from heat.
Stir in soup and sour cream.
Pour over potatoes and cheese.
Mix well. Turn into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with corn flakes and drizzle with 3 tablespoons butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour. Garnish with pimento and parsley.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Combine butter and flour in a large Dutch oven; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until roux is caramel-colored (15 to 20 minutes.
Chop celery, onions, green pepper and garlic. Add to roux.
Cook an additional 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Saute okra in vegetable oil.
Add to gumbo and stir well for a few minutes.
(Note:
May be stopped at this point.) Add next 9 ingredients and cook (simmer) over low heat for 1 hour. Add seafood last 10 minutes of cooking.
Remove bay leaf.
Do not boil after adding file, it will become stringy.

title: quick vegetable tuna casserole
directions: Mix vegetables, tuna, soup and seasoning.
Place in a 1-quart casserole.
Heat to bubbling in a microwave.
Place biscuits on top of hot mixture.
Bake in toaster oven or regular oven at 400° until biscuits are done.

title: purple passion salad
directions: Cream
sugar
and cream cheese together.
Add all other ingredients.
Add 2 tablespoons purple juice from cherries.

title: susan's crusty bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add salt and sugar; stir thoroughly. Add whole wheat flour first, then blend in white flour.
Makes a fairly stiff dough.
Shape into a ball.
Place in a greased bowl and grease the top of dough.
Cover with towel and let stand in warm place until doubled (1 1/2 hours).
Turn dough out on a lightly floured surface.
Makes 4 small loaves.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll out on a floured board.
Cut into strips 1/2 to 1 inch.
Bake at 350 degrees on a greased cookie sheet for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Remove from pan and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: busy day budget beef
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place meat on large piece heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over meat.
Bring foil up around sides and over top; gather together like a funnel with a small opening.
Place in pan and bake 45 minutes per pound in 350° oven or 60 minutes per pound at 300°.
Add one hour to the total cooking time if roast is frozen.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugars, apples and vanilla until blended.
Add flour and cinnamon.
Mix well and bake in greased and floured loaf pan for 1 hour or until brown at 325°.

title: corn bread
directions: Pour 1/4 cup oil in measuring cup.
Add milk to fill cup. Stir together dry ingredients, then add the milk and oil mixture. Stir only until mixed well.
Pour 2 to 3 tablespoons oil in pan. Place pan in oven until warm.
Pour mixture in pan and bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix together; put in freezer.

title: easy corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until center is firm.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: low-fat chili
directions: Saute turkey with onion.
Mix package of chili as directed on package and mix with turkey.
In a large pot combine kidney beans and tomato sauce.
Stir in chili and turkey.
Mix well.
Simmer as directed on package of chili.

title: haddock shrimp bake
directions: Place fish in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Spread with soup. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: eggplant, onion and tomato bake
directions: Lightly oil a heavy 3-quart casserole.
Layer the eggplant, onion and tomatoes in the casserole.
Sprinkle with garlic, salt, basil and olive oil.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours. Mix gently.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Garnish with chopped fresh tomatoes before serving.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2 qt. baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until firm.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, salt and butter or margarine thoroughly.
Beat eggs, lemon rind and vanilla.
Cream mixture until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Gradually stir into creamed ingredients.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick and cut into fancy shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes, until light brown around edges.
Remove to cooling rack.

title: pork chops baked in sour cream
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Season chops and dredge in flour. Brown in butter.
Insert clove in each chop and arrange in a baking dish.
Add the rest of the ingredients to the pan drippings; bring to boil and pour over the meat.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for
1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover; turn up heat to 500° and allow chops to brown slightly.

title: garlic bread
directions: Slice bread in half horizontally. Spray each half with cooking spray. Sprinkle with garlic powder and Parmesan cheese. Wrap in aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yields 8 servings.

title: tree bark cookies
directions: Place graham crackers on cookie sheet or jelly roll pan.
In saucepan, melt oleo.
Stir in brown sugar and bring to a boil for a full 2 minutes.
Pour over graham crackers and smooth over. Sprinkle walnut pieces on top.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes. Remove from oven and add chocolate pieces.
Smooth over to give tree bark appearance.
Return to oven for 2 to 3 minutes to melt chocolate, if necessary.
Cool completely.
Break into pieces.

title: peach cobbler(fresh)
directions: Spray Pam in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Put fruit in.
Mix rest of ingredients in bowl and mix.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Melt 2 tablespoons of margarine and sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until brown.

title: baked fish
directions: Grease baking pan with oil.
Place fish in a single layer in pan.
Combine remaining ingredients except parsley and pour over fish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Sprinkle with the parsley.
Serves 2 with 187 calories, 4 g carbohydrate, 8.3 g fat, 224 mg sodium and 42 mg cholesterol each serving.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water, then while still hot, add ice cream.
Stir until melted.
Add fruit cocktail and crushed pineapple.
Mix well.
Refrigerate until set.

title: ho-ho cake
directions: *Open the can; soften over low heat in pan of water or microwave.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Gradually stir milk and egg into pudding.
Mix in saucepan. Add rice and raisins.
Stir over medium heat until mixture just comes to a boil.
Pour into serving bowl.
Sprinkle with spices. Cover with plastic wrap.
Chill one hour.

title: frosty fruit salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Fold in whipped topping and freeze in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Slice 5 minutes before serving.
Can be taken from freezer and placed in refrigerator an hour or two for softer serving.

title: cracker cookies
directions: Melt
almond
bark
and chocolate chips in microwave or over low heat.
Stir until well blended.
Spread peanut butter between two crackers.
Using tongs, dip crackers in chocolate mixture, then
put
on cookie sheet which has been lined with wax
paper. When
cookie sheet is full, cool in refrigerator. Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: sauerkraut slaw
directions: Chop sauerkraut into short pieces.
Mix ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate, stirring occasionally, at least 24 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: rump roast with gravy
directions: In heavy 4-quart pot, heat oil.
Season roast on all sides and put in pot and brown thoroughly.
Remove roast and slice to desired thickness.
Mix flour, onion, green pepper, garlic powder and parsley into oil drippings in pot.
Cook over medium-high heat until brown.
Add about 3 cups water and simmer.
Return roast to gravy and simmer until tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with rice.

title: roman holiday soup
directions: In large saucepan, saute onion and carrots in olive oil until onion is translucent.
Add green beans, macaroni, broth and salt. Bring to boil and simmer about 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender and macaroni is cooked.

title: cinnamon fingers
directions: Cut crusts from bread; roll very flat.
Cream the cream cheese with 1/2 cup white sugar.
Spoon onto bread; roll from corner (like jelly roll).
Dip into melted butter; roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture (coat well).
Bake in 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Done when sugar around edges begins to "candy." Remove while hot; place on wax paper to cool.

title: indian fry bread
directions: In a large bowl combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Stir in water, about 1/4 cup at a time, until mixture forms a stiff dough.
Knead about 5 minutes, until dough is thick and elastic.
Pinch off about 2 tablespoons dough and form very thin round patties, using a rolling pin or hands.
Fry in hot oil (365°), turning once, until brown on each side.
Makes about 24 breads.

title: rich raisin cookies
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar gradually and cream thoroughly. Add whole egg and beat well.
Mix and sift flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon and add to the first mixture alternately with the milk.
Add vanilla, raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet and brush lightly with the slightly beaten egg yolk.
Bake at 375° for about 15 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 275° for 5 hours.

title: cauliflower and peas with curried almonds
directions: Cook cauliflower 10 minutes.
Cook peas according to package directions.
Melt 1 tablespoon of butter over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute.
Add sour cream; cook until well heated.
Combine vegetables, sour cream mixture and add onion salt.
Mix well.
Spoon into lightly greased 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Melt rest of butter in saucepan; stir in curry powder and almonds.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until almonds are golden.
Spoon over cauliflower.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Place pared and sliced potatoes, coated in flour and cheese, in buttered dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Turn once.

title: green salad
directions: In clear glass bowl, layer lettuce, carrots, celery, onions and peas. Spread mayonnaise and sprinkle with 2 teaspoons sugar. Slice pimento olives over mayonnaise. Chill. Just before serving, fry 6 to 8 slices crisp bacon and crumble over top.

title: smothered okra
directions: Saute in butter or bacon drippings, onion, bell pepper and okra.
Add tomatoes.
Cook about 20 minutes.
Add garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste.

title: instant chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Makes enough to fill 2 (2-pound) coffee cans.
For hot chocolate place 2 heaping tablespoons in a cup of boiling water.
Stir and serve.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Toss first 4 ingredients.
Mix salad dressing and whipped cream and mix with fruit.
Serve in bowl or on lettuce leaf.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Roll thin and drop in boiling broth.

title: springerles
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Stir in sugar, beat until thoroughly combined.
Add lemon extract, anise seeds and anise oil.
Mix and sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture and mix thoroughly.
Add 3 to 4 tablespoons milk or enough to get dough to stay together enough to roll.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll on floured board to 1/2-inch thick and mark with springerle roller. Cut squares and set on cookie sheet to dry overnight or 8 to 10 hours.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until browned on bottom.
Store in covered jar.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cook milk and flour or cornstarch until thick; let cool. Cream together butter, shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour mixture; beat 10 minutes.

title: poppy seed loaf
directions: Grease 2 large bread pans.
Mix all ingredients together. Spread batter evenly in prepared pans.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pepperoni cheese wheel
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together cream cheese, Muenster cheese, chopped pepperoni and milk.
Shape cheese mixture into a 4-inch ball; flatten the ball into a wheel shape measuring 4 1/2 x 1 1/2-inches.

title: spinach salad and warm dressing
directions: Prepare spinach.
Add sliced eggs and crumbled bacon.
