Prepare dressing by mixing all dry ingredients with a little of the vinegar.
Beat in oil slowly.
Add remaining vinegar.
Beat again. Heat in saucepan.
Just before serving, toss spinach with warm dressing.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Cream butter and sugar; add salt.
Add eggs, one at a time, alternating with wafer crumbs and milk.
Fold in nuts and coconut.
Bake for 2 hours.

title: italian-style nibble mix
directions: Pour popped corn in 13 x 9-inch baking pan and combine with wheat squares and oat cereal.
Heat in 300° oven about 5 minutes. Remove and drizzle with butter.
Combine cheese and dry salad dressing mix.
Sprinkle over corn and stir.
Makes about 9 cups.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, nuts and flour.
Mix all together and roll.
Leave overnight in a cool place.
Slice thin and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Warm in pot and pour in pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain excess fat from hamburger.
Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Salt to taste.
Sprinkle taco sauce on salad, if desired.

title: chicken-fried round steak
directions: Cut steak into 6 or 8 pieces.
Stir together eggs and milk. Combine cracker crumbs, salt and pepper.
Dip meat in egg mixture, then in crumbs.
In a large skillet, brown meat in hot oil, turning once.
Cover; cook over low heat for 30 to 45 minutes, or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: tropical candied yams
directions: Cook on top of stove for 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, covered, and 5 minutes, uncovered.

title: brazil nut cake
directions: Start heating oven to 300°.
Grease, then line with waxed paper a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
In sifter, put flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In large bowl, place cut up nuts, dates and cherries.
Sift flour mixture and spread evenly in pan.
Bake 1 3/4 hours or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean. Cool.
Wrap in aluminum foil and refrigerate.
Keeps 5 to 6 weeks.

title: love cake
directions: Set your heart at warm temperature.
Mix ingredients smoothly with complete faith in God. Scrape the bowl thoroughly, because the great joy of life is often found at the bottom.
Spread with tenderness and sprinkle with sympathy and Christian loving-kindness.
Cut in large, generous slices.
More goodness may be found underneath than is shown on the surface.
Serve a smile, love and hospitality on a large platter of compassion and understanding.

title: microwave baked beans
directions: Place bacon on paper towel lined plate.
Heat covered with paper towel 3 minutes or until crisp.
In heat resistant microwave-safe 1 1/2-quart casserole combine beans, onion, ketchup, mustard and brown sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle over baked bean mixture.
Heat uncovered in microwave oven 10 minutes or until sauce is bubbly.

title: popcorn candy cake
directions: In a large saucepan, melt marshmallows, oil and oleo until smooth. In a large bowl, combine popcorn, gumdrops and peanuts. Add marshmallow mixture and mix well. Press into a greased 10-inch tube pan. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Dip pan in hot water 5 to 10 seconds to unmold.

title: sweet cucumber pickles
directions: First Day:
Place cucumbers in a stone jar.
Dissolve salt in boiling water and pour over the cucumbers.
Let stand for 24 hours.

title: memory book cookies
directions: Beat margarine at medium speed.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in pecans.
Shape dough into 2 (16-inch) rolls, wrap in wax paper and chill at least 4 hours.
Cut in 1/3-inch slices.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.

title: aunt dora's pecan pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake on lower rack in oven at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: golden lemon cheese pie
directions: In mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in Eagle Brand until smooth.
Stir in RealLemon and vanilla.
Pour into prepared crust.
Top with Golden Lemon Topping.
Chill 3 hours.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on 10 to 12-inch serving platter.
Spread seafood sauce on top of cream cheese.
Sprinkle shrimp on top of seafood sauce.
Line edge of platter with crackers.

title: lemon cream cheese cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Cool slightly.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in Jell-O and lemon juice.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour in cooled graham cracker crust.

title: good morning shake
directions: Place juice and Marshmallow Creme in blender container. Cover; process until well blended.
Add yogurt; process until smooth.
Makes 6 (3/4-cup) servings.

title: butter bean soup
directions: Rinse and pick over beans.
Put in large soup kettle with water.
Bring to boil and turn off heat.
Let sit an hour or so. Add butter.
Turn on heat and bring to boil again.
Turn off heat. By the time this sits awhile the soup will be done.
You can cook in one cooking procedure if you prefer.
You can gauge how much water by how soupy you prefer it.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Good served with cornbread.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cover with the dressing.
Combine melted butter and chicken broth.
Drizzle over dry dressing mix.
Bake 1 hour or less at 350° until hot and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: holiday fruitcake
directions: Grease and flour bottom and sides of 12 cup Bundt tube pan. In a large bowl, combine eggs and water.
Add remaining ingredients, by hand.
Stir until combined.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 30 minutes.
Loosen edges and remove from pan.

title: italian soup
directions: Clean and chop into small pieces the onion, carrot and celery. Put vegetables into 3 1/2-quart saucepan.
Remove sausage from casing and break into small pieces.
Add meat and butter to saucepan with vegetables.
Set saucepan over medium heat; cook ingredients until sausage loses all red color, about 5 minutes. Add chicken broth, chopped, cleaned zucchini, spaghetti pieces and oregano to saucepan.
Add can of tomatoes, breaking the tomatoes apart with your hand.
Cook, stirring gently once or twice, until spaghetti and veggies are cooked (20 to 30 minutes).
Serve with Parmesan cheese grated on top.
Delicious!

title: debbie's baked omelette
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch deep pan with Pam.
Butter bread and place in bottom of pan.
I melt the butter and put it on the bread.
Beat eggs well (I use mixer).
Stir in the remaining ingredients and pour over bread.
Let this set overnight in the refrigerator.
It takes at least 8 hours to make it taste good. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.
Uncover and bake 5 additional minutes.
You can also sprinkle cornflakes on top the last 5 minutes.
Use your imagination.

title: mexicorn dip
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients; mix well.
Serve with corn chips.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken in half a pot of water.
Take off broth and cut chicken into small pieces.
Add all vegetables (use fresh if you have any).
Cook until all vegetables are done.
Add catsup last. Soup will thicken.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in each of 2 round layer pans. Sprinkle enough brown sugar (rather thick) to cover bottom of pans and pat into the butter.
Place 5 slices of pineapple in each pan, then pour half of liquid from pineapple into each pan.
Mix yellow cake mix as directed and pour half in each pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 375°.

title: green rice
directions: Grease pan with oil.
Beat eggs and add to milk.
Mix rice, grated cheese, parsley, garlic and onion together and spread in pan.
Pour egg and milk mixture over the top.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese do floppies
directions: Mix onion, mayonnaise and cheese.
Slightly freeze sandwich loaf.
Cut off crusts, then cut into quarters.
Spread with mixture and sprinkle with paprika.
Place on cookie sheets and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: fruit 'n yogurt pie
directions: Fold yogurt, fruit and Cool Whip, blending well.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Remove from freezer and place in refrigerator 30 minutes before cutting.
Store leftovers in freezer.

title: pie crust(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll out into 2 crusts.
Put strawberry topping in crust.

title: preserved children
directions: Mix the children and dogs together.
Put them on the field. Stir constantly.
Pour brook over pebbles and sprinkle with wildflowers.
Spread over all a deep blue sky.
Bake in the sun. When brown, set away to cool in the tub.

title: molasses curried fruit
directions: Drain syrup from fruit into saucepan.
Bring to a boil; boil rapidly until reduced to 3/4 cup.
Add molasses, vinegar, stick of cinnamon and curry powder.
Add drained fruit; simmer 5 minutes.
Garnish with cherries.
Serve hot or cold.

title: hamburger soup
directions: In a 2-quart pan, boil potatoes until tender. Set aside in water. While cooking potatoes, brown meat and onion in large soup pot.
Drain. Add soup, tomato sauce and beans. Add potatoes and enough water to your liking. Season to taste and simmer until flavors blend. Serve with cornbread or crackers.

title: christmas fruit and nut cake
directions: Moisten as needed.
Mix well; bake in tube pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: blueberry yum yum
directions: Cream together cream cheese, Dream Whip, sugar and milk.
Beat until very stiff.
Melt butter and mix with vanilla wafer crumbs. In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, you will layer mixture.
First put 1/2 of vanilla wafers in bottom of pan, then half of the cream mixture.
Add blueberries, then the rest of cream cheese mixture. Top with rest of wafer crumbs.
Chill 24 hours.
Cherry pie filling may be used.

title: tupperware pie crust
directions: Shake 60 seconds in a Tupperware bowl.

title: creamed turkey(serves 50)
directions: Cook turkey with salt, onion, a couple stalks of celery and couple of carrots for flavor.
Save broth.
In a large kettle (placed over heat), melt butter; add flour and 6 cups broth to make a medium thick sauce.
Add soups and let come to a boil.
Add cooked peas, turkey and pimento.
Let it come to a boil, but still cook over water as it scorches easily.
Serve over baking powder biscuits or toast.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Combine with all other ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Allow to sit 1/2 hour before serving.
tags: cream of broccoli soup or cream of celery

title: speedy tea cakes
directions: Beat eggs with sugar, salt and nutmeg.
Add butter, then add the flour, sifted with the baking powder, alternately with the milk.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls into hot fat and fry for about 3 minutes.
These cakes turn themselves over in the fat.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: southern corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add beaten egg and milk-water.
When oil is piping hot, add to batter. Pour back into pan and bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lo-cal refresher
directions: Add 1 packet Sweet 'N Low to 1/2 glass grape juice.
Add ice cubes.
Fill with club soda and enjoy.

title: shrimp royale
directions: Melt margarine; mix in flour.
Slowly stir in milk.
Cook to a boil and thicken.
Mix in onion, Worcestershire and bread cubes. Cool.
Fold in mayo, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Melt in 2 tablespoons of margarine, adding chopped shrimp; toss slightly and combine.
Put into baking shells.
Reserve 1/2 pound of shrimp to adorn top of shells at the last 3 minutes; place on top of mixture. Lightly sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 450° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: laura's corn pudding
directions: Combine and stir all ingredients.
Place in greased baking dish.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Add water to potatoes, celery, onion, parsley, seasonings and bouillon cube.
Cover and cook until tender.
Blend flour with small amount of milk and stir into vegetable mixture.
Add remaining milk and cheese.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted.

title: tea garden salad from cooking with hougen(richard t. hougen)
directions: Dissolve jello in hot tea.
Add cup of juice from oranges and pineapple.
Add regular orange juice to fill up if needed.
Stir. Place gelatin in refrigerator until thickened.
Drain and cut water chestnuts into slices.
Add chestnuts, pineapple and orange sections to jello.
Spoon mixture into a greased mold.
Refrigerate until set.

title: gramma martin's casserole(pastor martin's favorite)
directions: Brown meat, onion and celery. Add rice, chicken broth, etc. Put in large casserole.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour in a 350° oven. Remove cover and bake 1/2 hour longer.
(If too dry, add 1 cup boiling water with 1 tablespoon butter.)
Serves 8.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Prepare cornbread (first 10 ingredients).
Bake in 425° oven for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate milk shake
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender.
Blend until smooth.

title: bananas frosting
directions: Cream butter until fluffy.
Stir bananas and lemon juice; blend well.
Gradually beat in confectioners sugar until frosting is of spreading consistency.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: In a pan, combine pineapple syrup with chicken broth, brown sugar, vinegar, soy sauce, catsup and cornstarch. Cook, stirring until thickened. At this point, you can refrigerate the sauce as much as a day ahead.

title: onion rings
directions: Combine flour and salt; stir in beer and beat until smooth. Let batter stand for 3 hours.
Cut onions into 1/2-inch slices and dip into batter.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter.
Add eggs and pecans.
Fill pie shell and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: boori(indian bread)
directions: Mix ingredients together with water, just enough to make a dough, not too sticky.
Knead the dough real well.
Cut the dough into small balls as big as golf balls.
Use the rolling pin to roll the balls.
Roll it until they are 1/2-inch thick circles. Heat generous amount of oil in a Chinese wok or a deep pan.
Fry them one at a time.
Turn over when it puffs up and fry other side.

title: microwave deviled eggs
directions: Slice in half the hard cooked eggs.
Take yolks out and mash. Set aside.

title: chicken and dried beef
directions: Arrange dried beef in shallow baking dish.
Wrap bacon strips around each chicken breast.
Arrange over beef.
Spread soup with chicken.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours. Increase heat to 350°.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes longer, basting several times.
Yields 6 servings.
No seasoning is needed other than pepper.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into a bowl and set aside. Combine butter and brown sugar; blend well.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Add dry ingredients and chocolate bits; mix well. Spread into a greased baking pan and bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Cool and cut into squares.
Top with ice cream, if desired.
Makes about 24 squares.

title: punch(slushies)
directions: Combine Jell-O with 9 cups of boiling water; set this aside. Mix sugar and 4 cups of water.
Add this to the Jell-O mixture, then add lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Pour this into containers and freeze.
When ready to serve, set out for about 1/2 hour.
Pour ginger ale over frozen mixture and mix until slushy. Yields 75 cups.
Recipe can be cut in half for smaller servings.

title: champagne cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Beat pudding mix, milk and cream cheese (at room temperature) together until stiff.
Slowly fold in pineapple.
Spread on cooled cake and sprinkle crushed walnuts on top, if desired.

title: oatmeal-raisin cookies
directions: Combine eggs, raisins and vanilla.
Let mixture stand for 1 hour or more.
Thoroughly cream together brown and white sugar and shortening.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Blend into egg/raisin mixture; then oats and nuts (dough will be very stiff).
Roll into balls the size of a walnut and roll in a cinnamon/sugar mixture (1 teaspoon cinnamon with 1 cup sugar). Place on cookie sheet about 3 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and let cool a few minutes before removing from the cookie sheet.
These will keep several weeks, stored in a tightly covered container.
Put waxed paper between layers after cooling completely before storing.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over cabbage in bowl.
Let stand for several minutes to loosen leaves; drain.
Combine ground beef, rice, chopped onion, eggs, salt and pepper in bowl.

title: pepper roast
directions: Take off all fat.
Place slivered garlic in slits in roast. Wet roast under faucet.
Rub lemon pepper all over, kind of pat in.
Add more for good measure and pat on.
Marinate several hours or overnight.
Cook in oven, uncovered, at 200° for one hour, then turn oven as low as it will go and cook for 3 hours. Refrigerate.
When thoroughly cold, cut and serve.

title: one-step lasagna
directions: Combine water and spaghetti sauce in bowl.
Cover bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with 1 1/2 cups sauce.
Spread 1/2 Ricotta on enough uncooked noodles to cover bottom of dish, overlapping on top of sauce.
Sprinkle 1/2 Mozzarella over noodles.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons Parmesan.
Make another layer of sauce, another layer of noodles with remaining Ricotta, Mozzarella and the Parmesan.
Top with layer of dry noodles.
Pour remaining sauce over noodles, spreading to cover.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Cover tightly with heavy duty foil. Bake in preheated (250°) oven for 1 hour or until knife goes easily through noodles.

title: pear relish
directions: Peel pears and grind pears, onions, and pepper.
Mix all ingredients and boil 20 minutes.
Pack into sterilized jars and seal.

title: no egg chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together and beat well.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sirloin tips and noodles
directions: Rub roast well with Lawry's seasoned salt. Place meat, uncovered, in shallow baking dish or pan on wire rack. Bake at 250° for 30 minutes per pound. This will be very juicy and tender.

title: ham and cheese bake
directions: Cube bread and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer onion, ham and cheese on top of bread.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain first 5 ingredients.
Mix remaining ingredients and dissolve in pan.
Heat until sugar melts.
Pour over vegetables.

title: angel dream cake
directions: Mix jello, according to directions, and put in freezer to slightly thicken.
Tear angel food cake into pieces and put in a large bowl.
Mix pudding, according to directions, and stir into cake.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Stir in thickened jello.
Chill until firm.
After chilled, you can decorate with fresh fruit.

title: hungarian chicken
directions: Heat oil; add water and seasonings.
Stir.
Add chicken. Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Remove chicken and cool.
Remove meat from bones and cut into bite size pieces.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: "make ahead" mashed potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a large pot. Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer over medium heat until potatoes are tender. Drain.
Put potatoes in mixing bowl.
Beat with mixer until light and fluffy. Beat in butter and cream cheese (which have been cut in small chunks).
Beat in sour cream, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Transfer mixture to a heavily buttered casserole dish. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate.
Before serving, bring to room temperature, then bake, uncovered, in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.
May be fixed 2 to 3 days ahead.

title: buster bar pie
directions: Food process Oreo cookies until crumbly.
Add 1/2 cup melted butter and mix well.
Press cookie mixture into one 9 x 13-inch pan or two 8-inch pie plates.
Scoop out ice cream or yogurt into pan.
Wrap with Saran Wrap and return to freezer.
In double boiler over medium heat, combine semi-sweet morsels, 1/3 cup margarine and 1/2 cup sugar.
Cook, stirring constantly, until morsels are melted and sugar starts to lose its grainy texture by melting.
Remove ice cream-cookie mixture from freezer and top with fudge sauce.
Sprinkle with peanuts and return to freezer for at least 2 hours.
Thaw slightly before serving so that cutting into servings is easier.

title: spinach, bacon and mushroom salad
directions: Cut the stems off the spinach and wash the leaves well in cold water. Drain leaves and place in a salad bowl. Add bacon and mushrooms. Mix together the vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Pour over salad and toss well. Serves 6.

title: crabcumbers
directions: Scoop out inside of cucumbers with small knife.
Mix other ingredients and stuff inside cucumbers.
Chill.
Slice into desired size slices.
Serve with crackers and enjoy.

title: blackberry jelly
directions: Put your berries on to cook (do not add water).
Save the juice after running them through a colander.
Measure the juice and measure the sugar.
Let the juice boil.
Put the sugar in and dissolve, then bring to a rolling boil and pour into a jar.

title: chicken parmigiano
directions: Dip chicken in egg, then crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Turn chicken; bake 15 minutes more or until tender.
Meanwhile, combine tomato sauce, oregano, sugar and onion salt.
Heat to boiling, stirring frequently.
Pour sauce over meat.
Top with cheese.
Return to oven to melt cheese.
Serves 4.

title: butterscotch slices
directions: Sift flour, measure and sift again with baking powder and salt.
Cream butter.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Beat until fluffy. Add the vanilla and the egg.
Beat well.
Sift in flour mixture. Shape into rolls (1 1/2 inch).
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate for 2 hours.
With sharp knife, cut into 1/8-inch slices; place on cookie sheet a ways apart.
Bake at 375° for 7 minutes.
Yields 54 cookies.

title: hot chocolate mix(makes a great gift)
directions: Sift ingredients together and mix well.
Use 2 to 3 heaping tablespoons in one cup hot water.

title: pralines
directions: Combine ingredients. Cook in large container until it forms a soft ball when tested in cold water. You may use candy thermometer if preferred. Beat until creamy. Add nuts. Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper. You need to do this quickly because ingredients dry and stiffen quickly.

title: nine bean soup
directions: Wash beans and put them into a pot.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans and soak overnight.
Drain beans.
Add 2 quarts water and next four ingredients.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Season to taste.
Makes 8 cups.

title: easy chicken-n-gravy
directions: Batter chicken in the flour and paprika.
Brown in margarine. Put in a casserole.
Pour soups over chicken and bake about 50 minutes.

title: herb cream stuffed mushrooms(serves 16)
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Clean mushrooms; stuff.
(Use stems in other recipe.)
Place in shallow pan, pour thin layer of white wine on bottom.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until bubbly. Remove from pan with slotted spoon.
Serve warm.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: In saucepan, combine soup, milk, cheese and pepper; add noodles and chicken.
Over low heat, heat thoroughly.
Stir often. Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Beat in eggs with a spoon.
Add mashed bananas, flour and baking soda with sour cream. Add nuts.
Put in greased and floured loaf pan.
This makes a very moist banana bread.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix sour cream and cream cheese together. Add Italian dressing and shrimp.
Serve with crackers.

title: coconut shrimp with red curry sauce(yield: about 20 shrimp)
directions: Heat 3-inches of oil in a large deep skillet or heavy pot to 325°.

title: microwave crackle peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in a 2-quart ovenproof glass mixing bowl or pitcher. Cook, uncovered, in microwave oven 6 minutes at High or until sugar is dissolved.
Stir peanuts into syrup.
Cook uncovered in microwave oven for 8 minutes on High. Stir every 2 minutes.
Stir margarine into mixture.
Cook uncovered in microwave oven to hard-crack stage (8 to 10 minutes at High).
Stir every 2 minutes.
Add baking soda and vanilla extract and mix well.
Pour onto two lightly buttered baking sheets, spreading as thinly as possible.
As soon as candy is cool enough to handle, wet hands with water and stretch as thin as desired. Turn candy over and cool completely.
When firm and cool, break into medium-size pieces.
Store in a tightly covered container. Yields about 2 pounds.

title: seafood salad
directions: Combine dressings and cheese. Add other ingredients. Chill. Serve on curly lettuce.

title: ken's chocolate covered cherry pudding
directions: Mix together water, Equal, chocolate extract, cherry extract and Hi-Energy Chocolate Supplement.
Add canola oil and frozen cherries.

title: three layer pie
directions: Cream oleo and flour; add nuts.
Press into square pan (9-inches) and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: chicken breasts and sour cream
directions: Arrange chicken in
single
layer
in
casserole.
Over chicken, pour sauce made by combining soup with sour cream and mushrooms.
Flavor with tarragon
and sherry. Salt if desired. Bake at 325° for 60
minutes
or
until chicken is tender.
Do not cover.

title: western hash
directions: Brown ground beef in a small amount of oil. When ground beef is brown, drain.
Add onion and bell pepper.
When onion is done, add rice and tomatoes. Add salt and pepper to taste. If mixture gets too dry before rice is tender, add more tomatoes.
When rice is tender, put the cheese on top and let melt.

title: rice and broccoli bake
directions: Saute the chopped onion and the chopped celery in butter until tender.
Add the rest of the ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a quick shake bottle.
Refrigerate.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In skillet, cook sausage until browned and drain.
Separate crescents into triangles and press into a 12-inch pizza pan with sides.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Then sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with shredded cheese.
(You can refrigerate a few hours or overnight, if desired.
Cover with foil.)
In a small bowl, beat together eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour over crust and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: punch recipe
directions: Mix all ingredients, then fill 1 gallon jug with water and freeze.
Thaw to slush before serving.

title: chicken casserole(usa)
directions: Cook chicken and pick from the bones, place in the bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix soup with water and pour over the chicken.
Make Stove Top stuffing according to directions on box and spread on top of soup.
Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes.

title: whiskey sour slush
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Freeze at least 8 hours. Put into punch bowl or pitchers; stir until well mixed but still slushy.
Yields 1 gallon.
Serve with orange slices and cherries.

title: cheese and beef ball
directions: Mix all together well and form into a cheese ball or serve ready to dip with Ritz crackers or chips.
Feeds a bunch.

title: cecil's raisin cream pie
directions: Cook raisins and water together for 15 minutes.
Drain liquid, reserving 1/2 cup to be added back to raisins.
(If there isn't enough liquid, water may be added.)
Add to raisin mixture oleo, vinegar, brown sugar mixed with flour, cream or evaporated milk and beaten egg yolks.
Cook over medium heat until thickened. Cool slightly and put into baked 8-inch pie crust.
Top with meringue made from the egg whites and brown in oven.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Heat water and oleo to a boil.
Add flour and mix until it forms a ball.
Let it cool down, then add eggs, one at a time. Spray pan with Pam (9 x 13-inch glass cake dish).
Spread mixture in the bottom of the dish.
Put some on the sides.
Bake 35 minutes at 350° (should be fluffy and airy).
Let cool.
Beat together milk and pudding.
When thick, add cream cheese and pour over crust; then cover with Cool Whip.
Drizzle top with Hershey's chocolate syrup.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Drain the juice from the beans and simmer it with the bacon grease and dill seed for about 45 minutes. Pour over the beans.
Marinate overnight.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Set aside 1 cup dry cake mix.
Combine rest with 1/2 cup melted margarine and 1 egg.
(This will be thick.)
Pat this in lightly greased pan (9 x 13-inches).
Combine pumpkin, brown sugar, 3 eggs and spices.
While mixing add evaporated milk.
Pour over cake mixture.

title: family beef-vegetable casserole
directions: Place a layer of potatoes and carrots alternately in a greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Place crumbled hamburger on top. Pour in soups.
Stir gently.
Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 325°.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix well, then add 1 cup of pecans.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: lauren's sweet bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan and place in oven to melt butter.
Remove pan from oven and sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over butter, pressing down with a fork. Sprinkle coconut over crumbs.
Add a layer of nuts and one of marshmallow.
Drizzle condensed milk evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven and drizzle with melted chocolate.
Let cool before slicing.

title: orange-marshmallow-rice confetti
directions: Empty mandarin oranges into a large bowl.
Add marshmallows and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Drain if necessary.
Add cold rice and walnuts.
Prepare dessert topping mix as directed, then fold in gently into rice and orange mixture.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Just before serving, stir up mixture and lightly pile in serving dish. May garnish with oranges.
Makes 12 generous servings.

title: seafoam frosting
directions: Mix in top of double boiler and beat over boiling water with mixer
for 7 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Remove from over water and
stir
with
spoon
until
of
desired consistency. (Ready almost
immediately.)
Add
cup chopped nuts, if desired. Spread on cake.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
In a casserole dish, put chicken on the bottom and top with broccoli.
Pour mixture over chicken and broccoli.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 casserole dishes.

title: mexican hamburgers
directions: Divide hamburger meat into 16 thin patties.
Mix chilies and picante together to make sauce.
Cut cheese into thin slices and spread approximately 1 tablespoon of sauce mix (enough to cover area) on a meat patty staying approximately 1/2-inch from the edges.
Cover the sauce with one layer of cheese slices.
Top with second patty and crimp edges together to seal.
Continue process until all 8 burgers are assembled.	Salt and pepper to taste and cook on outdoor grill.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil, debone and chop chicken; place on bottom of casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Top with chopped onion, crushed Doritos and grated cheese.
Combine soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes together, stirring until well blended.
Pour on top of chicken mixture evenly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Peel and chop potatoes; boil with 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
Drain and mash.
Add butter, sugar, marshmallows, vanilla and seasonings.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: grandma florence's pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time. Beat well after each egg.
Gradually add flour, salt and vanilla. Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water. Add pineapple juice and chill. Add ginger ale just before serving.
Pour over ice or sherbet. Makes 50 servings.

title: easy banana nut bread
directions: Whip bananas until creamy.
Mix butter, eggs and cake mix together.
Add bananas and pecans; mix well until smooth.
Pour into 2 small loaf pans and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all cheeses at room temperature and add onion juice. Combine nuts and parsley; add 2/3 of mix to cheese.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Roll into ball or an appropriate shape for the season and cover with remaining parsley-nut mixture.
Remove from refrigerator at least 1 hour before serving.
Serve with unflavored crackers. Better if made several days in advance to blend flavors.
Can be frozen for future use.

title: pork rolls(healthy food)
directions: Bring a
full pan of water to a boil.
Add one piece of pork at a time.
Once pork is completely done, remove from the water. Mix
the soy sauce and mustard together.
Dip the pork in sauce. Place
pork
on
a
large
piece of lettuce and add slices
of celery.
Carefully
roll the pork and celery up in the lettuce. This dish is nonfattening, so serve and enjoy!

title: nannie's chicken and dumplings
directions: Cover chicken in water.
Add salt, butter, pepper and sage. Boil until tender.
Remove chicken and set aside.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix crushed pineapple and cream cheese.
Add pecans, onion, green pepper and seasoning salt.
Roll in a ball and chill.
Roll cheese ball in 1 cup of nuts, finely chopped.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: mustard sauce(serves 1)
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Let stand before serving, about 20 minutes.

title: strawberries and sour cream
directions: Dissolve jello with water.
Add strawberries (drained) and pecans.
Pour half of mixture in mold after it sets up.
Spread layer of sour cream and add remaining mixture on top.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Beat eggs very light. Gradually beat in the sugar. Add rest of the ingredients.
Put 2/3 of the batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread 1 can cherry pie filling over batter, then remainder of the batter.
You may sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon or after baked, glaze with thin powdered sugar frosting.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 40 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix water, sugar, vinegar and oil, pour over combined vegetables.
Will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in two 8 to 9-inch round pans or a 9 x 13-inch loaf pan that has been greased and floured. Bake in 350° to 375° oven for 25 minutes (or longer if necessary). Cool and spread with icing.

title: wild rice, cranberry and chicken salad
directions: In a saucepan, cook cranberries in a small amount of water until skin begins to pop.
Drain and place in a large bowl. Drizzle with honey to coat.
Cut sections of oranges in half. Combine orange sections, rice, chicken and walnuts with the cranberries.

title: aunt lucy's yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons hot water.
Mix in all ingredients.
Mix well.
Place on floured board.
Sprinkle with flour and knead well.
Keep adding flour until it is the desired thickness of biscuit dough.
Cover and place in the refrigerator. It will keep several days.
Pinch off what you want to bake; roll out on floured board and cut out.
A juice glass makes an ideal biscuit cutter.
Place in greased bread pan and bake at 400° for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: marinara sauce for pasta
directions: In a large saucepan, heat oil over medium heat.
Add garlic and saute for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add parsley and onion.
Slowly add tomatoes.
Stir to break up tomatoes.
Add bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer sauce over low heat for about 15 minutes for flavors to blend.
Serve sauce with spaghetti or other pasta dishes or with rice.

title: cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; heat in crock-pot.
Serve over nachos, crackers or just in a bowl.

title: "counry cabbage"
directions: Saute onions, bell peppers and celery.
Add chopped cabbage and pour tomatoes on top.
Place lid on and cook slowly.
Stir. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: burrito enchilada
directions: Sauce:
Mix one can of Hunt's special sauce and enchilada mix on stove in a saucepan with 1/2 can of water.
Bring to a boil about 5 minutes.
Let stand with lid. Remove from fire.

title: norwegian crown cake
directions: Blend flour and butter together 5 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients, blending thoroughly.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: doreen's pound cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat margarine and shortening until creamed.
Gradually add sugar, then eggs, one at a time.
Beat well, then add flour mixture, alternately with milk and flavoring.
Mix well.
Pour into a 10-inch tube pan or 3 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Blend 1st 3 ingredients well.
Add remaining ingredients. Spoon onto cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar on top. Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes.
(A very soft cookie.)

title: kid tested veggie bites
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Brush bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with 1 tablespoon of melted margarine.
Beat egg and water with a fork in a shallow dish.
Mix flour and salt in another dish.
Dip vegetables into egg mixture and then roll in flour mixture to coat. Place in pan.

title: mandarin pork roast
directions: Sprinkle roast with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Spread mustard over roast.
Cover with foil tent (do not seal completely) and bake at 325° until tender, approximately 2 to 3 hours.
Drain oranges.
Save liquid and mix with next six ingredients.
Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and thick.
Add onion, pepper and oranges.
Spoon over roast and bake at 400° for 30 more minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, milk, vanilla and rice.
Bake at 350 degrees until knife comes out clean and pudding is lightly browned on top.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with garlic salt, salt and pepper to taste.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coffee can pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour 3 coffee cans.
Preheat oven to 350°. Combine ingredients.
Mix well and pour into coffee cans.
Fill 1/2 to 3/4; set on counter for 20 minutes, then bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Cut cake in half. Slice ice cream.
Alternate layers of ice cream and cake. Frost with Cool Whip.
Put back in freezer until ready to serve.

title: rocky road treat
directions: Heat chips, milk and margarine over low heat until chips are melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan, covered with waxed paper.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: bunuelos (mexican cookies)
directions: In a large bowl, mix the flour, milk, margarine, salt, baking powder and egg with 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Put dough on floured board and knead until smooth.
Divide dough into 36 (1-inch) balls and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Place balls between 2 sheets of waxed paper 3 inches apart.
Roll with rolling pin until dough is paper thin.
Peel off paper.
In deep, hot oil in electric skillet at 370°, fry pastries, four at a time, for 45 seconds on each side. Drain on paper towels.

title: cheese squares
directions: Grease pan.
Place one package of rolls in the pan.
Mix rest of ingredients together (except egg white).
Spread on top of dough (in pan).
Place other package of rolls on top.
Spread egg white on top of dough.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter and pecans.
Melt butter and add to mixture, then add pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain off fat.
Add all ingredients.
Cook sauce for 45 minutes.
Cook noodles.
Layer noodles, sauce and cheese. Repeat until all is used.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: sugar-free peanut butter pie
directions: Mix sugar-free vanilla pudding with milk according to directions
in blender.
Add peanut butter.
Blend until smooth. Pour into a cooled crust. Top with Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients and brown.
Makes 180 meatballs.
For sauce, mix tomato paste, tomato sauce and water.
Cook on low for 1 hour; add another can Parmesan cheese and simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook together the hamburger and diced onion. Drain off grease. Add beans with above ingredients and bake for about 1 hour at 350°.
This is a favorite with my family.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, nuts, dates, flour and baking powder together.
Will be thick.
Grease and flour 8-inch cake pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Cook.
Break up and mix with Cool Whip. Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Split chiles; remove seeds and rinse.
Alternate chilies, cheese, chiles in 3 layers.
Beat eggs, flour and salt.
Blend in evaporated milk.
Pour mixture over chiles and cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: glazed apple cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg, then add dry ingredients which have been sifted together alternately with cream.
Add apples, nuts and raisins.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet about an inch apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
While still slightly warm, frost with thin powdered sugar frosting to make a glaze.

title: stuffed french stick
directions: Mix margarine and garlic, spread on 1 half of bread.
Sprinkle grated cheese, parsley and basil on top.
Layer tomato and add Mozzarella on top.
Shake pepper to taste.
Cover with other half of loaf.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Serve with salad and crock of soup.
Yum!

title: low sugar chocolate chip cookies
directions: *If you want chocolate cookies, add 2 tablespoons of cocoa powder to flour mixture

title: chicken loaf supreme
directions: Beat eggs, add milk and mix with the chicken, bread cubes, onion, celery and pimento.
Spread in shallow pan.

title: amaretto fudge
directions: In a large saucepan, combine all ingredients and brush sides of pan with butter or margarine.

Stir over moderate heat until sugar is dissolved, then bring to boil and cook without stirring until 238° is reached on candy thermometer or until a small amount forms a soft ball when dropped in water.
Remove from heat and let stand until 140° is reached.
Beat with spoon until mixture begins to thicken slightly (mixture will be shiny).
Pour quickly into a foil-lined 8-inch pan (square).
Let stand until hard and cool. Remove from pan, peeling foil away and cut with sharp knife into 1-inch squares.
Delicious!

title: mile high pie
directions: Beat the Dream Whip according to directions; set aside.
Beat together the egg whites, lemon juice and strawberries.
Slowly add sugar; beat about 15 minutes.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Pour into cookie crusts and freeze.

title: quick strawberry daiquiri pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, combine crackers, sugar and margarine or butter.
Mix well and press in bottom and up sides of 9-inch pie pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: "zero" herb dressing
directions: In a bowl, whisk all ingredients until well blended. Alternately combine all ingredients in a jar; secure lid and shake until well blended. Remove garlic before serving. Makes 1 cup fat-free dressing. Great for all tossed salads/veggies!

title: vegetable dish
directions: Mix soup, eggs and a little water.
Beat well. Add mayonnaise and mix well.
Add cheese and 3/4 of onion rings.
Pour over vegetables and mix well.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Last 10 minutes, add rest of onion rings.
Make an extra one and take to a friend.

title: tomato pie
directions: Add all ingredients to pie shell in layers in order given. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: williamsburg gingerbread cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add spices, lemon flavoring and milk, blending well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with molasses to make smooth dough.
Chill in refrigerator 2 hours. Roll out dough 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with fancy cutter and bake on greased and lightly floured cookie sheets until done, about 8 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes 5 dozen large cookies.

title: baked easter lamb dinner
directions: In large baking or roasting pan, combine all ingredients well. Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Garnish with fresh mint leaves.
Serves a family of 8 to 10 people.

title: apricot salad
directions: Drain fruits and reserve juices.
Add enough water to fruit juice to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Heat juice in small saucepan. Dissolve gelatin in heated juices.
Allow to cool.
Add apricots, pineapple, lemon juice and brandy.
Pour into lightly greased quart casserole or 6 (6 ounce) individual molds.
Chill until set. Unmold on plate with lettuce leaves.
Top with mayonnaise.

title: swirled mint cookies
directions: Combine flour and baking powder.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter or margarine until softened.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg, vanilla and peppermint extract; beat well.
Add flour mixture and beat until well mixed.
Divide into thirds.
Stir red coloring into one, stir green and leave third plain.
Cover each and chill about 1 hour.
Roll each of the doughs into 1/2-inch diameter ropes.
Using one rope of each color, braid the colors. Slice the twisted ropes into 1/2-inch pieces.
Shape each slice into a ball.
Place on cookie sheet and flatten to 1/4-inch thick with bottom of glass that has been dipped in sugar.
Bake in a 375° oven until done (8 to 10 minutes for large cookies and 6 to 8 minutes for small ones).
Remove and cool.
Makes about 72 (2 1/2-inch) or 144 (1 1/4-inch) cookies.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown onion and hamburger.
Mix together soups, milk and jalapenos (to taste); add to meat.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, put 1/2 of meat mixture with cheese and tortillas, then put remaining meat mixture and top with tortillas and cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.
You may wish to put crushed tortillas on top.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix thoroughly; make small balls.
Fry in hot oil.

title: beef brisket
directions: Mix first four ingredients together; pour over brisket and wrap securely in foil.
Bake in pan at 325° for 1 hour per pound. Separate gravy and meat.
Refrigerate overnight.
Skim off grease from gravy.
Slice real thin and pour gravy over meat.
Either serve or freeze.
May heat and eat.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Heat soups, mushrooms and milk.
Add chicken.
Butter casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: famous jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add other ingredients and stir together.
This makes four thick layers.
Put together with icing.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased, floured pans.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: hungarian kossuth cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until smooth.
Add egg yolks, 2 at a time.
Add flour and baking powder.
Beat egg whites stiff. Fold into mix until blended.
Pour into lightly greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until spongy.
Do not overbake.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli to package directions.
Mix in casserole dish the broccoli, onions, celery and rice.
Drop cheese over top. Pour over all ingredients the cream of chicken and mushroom soups. Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Empty peaches and juice in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Slice butter across top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook the zucchini for 4 minutes. Drain. Gently stir in carrots, onion, 1/2 cup stuffing, sour cream and soup.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt the oleo.
Toss with remaining stuffing. Top casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: millie's salad
directions: Prepare 24 hours ahead.

title: black bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and toss gently.
Let salad rest, loosely covered, at room temperature for at least 1 hour before serving.
You may want to double this recipe.
It goes in a hurry.
Makes 6 servings.

title: asian roast pork
directions: Combine soy sauce, marmalade (or apricot preserves), ketchup and crushed garlic.
Brush all over roast.
Place in slow cooker and pour remaining sauce over all.
Cover and cook all day on low, at least 10 hours.
(Cook on high 5 to 6 hours.)

title: strawberry soup
directions: Clean and puree strawberries in blender.
Combine pureed berries, orange juice, lemon juice and cornstarch in a saucepan. Cook over low-medium heat until mixture becomes thick and clear; stir constantly.
Let cool to room temperature.
Add wine.
Chill before serving.
Serve in soup bowls with a dollop of dairy sour cream.

title: family reunion ham loaf
directions: Slightly beat eggs. Combine eggs with tomato soup, milk and cracker crumbs. Add to ground meat and mix thoroughly.
Pack into 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sinful cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 egg and butter.
Blend well.
Fold in nuts.
Put in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mandarin orange delight
directions: Mix dry Jell-O into cottage cheese.
Mix real well.
Drain pineapple.
Add it next.
Add mandarin oranges and a container of Cool Whip.

title: nutty chicken
directions: Mix together peanuts, crumbs and seasonings.
Dip chicken pieces in broth and then in peanut mixture.
Coat all over.
Place in a single layer on lightly greased foil lined baking pan.
Bake at 400° for approximately 40 to 45 minutes for bone in chicken or 30 to 35 minutes for boneless chicken.
Do not turn during baking.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread thin layer of cream cheese in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Then layer in order listed with taco sauce poured over top. Serve with taco chips.

title: cuban beans
directions: Saute onion, garlic and green pepper in 1 tablespoon of oil. Add 1 teaspoon of sugar and remaining ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook over low heat for 45 minutes.
Squeeze an orange over this mixture and serve with plantain chips.

title: surprise meringues
directions: Beat egg whites, salt, cream of tartar and vanilla until soft peaks form.
Add sugar gradually, beating until peaks are stiff. Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.

title: olive-cheese balls
directions: Work cheese and flour together until crumbly.
Add margarine and mix well with fork.
(If dough seems dry, work with hands.) Mold 1 teaspoon or more of dough around each olive; shape into ball.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Cover and chill 1 hour or longer.
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes about 3 dozen balls.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: In a large bowl, combine cucumbers, onion and red pepper. Sprinkle with salt and mix well. Let stand one hour. Drain. In a medium bowl, combine sugar, vinegar, celery seed, mustard seed; stir until sugar is dissolved. Place cucumber mixture in nonmetal container. Pour vinegar mixture over cucumbers. Cover and chill for at least 24 hours to blend flavors. Makes about 8 cups.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in halves lengthwise.
Remove yolks; mash with fork. Add remaining ingredients.
Whip until smooth and fluffy.
Fill eggs.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Cook onion in margarine until tender.
Combine milk and cream of chicken soup.
Cook rice according to directions on package.
Add all ingredients together.
Top with cheese.
Bake in a casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: irish soda bread(a must for saint patrick's day)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter 2 (8-inch) round cake pans. Combine flour, sugar, caraway seed, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Mix buttermilk and soda in small bowl.
Gradually add buttermilk to flour mixture, stirring with a wooden spoon until blended.
Add raisins.
Mix dough with hands to blend well. Divide dough in half and transfer to pans.
Bake until top is browned and loaves test done, about 1 hour.
Let cool slightly. Turn loaves out onto wire racks and cool completely.
Great with Irish stew.

title: empanadas de carne (meat empanada)
directions: Cover meat with water.
Cook meat until tender; save the stock.
Fry vegetables in a little oil.
Add 1 cup of meat stock. Boil for 2 minutes.
Add the meat, which has been finely chopped. Boil, until well mixed, 5 minutes.
Add the chopped, cooked eggs, salt, pepper, garlic and parsley.

title: beef tips
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place all ingredients in a 3-quart casserole.
Cover tightly.
Bake for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: potato mixture
directions: Mix and spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle lightly with flavored bread crumbs.
Dot sparingly with margarine.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown ground meat.
Grease and heat large skillet.
Sprinkle very thin layer of cornmeal in skillet and let brown slightly. Pour 1/2 the batter in skillet.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over batter, then the meat, onion and peppers.
Pour remaining batter on top.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the cheese.
Lay cheese on top of mixture.
Heat in microwave and serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: microwave nachos
directions: Place sheet of wax paper on 10-inch glass or paper plate. Cover with tortilla chips.
Sprinkle with cheese and microwave at Medium for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until cheese melts, rotating once or twice.

title: spanish rice
directions: In large skillet, fry bacon until crisp; drain on paper towel. Reserve 2 tablespoons drippings.
Cook rice, onion and green pepper in drippings until onion is tender.
Add crumbled bacon and remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, 30 to 45 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Yield:
5 to 6 servings.

title: overnight almond coffee cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan and lightly dust with flour. Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, sour cream and almond extract, mixing well. Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and nutmeg. Add to wet ingredients, mixing well. Spread into baking pan.

title: 1-2-3-4 marble cake
directions: Cream
shortening
and	sugar together.
Add eggs.
Add flour (sifted with baking powder) alternately with milk.	Add flavoring as	desired.
Separate
batter
into
3 parts.
Add desired coloring
or spice to each.
May leave 1 plain.
Drop by spoonfuls, alternating colors, into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: meringue kisses
directions: You can change the taste and flavor of these light, airy cookies by substituting your favorite dried fruit.

title: egg rolls made easy
directions: Fry ground beef, stirring until loose; drain.
Put in large bowl.
If using shrimp, cook, peel and cut into small pieces. Shred cabbage and carrot on cole slaw cutter; add to meat.
Add diced onion, soy sauce, salt and pepper to taste and mix well. Let egg roll wraps thaw at room temperature.
Peel one at a time very slowly so not to tear.

Fill with mixture (about tablespoon full) and wrap, making sure ends are tucked in while wrapping. While wrapping about half of them, let oil or Crisco get hot in skillet (medium heat about half full) and start to fry, laying fold side down.
Turn when golden brown.
Take out and lay on paper towel, then do other half of wraps.
Makes about 50; they can be frozen before frying.

title: rose's legendary honey cake
directions: Pour into angel or bundt pan. Bake 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Raisins, fruit or nuts may be added.

title: orange glaze cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, oil, water, eggs and box of jello; beat about 5 minutes.
Bake in tube pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
For the glaze, beat the powdered sugar and juice of one orange and pour on cake while hot.
You may use strawberries and strawberry jello if you wish.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix flour, cheese and pepper.
Add butter and mix well.
Shape with hands into biscuit size.
Put half pecan on top of each biscuit.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 325°.

title: chess pie
directions: Set oven to 300°.
Cream butter and white sugar. Add beaten whole eggs. Add vanilla, vinegar and salt to mixture. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 300° for 10 minutes, then 350° for 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream peanut butter, margarine and sugars.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Stir in dry ingredients, alternately with milk. Add vanilla.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: banana nut cake(sugar-free)
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add all remaining ingredients except walnuts.
Mix well.
Stir in walnuts.
Spread into well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool 15 minutes. Glaze with a mixture of 3 ounces cream cheese (any kind), 2 tablespoons thawed apple juice concentrate, 1/4 teaspoon vanilla and 1/8 teaspoon cinnamon.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni for 10 minutes.
Combine milk, butter, salt, pepper, parsley flakes and garlic; heat until hot, but not boiling.
When macaroni is done, put 1/2 cup of the milk mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan, then add half the macaroni, half the remaining milk mixture and half the cheese.
Repeat the layers, ending with Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: date nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease loaf pan. Combine first 3 ingredients. Cover and cool. Combine dry ingredients.
Set aside. Cream the sugar and egg together.
Add to date mixture alternately with dry ingredients. Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased pan. Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 325°.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking! Cool on rack.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, saute onion, celery and broccoli in butter for 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese, soup and milk until smooth.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add tomato soup and cream cheese; bring to a boil.
Cool about 10 minutes in the refrigerator.

title: super cake
directions: Layer pineapple and fruit pie filling. Add cake mix.
Melt oleo; pour over cake mix.
Add chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in 1 1/2-quart greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top with 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese and continue baking for 10 more minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar and oil.
Mix together flour, cinnamon, salt, soda and baking powder.
Then add vanilla, zucchini and nuts.
Divide into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 325° approximately 60 minutes.

title: marinated port wine roast
directions: Combine brown sugar, soy sauce, Port wine, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Place beef in marinade and marinate overnight (turning at least once).
Grill meat over open flame or roast at 375° until done.

title: artichoke pie
directions: Place pie crust in pie pan and flute edges.
Dice garlic. Place oil, artichokes and garlic in pan and saute.
In a medium size bowl, beat the eggs and add 1/4 cup grated cheese.
Add Mozzarella and artichokes and garlic.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Lower the oven temperature to 350° and bake for 35 minutes.
Take out of the oven. Wait until cooled and then serve.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix well and drop on greased pan.
Bake in hot oven (about 400°).

title: italian loaf
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, bell pepper, mushrooms and salt, pepper and Italian seasonings.
Drain fat and add 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese, Philadelphia cream cheese and 1/2 cup water.
Heat until melted and creamy.
Place bread onto aluminum foil.
Slice off top of French bread, hollow the middle of the bread.
Layer 2 Mozzarella cheese slices into bottom of bread.
Pour mixture into bread, place 2 slices of Mozzarella cheese slices over mixture and place bread top back on top.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Slice and serve with salad.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix and sift flour, salt and soda in large bowl.
Add sugar, egg and fruit cocktail.
Mix by hand well and pour in well-greased large rectangle pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut in squares while hot and glaze with icing.

title: chicken and asparagus casserole
directions: Step 1:
Arrange chicken breasts skin side up in a 12 x 8-inch microwave-safe baking dish.
Cover with waxed paper.

title: linguine with tomatoes and basil
directions: Combine tomatoes, Brie cheese, basil, garlic, 1 cup oil, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper in a large serving bowl.
Prepare at least 2 hours before serving and set aside, covered, at room temperature. Ten minutes before serving, bring 6 quarts of water to a boil in a large pot.
Add 1 tablespoon oil and remaining salt.
Add linguine and boil until tender, but still firm, 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain pasta and immediately toss with the tomato sauce.
Serve at once, passing the peppermill and grated Parmesan cheese, if you like. Makes 4 to 6 portions.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Make small balls, 1-inch.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Don't get too brown!
Serve hot or warm.
Makes about 55 balls.

title: lemon glaze
directions: In small bowl, blend together until smooth.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Sprinkle pecans in bottom of baked pie shell.
In medium bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add sugar and beat until smooth. Beat in Cool Whip.
Pour into shell and top with blueberry filling.

title: l.a. dirty rice
directions: Cook rice per directions.
Set aside.
Fry bacon strips on medium heat and remove from pan.
Leave drippings in pan.
Add sausage and stir until heated.
Add remaining ingredients, except peas.
Saute until tender and hot.
Turn off heat.
Add cooked rice to ingredients, folding rice until completely mixed.
Add peas, folding gently.
Add additional seasonings, if desired.
Top with paprika and parsley for color.
Crumble bacon strips on top.
Eat! Serves 6.

title: rice krispies chocolate chip treats
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter.
Add marshmallows.
Blend until marshmallows are smooth (melted).
Remove from heat.
Wait, then add chocolate morsels.
(Don't want them to melt.)
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir until well coated and morsels well mixed.
Place in rectangular baking pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares. Enjoy!

title: festive spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach until dry. In medium bowl, stir together spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix, water chestnuts and green onions. Cover; refrigerate. If desired, serve with pumpernickel bread or crackers. Makes 3 cups.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, milk, vanilla, flour and margarine until all ingredients are combined.
Fold in coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Crust forms as pie bakes.

title: oatmeal wheat bread
directions: Combine 2 cups boiling water, margarine, salt, lecithin, honey and oats in mixing bowl and set aside.

title: almond roca
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in heavy pan and keep on low heat. Cook until temperature reaches 300°.
Pour into large buttered pan.
Let set 10 minutes.
Add 1/2 bag of milk chocolate chips on top.
When melted, spread evenly.
Spread ground almonds all over the top.
Let set until cool.
Hit bottom of pan on countertop to break into pieces.

title: sausage spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti in salted water and drain.
Boil broccoli and onion until tender and drain.
Cut up sausage and tomatoes.
Stir tomato juice and soup until well bended.
Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish and bake uncovered at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Spread over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Garnish with pineapple and green peppers and uncover last 1/2 hour.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken in oil in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients and cook covered until done, about 40 minutes.
Yields 2 servings.

title: red pasta fagioli(calabrese style)
directions: Mix together tomato sauce and paste with equal amounts of water in pan; add next 6 spices.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add Great Northern beans and cooked vermicelli (if sauce is too thick, thin with water used to cook vermicelli). Pour into bowls.
Season with Parmesan cheese.
Dip buttered Italian bread in soup and enjoy.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Preboil dry beans until soft.
Drain well.
Place all ingredients in crock-pot in order listed.
Stir, cover and cook on low heat for 10 to 12 hours (high 5 to 6 hours).
Recipe may be halved.

title: sweet and sour smokies
directions: Warm the sausages in a heavy skillet.
Combine the chili sauce, preserves, and brown sugar.
Mix well. Pour over sausages and heat thoroughly.
Serve hot in a chafing dish.
Makes about 80 smokies.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles as per package directions. Brown hamburger, garlic and onion. Mix together sauce, tomatoes and seasonings with hamburger. Layer noodles, hamburger mixture, cottage cheese and cheeses. Cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: quick and easy cranberry salad
directions: Mix 2 packages raspberry Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water.
Mix well.
Add 1 small can crushed pineapple (undrained) and 1 can of cranberry sauce and, if you choose, 1 cup chopped nuts.
Put in refrigerator.

title: banana chocolate chip bread
directions: Cream sugar, butter and egg together in large mixing bowl. Beat until fluffy.
Set aside.
Combine bananas and milk in small bowl.
Set aside.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda together. Stir by hand all ingredients, including chips and nuts.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool on rack.

title: fried rice
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Add rice.
Cook over low heat for 2 or 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add eggs and soy sauce.
Continue cooking until eggs are cooked, stirring occasionally.

title: old-timey potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in salt water until well done.
Drain and add raw egg and margarine. Mash together until potatoes are soft and fluffy.
Add diced onions and vinegar.
Mix together. Sprinkle with pepper.
Serve warm.

title: pastry crust mix
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Blend in shortening with a knife or pastry blender until mixture is of pebbly consistency. Store in covered container in refrigerator.
When needed, measure these amounts:

title: chicken almond casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until tender.
Stir in soup and chicken broth; heat until boiling.
Combine cornstarch, lemon juice and soy sauce; mix until smooth.
Add to soup mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add chicken, almonds, salt and pepper; mix well.
Put in casserole.
Can be refrigerated for several days.
Just before serving, place in a 350° oven until heated through.
Serve over rice.
This is excellent for a meal that must be prepared ahead of time.

title: salsa piquante
directions: Mix all ingredients; simmer for 15 minutes.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes a little more than a pint.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish, mixing well.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.
Has 399 calories per serving.

title: strawberry shortcake delight
directions: Cut cake in half to make 2 layers.
Spoon out center of bottom layer.
Place pieces in center hole.
Drain strawberries and save juice.
Fill bottom layer with ice cream.
Poke holes all around bottom layer.
Pour 1/2 juice over bottom layer and top with 1/2 strawberries.
Place top layer over bottom layer.
Poke holes in top layer.
Pour other half of juice over top layer.
Frost with Cool Whip and top with other 1/2 of strawberries.

title: no cook chocolate fudge
directions: In medium bowl with electric mixer on high, beat cheese, butter, vanilla and salt until smooth.
With wooden spoon, stir in cocoa, sugar and milk until well blended.
Press into foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill 3 hours.
Remove and cut into pieces. Must be kept chilled.

title: "bisquick" mix
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Crisco oil.
Mix well.
Pour Crisco oil over and mix until very fine.
Store in airtight container in cool dry place.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken.
Cut in good sized chunks.
Mix chicken, vegetables and soup.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with one can crescent rolls. Pour in mixture.
Top with remaining rolls.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Remove party rolls from tray.
Slice in half.
Combine margarine, mustard, poppy seed and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread on both sides of rolls.
Distribute the chopped ham and grated cheese evenly between the two packages of rolls.
Place back in trays.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until rolls are hot and cheese is melted.

title: fruit cocktail dessert
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add egg and fruit cocktail.
Mix with a spoon.
Put in pan and sprinkle brown sugar and chopped nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: dip
directions: Spray baking dish and add beans, salsa mix and hamburger which has been mixed together. Sprinkle with mild cheddar cheese. Place in oven until cheese melts. Serve with chips.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all ingredients well, Chill for one hour before serving.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add salt and pepper.
In separate pan, combine the mushroom soup, chicken soup, enchilada sauce, chilies and condensed milk. Cook until hot, stirring often to keep from scorching.
Add meat to mixture.
Crush doritos and line the botton of a casserole dish.
Pour meat and soup mixture over doritos, sprinkle with cheese.
Add another layer of doritos, meat/soup mixture and cheese on top.
Place in hot oven until cheese is melted.

title: shrimp and cream cheese appetizer
directions: Place package of cream cheese on serving plate.
Cover with shrimp cocktail.
Serve with crackers.

title: green chili pie
directions: Chop onion fine and fry in small amount of oil until tender. Add chopped green chilies and 1 cup of water; simmer 5 minutes. Butter a casserole.
Put a layer of Fritos, layer of grated or sliced Velveeta and layer of chili-onion sauce.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Cut in shortening until the consistency of small peas. Stir in buttermilk. Roll out and cut into 10 to 12 biscuits. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale thoroughly.
Chill. When ready to serve, add ginger ale and pour over ice ring made with pineapple chunks and lime slices.
Makes approximately 30 cups.

title: hamburger and potato casserole
directions: Make hamburger patties; flour top and bottom. Brown in skillet, then add cream of mushroom soup. Slice 5 or 6 potatoes and add them with 1/2 cup water. Salt and pepper to taste. Cook until potatoes are tender.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Rinse and dry potatoes Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through.
Place potatoes in a microsafe dish or pan. Sprinkle with melted butter and chopped herbs Microwave on HIGH power for 10 minutes, rearranging the potatoes after 5 minutes. Let rest for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Microwave for another 4-6 minutes on HIGH until cheeses are melted and potatoes are soft.
Sprinkle with salt.

title: lajuana's chocolate coffee
directions: Combine ingredients and store in a jar.
To make 1 cup coffee, mix 5 to 6 tablespoons of mix with 8 ounces boiling water.

title: amaretto compote
directions: In saucepan combine water, prunes and apricots.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and let stand for 15 minutes.
Drain, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
In same pan, combine the reserved liquid, pears, Amaretto, sugar and lemon peel.
Bring to boiling, reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes or until pears are crisp-tender.
Stir in prunes and apricots; heat through. Spoon into 4 individual serving dishes.
Serve warm.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hungarian cabbage
directions: Cook bacon in medium skillet until crisp.
Remove from skillet.
Crumble bacon, and set aside.
Add cabbage, salt, pepper, vinegar (if desired) over low heat.
Stir occasionally. Cabbage should be tender, but crisp.
Transfer cabbage to serving dish and top with bacon.
Serve hot.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Combine avocado, beans and lime juice in a food processor process until blended and smooth or can mash ingredients together with a fork. Transfer mixture to a medium bowl and fold in tomato and cilantro. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Serve guacamole dip with chips.

title: baked beans
directions: Partly cook the bacon with onion and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and put in a greased casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add pimento cheese spread (dissolve cheese).
Add Cool Whip.
Add crushed pineapple with juice.
Use a wire whip and refrigerate until cool.

title: creamy cucumber salad
directions: Peel and mince garlic.
Mix with sour cream, salt and pepper in medium bowl.
Peel the skin from the cucumbers and slice very thin.
Add to sour cream mixture.
Refrigerate for 6 hours or until cucumbers get soft.
Serve well chilled.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush crackers; add finely chopped fruit and nuts, then coconut.
Melt marshmallows in milk over low heat.
Add to cracker mixture.
Mix well and pack in sprayed loaf pans or roll into 6 x 1 1/2-inch size rolls and wrap in Saran Wrap.
Keep in refrigerator or freeze until ready to serve, slice thin.

title: peanut butter roll candy
directions: Mix
3/4 box of confectioners sugar, margarine, vanilla and milk
until
very
stiff
and
firm.
Add remaining sugar. Roll as for pie.
Spread with desired amount of peanut butter. Shape in large roll. Cut roll in half and wrap in waxed paper. Place in freezer or refrigerator.
Slice when firm.

title: quick cheese cake
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Use honey according to taste (1/2 cup makes it very sweet).
Blend less than a minute, or until smooth and creamy.
Pour into crust and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pappy's southern rolls
directions: In a small bowl, dissolve yeast in water for 10 minutes.
Drop eggs into mixing bowl; add melted shortening, milk, dissolved yeast, sugar and salt.
Beat well and begin working in the flour. Knead continuously in the bowl until it is smooth and elastic. Cover and let rest in a warm place for 45 minutes or until double in bulk.
Punch down dough.
Cut off small pieces about the size of a walnut.
Place in greased muffin pan.
Let rise in a warm place until rolls are as high as the pan.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 8 to 12 minutes.
Hot from the oven, brush with margarine to give extra flavor.

title: walnut pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, flour, corn syrup, butter and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Arrange nuts on top. Bake in lower third of oven at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until center is set.
Cool completely.

title: twinkie delight
directions: Note:
Low-fat and fat-free Twinkies, Cool Whip and pudding can be used.
No one will ever know it.

title: lentil-ham salad
directions: Heat water and lentils to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover, simmer 3 minutes; remove from heat.
Let stand 1 to 2 hours.
Drain lentils; stir in ham, salad dressing, onions, olives, salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Line salad bowl with lettuce leaves.
Spoon salad into bowl and garnish with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: wild chicken salad
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well. Cover tightly and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: yum yum cookies
directions: Mix and bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat, then add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Mix well.
Drop cookies by teaspoon on wax paper.
Makes about 70 cookies.

title: lime salad
directions: Let Jell-O slightly gel and mix all ingredients.
Chill.

title: grandma's carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco oil, eggs and vanilla.
Beat about 5 minutes.
Sift dry ingredients together and gradually add to batter.
Then add shredded carrots, flaked coconut, crushed pineapple with syrup and chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let cool.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: hot cider punch
directions: Bring apple cider and next 6 ingredients to a boil in a Dutch oven; reduce heat, and simmer 1 hour.
Pour mixture through a wire-mesh strainer into a container; discard spices.
Add lemon slices to punch just before serving.
Serve warm.

title: nutritional snack
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Do not cook.
Roll into several rolls. Chill and slice as needed.

title: pineapple chicken stir-fry
directions: Combine soy sauce, cornstarch and ginger.
Pour oil in wok and heat for 1 minute.
Add chicken.
Cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add vegetables and pineapple.
Cover and cook for 3 to 4 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add soy sauce mixture and cook until sauce is bubbly and thickens.
Serve over rice.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Put sugar, egg, vinegar, water, mustard and salt in saucepan. Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring often.
Let cool, then add the Miracle Whip. Fold the dressing into grated cabbage for cole slaw.

title: apple bar
directions: Add to margarine the sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Fold into sugar mixture.
Dice the apples (peeled) into dough.
Add chopped nuts, if desired.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix well and pour into sheet cake pan that has been well oiled; batter will be thick.
Bake at 350° until inserted with toothpick and comes out clean.
