Cool before cutting into squares.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Put chicken in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix soups, broth and vegetables along with a dash of salt and pepper and pour over chicken.
Mix Bisquick and milk.
Pour over all.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes, until crust is golden brown.

title: classic spinach salad
directions: In large salad bowl, combine spinach, mushrooms, tomato, croutons, red onion and bacon.
Add dressing and toss gently. Garnish with egg.
Makes about 6 side dish servings.

title: maryann's banana cake
directions: In medium size bowl mix flour and baking soda.
In another bowl beat butter and sugar together until creamy.
Beat in eggs and mix well.
In a small bowl or glass combine milk and vinegar. Beat into the egg and sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Add bananas and mix well.
On low speed add dry ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13 inch pan at 350° for 1/2 hour or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chocolate velvet cake
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave in bowl about 1 1/2 minutes. Stir until smooth.
Beat butter and sugar at medium speed until well blended-about 5 minutes.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating just until blended after each addition.
Add melted chocolate, beating until blended.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Sift 3 times.
Gradually add 1 cup hot water in a slow stream.
Beat just until blended, stir in vanilla.
Spoon into 3 greased and floured 8 inch round cake pans.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes-remove from pans and let cool on wire rack.

title: italian love cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Pour cake batter into pan.
Mix Ricotta, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Spread evenly over cake batter in pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool in pan.
Mix pudding mix with milk.
Blend in thawed Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled cake.
Refrigerate.
This is a very nice cake for a large group.

title: fruit iced tea
directions: Brew tea bags in 2 cups water.
Add remaining ingredients to brewed tea and enough water to make 1 gallon.

title: crab imperial
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon margarine or butter.
Mix in flour.
Slowly add milk. Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and thickens. Add onions, Worcestershire sauce and bread cubes; let cool.
In a separate pan, heat the remaining 2 tablespoons of butter and crabmeat. Gently fold crabmeat into the sauce mixture. Spoon mixture into shells.
Make topping by stirring together mayonnaise, lemon juice, egg, salt and pepper. Spoon over filled shells.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 450° for about 10 minutes or until lightly brown on top.

title: make-ahead baked egg casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch glass casserole dish.
Crumble French bread in dish.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over bread.
Beat eggs and combine with milk, salt, dry mustard and any or all of other desired ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Refrigerate up to 24 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter; gradually add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs and banana.
In a separate dish, combine milk and lemon juice.
Slowly fold 1/4 flour, then 1/3 milk mixture to batter.
Repeat until flour and milk are mixed well into the batter.
Pour into bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fudge walnut brownie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9-inch pie plate.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Stir in sugar, butter and vanilla.
Stir together flour, cocoa and salt; stir in butter mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour into prepared pie plate.
Bake 30 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Garnish with whipped cream or serve with ice cream, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: risen doughnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast; add 1 tablespoon sugar in warm milk.
Add 1 1/4 cups flour; beat thoroughly.
Let rise for 40 to 50 minutes. Add 3/4 cup sugar, butter, salt and about 4 cups of flour.
Let rise a second time (40 to 50 minutes).
Roll out dough and cut. Let rise, then fry in hot grease.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Break cake into pieces in a large dish.
Dissolve jello in boiling water and add strawberries.
Pour over cake and let set. Make sure jello and strawberries are mixed with cake.
Mix pudding mix as directed on box.
Spread over strawberry mixture. Spread Cool Whip over pudding mix after pudding has set. Refrigerate.

title: caramelized onion and cheese bites
directions: In a large skillet, cook the onion in hot oil about 3 minutes or just until tender.
Add the walnuts and the sugar.
Continue to cook and stir about 5 minutes more or until the onion is slightly caramelized and walnuts are lightly toasted.
Stir in the mustard.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Spray 2-quart casserole lightly with nonstick vegetable cooking spray.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: rainbow pudding
directions: Mix strawberry jello with boiling water.
Add fruit cocktail with the juice.
Stir and refrigerate to let it set up.
Mix vanilla pudding with cold milk; spread over jello.
Drain pineapple; mix the juice with pistachio pudding mix.
Spread over vanilla pudding.
Spread crushed pineapple over the green mixture. Top with Cool Whip.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Make small rounds spooning out on skillet.
Cook until brown.

title: fried squid rings(portuguese)
directions: Heat oil in a deep pan to 375°.
Combine beer, flour, salt and paprika.
Dip squid rings into batter and let excess batter run off.
Drop into hot fat.
Turn to brown on both sides and remove as soon as brown (30 seconds to 1 minute).

title: white fish fillet
directions: Defrost bread dough.
Melt butter.
Add onions and garlic. Saute until transparent over medium heat.
Add ham; saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Take off stove; cool 5 minutes.
Add Parmesan, seasonings and olives.
Mix.
Let chill until ready to use.
Can be prepared 24 hours in advance.
Roll dough out on floured board to 1/8-inch, approximately 16 x 12-inch.
Place filling on dough. Spread evenly.
Roll jelly roll style.
Pinch and seal ends with olive oil.
Rub oil over top and sides of loaf.
Salt lightly. Sprinkle with reserved Parmesan and Italian seasoning.
Place in greased large baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until sounds hollow and top is brown.
Let sit 10 to 15 minutes; slice.

title: marinade
directions: Use with blade roast, sirloin or London broil.
Marinate overnight.
Makes approximately 3 cups marinade.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: manicotti
directions: Cook shells according to package instructions, rinse and drain.
Saute ground beef, garlic and onion until done and drain. Add cottage cheese, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, salt, pepper and 3/4 cup Ragu sauce.
Stuff shells with meat mixture, place in lightly greased baking dish.
Pour sauce over shells and cover with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Cover dish and bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then uncover and bake for an additional 10 or 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture with buttermilk.
Add flavoring and beat at medium speed for at least 8 to 10 minutes.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Pour in batter and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Allow to cool in pan for 10 minutes before turning out.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, cloves and cinnamon. Combine the pumpkin and oil.
Combine all ingredients and pour into 3 large loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until top springs back when touched.

title: sausage cheese ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot!

title: onion burger
directions: Makes 8 patties. Grill or broil.

title: boiled dinner
directions: Combine all ingredients into a large pan; cover and let boil until all ingredients are tender (3 hours or maybe 4).

title: cherry-poppy seed twinks
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
In a large bowl, beat powdered sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and egg; blend well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Stir in flour, poppy seed and salt; mix well.

title: fresh fruit cobbler
directions: Slice fresh fruit in bottom of pan, just enough to cover the bottom.
Cut crusts from bread and place on top of fruit. Mix together flour, sugar, butter and egg.
Pour over top of bread. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: kimpira-gobo(sauteed burdock flavored with soy sauce; very good)
directions: Wash burdock root and scrape off the thin, brown skin with back of knife.
Cut into 2-inch matchsticks.
Soak in water immediately to prevent change of color.
Pare carrots and cut into strips of the same length and thickness as the burdock.
Roast sesame seed in a dry skillet over low heat, stirring constantly to prevent burning.
When seed begins to pop, transfer to dry bowl.
Soak dried red pepper in water to soften.
Cut in half and squeeze out seed under water; chop finely.
Drain burdock and pat dry with paper towel.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon and melted butter or oleo and sprinkle on bottom of baking pans.
Arrange sliced apples on top of sugar mixture.

title: overnight meringues(cookies)
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff.
By hand fold in flavorings, then nuts.
Place plain white or brown paper on baking sheet and drop meringues by teaspoons.
(It's not necessary too allow room for spreading.) Place pan in a preheated 350° oven and immediately turn oven off. Remain in oven overnight.
Do not open oven door.
Yield: 36 meringues.

title: baked corn
directions: In mixing bowl, combine all ingredients listed.
Grease baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn oven up to 400° and brown.
Should be golden brown when done.
Ovens may vary, so check often.

title: u.m.w.'s date pudding for "40"
directions: Pour boiling water over dates; let stand until cool. Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and blend.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon, vanilla and salt.
Add apples and nuts.
Add dates from which liquid has been drained.
Pour into 4 greased 7 x 11-inch pans (waxed paper in bottom) or use 35 to 36 pans for larger recipe.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cut servings approximately 2 x 5 inches.
Serve with Brown Sugar Sauce.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash and drain spinach leaves.
Tear into bite size pieces. Chop the eggs and slice the onions; toss these and the mushrooms with the spinach.
Pour on your favorite Italian dressing.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Brown pepper and onion in tablespoon of oil; set aside. Prepare cabbage leaves; cut out core and place in a large pot of water to cover cabbage. Simmer until leaves fall away; cool.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients; shape dough into mounds.
Bake about 25 minutes at 325°.
Roll in powdered sugar while still hot.

title: hot sweet pickles
directions: Drain dill pickles.
Remove about half of the pickles from the jar and place in a large bowl.
Pour the sugar and jalapeno peppers, including the juice over the pickles in the jar.
Stir with a wooden spoon until the sugar dissolves.
Add remaining pickles to the jar, a few at a time, stirring after each addition. Let set for 4 or 5 days, stirring them each day; they do not need to be refrigerated during this time.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine until fluffy with mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, along with flour.
Add flavoring.
Pour into a floured and greased tube cake pan.
Cook 1 1/2 hours at 300° or 310°.

title: cheese broccoli
directions: In boiling, salted water, cook broccoli; drain.
In a saucepan over low heat, combine mayonnaise, cheese and milk.
Heat, stirring frequently, until cheese melts.
Serve over cooked broccoli.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fresh tomato soup
directions: Saute celery, onion, carrot and green pepper in margarine or olive oil in large heavy pan.
Add 4 cups broth, tomatoes, salt, pepper and sugar.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Blend flour with remaining 1/2 cup broth. Stir gradually into soup; cook until slightly thickened, stirring frequently. Serve hot.

title: peaches and cream cake(serves about 16 people)
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put into large mixing bowl the first 7 ingredients and beat until well blended.
Spread in bottom of greased pan.

title: cheesecake
directions: Press into 10-inch spring-form pan.

title: soft oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, oil, milk, sugar and oats; mix well. Add raisins and nuts if desired. Place by tablespoon about 1/2 inch apart on cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Don't overbake.
Makes 50 cookies.

title: delicious dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.
Delicious with veggies and/or potato chips!

title: snappy green beans("pickled green beans")
directions: Pack beans into hot, sterilized jars.
Place 1/2 teaspoon mustard seed, 1/2 teaspoon dill seed, 1/8 teaspoon crushed red pepper and 1/8 teaspoon minced garlic into each jar.
Add beans.

title: communion bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, combine the flour, sugar and salt.
Add the butter and cut it in with a pastry blender or pulse 3 or 4 times in a food processor until it resembles fine crumbs.
Add the milk and combine until a stiff dough forms.

title: charcoal broiled chicken breasts
directions: Mix ingredients all together.
Add chicken and marinate 3 hours or longer.
Broil over charcoal for 10 minutes or until tender and juicy, basting with marinade.
Don't overcook.

title: leigh's dandy dirt cake
directions: Crush the cookies in large plastic bag using rolling pin. Cream the butter, sugar and cream cheese.
In another bowl mix the milk, pudding and Cool Whip.
Combine the two mixtures.
Alternate layers of this mixture and the cookie crumbs in a plastic flowerpot, starting and ending with the cookie crumbs.
Chill for several hours prior to serving.
Can decorate with silk flowers and gummy worms.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into about 8 pieces each.
Place in saucepan and cover with water.
Salt may be added before or after cooking.
Bring to boil and turn down heat to low.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Drain broth from potatoes and put potatoes into mixer bowl.
Beat on low speed until potato chunks are broken up.
Add margarine and beat on medium speed until potatoes are smooth.
Add milk and beat on medium speed until milk is blended with potatoes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on box.
Drain in cold water.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well. Chill before serving.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place thawed potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine next 7 ingredients; pour over potatoes.
Top with crushed crackers and drizzle with 1/4 cup melted butter. Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: chicken tortilla
directions: Boil, cool and debone chicken.
Shred chicken into pieces (put in mixing bowl).
Mix sour cream and 1/2 grated Monterey Jack with chicken and salt and pepper to taste.
In another bowl, mix cream of chicken soup and enchilada sauce.
Put chicken mixture in floured shells (roll like burritos).
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour cream of chicken and enchilada sauce over shells.
Sprinkle the other half of cheese on top.
Bake until sides bubble in a preheated oven at 375°.

title: quick and easy fruit cocktail and marshmallows
directions: Mix marshmallows and fruit cocktail.
Let stand for one hour. Heat sugar, milk and tapioca.
Let cool.
Combine the two mixtures and add Cool Whip.

title: tomato soup cake(double recipe)
directions: Combine soup, 1/4 can water and baking soda.
Soak raisins in hot water.
Mix everything, except flour and tomato soup mixture. Add tomato soup mixture and mix.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: The secret to good ribs is long, slow cooking.
Grill ribs with coals as low as possible, gray.
While ribs cook, mix remaining ingredients for basting sauce.
Do not baste ribs until completely cooked and fat has cooked away, then ribs will act as a sponge.
Total Cooking Time: 4 to 6 hours!

title: hot buttered rum
directions: In a pan over low heat, melt butter.
Add sugar and mix with mixer or whisk until butter is totally mixed with sugar.
Add spices slowly and continue to mix.
When totally mixed, add rum and mix until smooth.
Place in Tupperware and let cool.
Will keep in Tupperware and refrigerator for 1 year.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Stir all together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except berries.
Drain berries and fold into cake mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes.
You can add juice to frosting or top with whipped cream.

title: vinaigrette dressing
directions: Mash egg yolks to a paste with malt vinegar or cider vinegar. Gradually blend in salad oil.
Stir in green onions; add salt and coarsely ground pepper to taste; mix well.
Makes about 3/4 cup.

title: chicken divan
directions: Flour chicken and saute until brown.
Cook broccoli until unfrozen and separable.
Drain and set aside.
Melt margarine; add flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Add broth and cook until thick.
Stir in cream and wine.
Place broccoli in shallow baking dish.
Pour half of sauce over this.
Next, put chicken in. To remaining sauce, add Parmesan cheese.
Pour remaining sauce over chicken and sprinkle with more cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly browned on top.
Very good!

title: oh henry bars
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Spread in a lightly oiled 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° (will not look done, but do not cook longer).
Cool.

title: artichoke bake
directions: Saute onion and garlic in liquid from artichokes.
Mix all together and bake in a well-greased 9 x 12 pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Best if made a day in advance and let absorb flavors before serving.
Serve cold or hot.

title: ham sandwich
directions: Take one piece of bread.
Roll it flat with a glass.
Put ham on it, mustard next, then mayonnaise.
Roll it up.
Get some chips to go with it.

title: saucy oriental cabbage balls
directions: Mix ground beef, cabbage, egg, garlic, onion, milk, bread crumbs and 1 tablespoon soy sauce. Shape in 1 1/2-inch balls. Place balls on baking sheet and bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Place 2 tablespoons meatball drippings (discard the rest) into a pan. Add carrots and cook until soft.
Add remaining 1 tablespoon soy sauce, ginger, sherry (optional), broth, sugar and cornstarch mixture; bring to a boil.
Add meatballs and cook, stirring, until meatballs are hot throughout.
Serve over rice, if desired.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: In a bowl, cream the sugar and eggs. Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Remove from bowl and shape like a jelly roll. Refrigerate overnight.
Cut thin and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Nuts may be added.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain and put back into the pot. Add slices of Velveeta to broccoli.
After cheese melts, stir in cream of mushroom soup.
Mix well and place in a baking dish sprayed with a nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: stewed okra and tomatoes
directions: Melt fat in skillet. Brown onion and okra, slightly as it cooks.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper, slowly until vegetables are tender and mixture is thick (about 30 minutes).

title: tuna salad
directions: Drain tuna, mix with lemon juice.
Add remaining ingredients, except mayonnaise and toss lightly.
Add mayonnaise.
Chill a few minutes, if desired.
Serve on slices of tomato or lettuce leaves.

title: grandma nora erler's oatmeal refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar.
Blend well.
Blend in eggs and dry ingredients.
Shape into long roll 1 1/2-inch diameter in waxed paper.
Chill.
Slice thin.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes in orange cups
directions: Mash sweet potatoes.
Add seasonings, butter, vanilla and milk.
Potatoes should be light and fluffy.
Pile the mixture into orange halves.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
About 1/2 an hour before serving time, remove cover, make an indentation in top of each potato and put in a marshmallow.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: turkey-how to roast
directions: Add hot water
to
moisten
crumbs.
Place inside cavity and sew shut with string before roasting.

title: fried pie pastry
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add melted shortening. Stir until blended.
Combine milk and eggs, stirring well.
Pour milk mixture into flour mixture.
Stir just until blended, adding more milk if necessary.
Enough pastry for 22 pies.
You may add any kind of fruit or meat filling and deep fry.

title: lime party salad
directions: Combine milk and marshmallows and melt in pan.
Stir in jello powder.
Remove from heat.

title: chocolate freeze
directions: Dump ingredients into ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: baked tomatoes, stuffed with sausage and rice
directions: Cut a slice from the stem end of each tomato.
Using your fingers, fish out the seeds from the tomato's cavity and discard. With a sharp knife, hollow out the tomatoes, leaving the walls intact and reserving the extra pulp.
Invert the tomato shells on a baking rack for 10 to 15 minutes while making filling.

title: oatmeal jelly bars
directions: Mix well with fingertips-oats, flour, sugar, salt and margarine.
Pat 1/2 of mixture into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Spread jelly evenly over dough.
Sprinkle remaining mixture over jelly.
Lightly flatten with fingertips.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool in pan and cut into 24 bars.

title: chicken and pasta salad
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut each potato in half.
Toss potatoes with 1 tablespoon oil and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Roast 25 minutes or until golden and tender, turning with pancake turner.

title: brown derby chicken salad
directions: Toss first 7 ingredients with yogurt and dressing.
Chill.

title: zucchini "apple" pie bars
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and oleo like pie dough (reserve 2 1/2 cups).
Pat into 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Peel and slice zucchini; cook together with lemon juice until yellow.
Add sugar, nutmeg, 1 cup crust mix and cinnamon; mix and let stand 5 minutes.
Pour over cooled crust. Add nuts to rest of crust; sprinkle over zucchini.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
"Can't believe it's not apple!"

title: beet gelatin salad
directions: Drain beets; save liquid.
Mash beets.
Heat water; dissolve jello in hot water.
Add mashed beets and drained juice from beets.
Chill until firm.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Blend the first 3 ingredients.
Add the sour milk or buttermilk, flour, soda, salt, vanilla and rhubarb.
Top with the sugar and cinnamon combined before baking. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in
a greased 9 x 3-inch pan. Bake longer if using frozen rhubarb.

title: tex mex roll arounds
directions: Combine cream cheese and picante sauce.
Spread on tortillas. Roll up and cut into bite size pieces.
Secure each piece with toothpick.
Refrigerate before serving.
Great for party snacks.

title: barbara's hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add sauce, soup, salt and pepper.
Stir in onions and celery. Mix potatoes into meat sauce.
Bake, tightly covered, for 2 hours at 350° or 5 hours in crock-pot on high or 8 to 9 hours in crock-pot on low setting.

title: strawberry almond shortcake torte
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup margarine at medium speed until well mixed, about 1 to 2 minutes.
Add 1 egg and 1 teaspoon almond extract.
Continue beating, scraping bowl often, until creamy, 1 to 2 minutes.

title: easy salad
directions: Mix fruit cocktail and frozen strawberries in a bowl.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Slice banana into fruit mixture.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: apple cider(hot)
directions: Put in basket of coffeepot and perk.
Serve in coffee mugs with cinnamon stick.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Tear into small pieces the lettuce.
Add cut up cauliflower on top, then add jar of bacon bits.
Sprinkle the diced onion over bacon bits.
Combine mayonnaise and sugar.
Stir until smooth. Pour over other ingredients.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top. Let set 1/2 day.
Mix before serving.

title: mexican salad
directions: Cut up lettuce, tomato, bell pepper and grate cheese.
Drain beans and crush Doritos.
Mix all together, except chips and dressing.
Add when ready to eat.

title: squash supreme
directions: Mash squash; add sour cream, soup, carrots, onion, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle a layer of crumbs in shallow casserole dish; spoon squash mixture over crumbs.
Cover with additional crumbs and dot generously with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Bake cake in oblong pan; cool and punch holes all over.
Heat Eagle Brand and milk until boiling; remove from stove and add flavoring.
Pour mixture over cake and chill in freezer until cold.
Cover with Cool Whip; sprinkle coconut over Cool Whip. Chill overnight before serving.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Blend cheese and margarine.
Combine with flour, cereal and red pepper.
Roll out and bake at 300° for 20 minutes on greased cookie sheet.
Dough may be pinched and rolled in small balls.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sunday chili(serve with cornbread)
directions: Soak beans overnight in cold water to cover.
Drain.
Place beans in slow cooker.
Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute until soft, 3 to 5 minutes.
Add green pepper, cabbage, potatoes, tomatoes with liquid, chili powder and cumin.
Continue cooking, stirring frequently, 3 minutes, then transfer to slow cooker.
Add rice and water.
Cover and cook on low until chili is thick and beans and rice are tender, 6 to 8 hours.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Top with shredded cheese, if desired.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in a greased loaf pan.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bread 'n' butter pickles
directions: Layer sliced cucumbers with salt and ice.
Stir.
Let soak 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
While soaking, prepare onions and peppers.
Mix sugar, vinegar and spices together in large heavy pan. Cook syrup to dissolve. Drain salt water off cucumbers. Add cucumbers, onions and peppers to syrup. Bring to a boil.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: honey-glazed pork roast(microwave)
directions: In 2 cup glass measure, combine honey, juice, cinnamon and cornstarch.
Cook in High for 1 minute or until glaze boils and thickens.
Set aside.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, salt and milk.
Bring to rapid boil. Reduce heat and cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, marshmallows and butter.
Blend well and add nuts.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: very cheesy macaroni
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook macaroni according to package directions until al dente, or still slightly firm.
Drain well. Fill another saucepan 3/4 full with water.
Bring water to a boil. Add broccoli, reduce heat to medium and cook until al dente. Drain and set aside.

title: wine jelly
directions: Mix wine and sugar in a saucepan.
Heat on low until sugar is completely dissolved, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and immediately stir in the Certo fruit pectin.
Pour into 4 small sterilized jelly jars.
Place lids loosely on top of jars.
When jelly is completely cooled, tighten the lids.
Store in a cool place.
This has been a Cherry Avenue favorite.

title: pumpkin pie spice cake
directions: Mix well and put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 1 cube butter and add to 1 yellow cake mix.
Crumble over pumpkin and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken cutlet melange
directions: Dredge cutlets in flour and brown in oil (use large skillet). Cover with sliced potatoes.
Cover potatoes with onion slices. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Add pepper to taste.
Mix bouillon cube with water.
Pour bouillon and wine over onions.
Cover and simmer about 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: pretzel salad
directions: The salad is layered in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip Cool Whip and pudding together.
Add brandy or schnapps, rum and food coloring.
Blend well.
Store in refrigerator overnight for best flavor.
Use for dip for any kind of fresh fruit.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Heat yams.
When warm, pour off liquid and mash.
Add melted margarine; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until top and edges brown, about 60 minutes.
(If only edges brown, place under broiler to brown top, about 3 to 4 minutes.)

title: fruit juice punch
directions: Combine al ingredients; mix well.
Pour over crushed ice and serve immediately.
Calories per serving:
about 50.

title: orange honey chicken
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Dip chicken in orange juice and coat with crumb mixture.
Put on lightly oiled foil-lined pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, dissolve bouillon in 1/2 cup boiling water and add last 2 ingredients and leftover orange juice, stirring until butter melts.
Pour over chicken and bake.
Baste frequently until done, approximately 30 to 45 minutes longer.

title: hawaiian dream cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed and bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: easy taco salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients.
Cook the chile and pour over salad.
Top with grated cheese.

title: chocolate ball candy
directions: Melt butter; add vanilla and Eagle Brand milk.
Stir in powdered sugar, coconut and pecans.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Form in balls and chill.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite size pieces (this should take about 2 months).
Add gravy and cook about 4 weeks at 465°.
This will serve 3,800 people.
If more are expected, 2 rabbits may be added, but do this only if necessary, as most people do not like finding hare in their stew!

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix milk, lemon juice and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Pour into pie crust.
Let set several hours before serving. Best if made night before.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Combine hamburger meat, bell pepper and onion.
Brown and drain off excess fat.
Mix with remaining in large casserole dish. Then top with cheese.
Cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken-cheese chimichangas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion and garlic powder in oil in skillet until tender.
Add chicken. Cook over low heat until heated through.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 cup cheese. Separate roll dough into rectangles; press perforations to seal. Spread 1/2 cup salsa to within 1/2 inch of edges.
Spoon 1/3 cup chicken mixture onto half of each rectangle.
Roll up and pinch sides.
Bake 16 to 21 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 cup of cheese on top. Melt it.
Serve with remaining items.

title: frozen punch
directions: Mix ingredients together; freeze for at least 24 to 48 hours. Remove from freezer 2 to 3 hours before serving and crush mixture. Serve as a slush.

title: low-fat festive rice
directions: In medium nonstick saucepan, bring broth to a boil.
Add rice.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in 4 tablespoons butter sprinkles, parsley and vegetables.
Cover. Continue cooking 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes or until broth is absorbed.
Sprinkle with remaining butter sprinkles.
Fluff with fork and serve.

title: breakfast quick quiche
directions: Trim bread crusts, butter one side each slice.
Place bread, buttered side down in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown sausage and crumble into small bits, drain on paper towels.
Stir in mustard and sprinkle over bread.
Beat eggs, add milk and Worcestershire sauce together.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over bread-sausage, and pour egg-milk mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: onion casserole
directions: Cook onions in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Layer half of onions in buttered dish (I use an 8 x 10-inch casserole), followed by half of soup and almonds.
Repeat.
Mix melted butter and corn flakes.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: spiced cranberry jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except orange and walnuts.
Refrigerate for 1 1/2 hours.
Mix in orange sections and walnuts.
Pour into a 5-cup mold.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: crustless pizza
directions: Brown ground beef. Drain meat and mix with spaghetti sauce. In separate pan, cook chopped onions and mushrooms in butter until onions are clear. Then add to the meat mixture. Layer meat mixture and cheese, ending with ground beef. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: monkey bread
directions: Break off balls of dough.
Roll in margarine, then sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place in greased tube pan.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Invert pan to cool.

title: starving artist chicken salad
directions: Mix lemon juice with mayonnaise.
Add soy sauce and curry. Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss gently and chill.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix batter by directions on box.
Take out 1 cup of batter and put the rest evenly in 3 cake pans.
Bake until done.

title: jack cheese balls
directions: Melt cheese in a double boiler.
Crumble sausage into cheese, stirring constantly.
Add Bisquick mix and cayenne pepper.
Roll into small balls.
Freeze on cookie sheet for best results and cook as needed (if cooked right away, they will flatten some). Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes, depending on whether or not frozen.

title: polish potato pie
directions: Skin kielbasa and cut in 1/2-inch pieces.
Cook potatoes 15 minutes, drain, peel and slice.
Combine onion, garlic, flour, salt, chives, parsley, pepper and mace in a small bowl.
Line 10-inch pie plate with crust.
Arrange layers of potatoes, then spices and then meat.
Dot with butter and 1/3 of cream.
Repeat: potatoes, spices and meat.
Cover with top crust.
Make a hole in center of top crust.
Mix egg and remaining 1/3 cup cream and hold. Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Pour egg and cream mixture through top vent.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: old fashion lemon pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour and salt.
Then add juice and melted butter; pour into an unbaked crust.
Bake at 350° until top is brown.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream the eggs together with the soft butter and 1 cup sugar. Add the flour, lemon rind, lemon juice and milk.
Beat the egg whites together until stiff; fold in last.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°, then for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: orange sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water.
Place potatoes in baking dish that has been greased with butter or margarine.
Mix remaining ingredients and cook until it begins to thicken; pour over potatoes.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix meal, flour, egg, buttermilk and water.
Have skillet hot with 1 teaspoon shortening added.
Pour bread mixture in skillet and bake for about 10 minutes on bottom rack and about 10 minutes on top rack at 450°, then broil to brown top.

title: skillet scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice thinly.
Heat shortening in large skillet.
Add potatoes, onions and seasonings.
Fry potatoes slowly over low heat until golden brown, turning frequently.
Pour on cream; add cheese, stirring gently to mix.
Cover and cook slowly 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mac and beef
directions: In 4-quart Dutch oven over medium heat, cook beef, onions and cumin until beef is browned, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Add soup; stir until smooth.
Stir in broth, water, tomatoes and chilies.
Heat to boiling.
Add macaroni.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook 12 minutes or until macaroni is tender, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 cups or 4 servings.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Boil peppers for 5 minutes.
Cook ground meat, onion, salt and pepper until almost done, then add Minute rice and finish cooking. Stuff peppers with meat mixture, pour Creole Sauce over and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until tests done.

title: nancy's fudge cookies
directions: Melt chips and	butter in double boiler (or microwave). When completely melted,	remove	from heat and add Eagle Brand milk; mix well.
Add
flour;
mix well.
Add nuts and vanilla; stir well.
Drop
by
teaspoon
onto
ungreased	cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: heloise's fat-free cream soup
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in an airtight container.
To make soup base, add 2 cups cold water to the mix in a large saucepan and stir constantly over medium heat until thick.
You can use this base to make any flavor "cream" soup.
Just add your main ingredient to the mix, mushrooms, for example, and cook for a few minutes longer.
If soup is too thick, add more water and stir thoroughly, still over medium heat.

title: deluxe strawberry french toast
directions: Drain strawberries, reserving liquid.
Add water to reserved liquid to measure 1 cup.
Combine sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Gradually add liquid.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture is clear and thickened.
Stir in strawberries and almonds.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk, salt, chicken, vegetables, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can of onion rings.
Spread into greased 8 x 12-inch dish. Bake uncovered at 425° for 30 minutes.
Add remaining cheese and onions and bake 5 minutes.

title: aunt clara's chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour.
Pour 1/2 cup boiling water over this.
Add butter and egg yolks mixed with milk and vanilla.
Cook until thick.
Pour into 9 inch baked crust.
Cover with meringue and bake until browned.

title: spiced tea(yields 20 servings)
directions: Pour quart of boiling water over tea and spice.
Let stand until nearly cold; add juice of 3 lemons and 3 oranges or 1/2 cup frozen lemon juice and 1 can frozen orange juice.
Add sugar and 12 cups water.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Mix cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar.
Combine both mixtures and add Cool Whip, folding in.
Break up cookies.
Place in layers, starting with cookies. Crush more cookies on top to look like dirt.

title: never-fail fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until smooth. Remove from heat.
Add nuts.
Drop onto waxed paper.

title: hamburger goulash
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain fat.
Add tomato sauce, oregano, mushrooms and a little sugar; simmer about 5 minutes. Stir in cooked egg noodles.
Put cheese on top.
Stir into dish when it melts.

title: light vegetable tuna pie
directions: In mixing bowl, combine egg, mayonnaise, seasoning, onion and green pepper.
Stir in bread crumbs; mix in tuna.
Press gently into 8-inch pie plate with fork.
Toss vegetables with 1/4 cup cheese into shell.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup cheese over vegetables.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: farm style potato swirl
directions: Cut potatoes into cubes.
Place in a large saucepan.
Cover with water and add a dash of salt.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for about 20 minutes, until potatoes are just tender. Drain.
Mash potatoes.
Add green onions and garlic mix to blend. Add butter, hot milk, egg, yolk, pepper and nutmeg.
Whip until light and fluffy.
Add parsley.
Add Mozzarella cheese, sausage slices and Parmesan cheese.
Spoon mixture into a buttered ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Arrange some sausage slices on top.
Heat under the broiler until light browned and hot, 5 to 7 minutes.
Serve with a green salad or marinated tomatoes.

title: barbecued meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Form 3 loaves in 13 x 9 cake pan. Pour barbecue sauce over the loaves. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix together and bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fudge scotch ring
directions: Melt chips and milk together in microwave.
Add vanilla. Stir.
Let cool before adding nuts.
Pour into long buttered pan; let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Brown onion in butter.
In a large bowl, combine soups, broth and chilies.
Add diced chicken and mix.
Layer chicken mixture, cheese and tortillas in rectangular casserole dish until all ingredients have been used.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Drain juice from fruits and mix.
Colored marshmallows may be used.
Chill.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Saute onion in 1 tablespoon butter or shortening.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into baking dish and bake until set, about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on package.
Drain.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Mix cheese, onion and mayonnaise with hot vegetables.
Crush Ritz crackers, melt margarine, mix with crackers until they are damp.
Sprinkle over top of vegetable mix.
Bake at 325°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Combine raisins and nuts and toss with 2 tablespoons of flour mixture.
Beat together shortening and spices.
Gradually add sugar and beat until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour mixture and applesauce, beating only until smooth.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Grease Bundt or 3-quart ring mold.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove cake from pan and place on rack until cold.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Dust with confectioners sugar or use cream cheese frosting, if desired.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, carrots and celery in water until tender. Drain, reserving liquid and setting vegetables aside.
Saute onion in butter until soft.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly until thickened.
Gently stir in cooked vegetables.
Add 1 cup or more of reserved cooking liquid until soup is desired consistency.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add other ingredients and eggs, one at a time.
Cook 1 hour and 25 minutes at 300°.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Cut butter into dry cake mix until crumbly.
Pat into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan, building up sides.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
While hot, put apples on top and sprinkle on sugar and cinnamon.
Blend sour cream and egg.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients into double crust.
Bake in 9-inch pie pan at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: zucchini squash bake
directions: Cook all ingredients together for 5 minutes.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and Italian spices.
Put in casserole dish. Add 1 can garlic croutons.
A small can of V-8 juice may be added.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Cut up chicken breast into 1-inch pieces.
Dip in egg batter and roll in flour lightly.
Brown in oil.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cheese.
Pour half the mixture into well-greased pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Add other half of mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together ingredients and beat well.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cook 2 hours, covered, at 350°.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef over medium heat.
Drain fat.
Add beans, onion and soup.
Stir well and heat 10 minutes.
Place mixture in casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook onion and squash together and drain.
Line pan with half of stuffing.
Mix other ingredients with squash and onions.
Pour over stuffing and cover with the rest of stuffing.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream, sauce and dry taco mix together.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Spread sour cream mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Garnish with lettuce, olives and tomatoes.
Top off with cheese. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Combine chopped apples and candy bars in medium bowl.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate, covered, until ready to serve.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, bring 1/2 cup water to boiling.
Add broccoli and onion.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until tender. Do not drain.
Stir in soup, milk, cheese and pepper.
Cook and stir until heated through.
Top each serving with chopped peanuts and shredded cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip-peanut butter cup cookies
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, cocoa and baking soda; set aside.
In large bowl with electric mixer, beat butter, peanut butter, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla about 3 minutes until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Reduce mixer speed to low.
Gradually beat in flour mixture until smooth.
Stir in peanut butter cup pieces along with chocolate chips.
Drop dough by heaping tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet, 1-inch apart.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes until dry and slightly firm to touch.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet, then remove to wire rack to cool completely.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Stir in zucchini and flour alternately, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Add nuts and raisins. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: no-bake fudge oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk and butter for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Quickly drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Use 2 spoons.
Let cool.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook onion and celery in oleo until tender.
Add mayonnaise, then mix in a large bowl with cornbread stuffing and seasoning mix.
Add chicken broth, salt, eggs, milk and deboned chicken, then pour in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
Add cream of mushroom soup on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add cheese on top and bake 10 minutes more.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, salt, and milk in a saucepan. Boil, cook to soft ball shape. Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla. Beat until mixture thickens. Add nuts. Pour into greased plate.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add flour, sugar and brown sugar; beat until well blended.
Blend in melted butter; stir in chocolate pieces and walnuts.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: whole wheat biscuits
directions: Stir
whole
wheat
flour,
unbleached	flour, salt and baking powder together.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender. Add
milk all
at
once
and stir vigorously until dough just stiffens
up, then
turn	out
on a lightly floured board and knead
times. Roll or pat out to thickness of 1/2-inch and cut
out
with
a biscuit
cutter.
Place on a greased baking sheet.	Bake
in
450° oven
about 12 minutes.
Serve hot for best taste.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugars, vanilla and butter.
Add eggs and beat well and then add peanut butter.
Sift flour, soda and salt together and mix with rest of ingredients.
Add milk.
Roll in ball like a marble and cross with fork.
Bake in 375° oven for about 10 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend.
Spoon batter into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until done.
Cool completely before slicing.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sloppy joes(for a crowd)
directions: Brown hamburger with onions and peppers.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for approximately 15 minutes.
This should serve about 60 people.

title: g.g.'s cold cucumber soup
directions: Put cukes and onion in blender.
Add enough milk to puree. Blend in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Can be made a day ahead. Garnish with slice of cuke and dill.

title: fruit cake squares
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add pecans. Press down lightly.
Bake for 1/2 hour, or until done.
Let cool; cut into squares.

title: chicken mole
directions: Cook the chickens in just enough water to cover them.
Saute the sesame seed in a little oil, with tortilla.
Boil some water; turn heat off and soak red peppers for 15 minutes.
When peppers are soft, drain them.
In a blender, put the peppers, the pumpkin and sesame seed, black pepper, garlic cloves and the toasted tortilla.
Heat 1 tablespoon corn oil in a pot and transfer the mixture from the blender.
Add chicken to the sauce mixture (optional).
Add 1 cup of the chicken liquid.
Cover and simmer until chicken is tender.

title: marinated salad
directions: Bring sugar and vinegar to boil; cool.
Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: concord grape pie
directions: Slip skins from grapes and set aside. Heat grapes in saucepan for 3 to 4 minutes. Then run through a sieve to remove seeds. Combine pulp, skins, cornstarch, sugar and salt.

title: rice-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli separately.
Saute onions and celery in large skillet with oil.
Add all other ingredients (drain broccoli).
Pour into casserole and bake 30 minutes at
350°. Serves 12.

title: shrimp pizza
directions: Spread plain cream cheese on dish.
Spread chive cream cheese over.
Spread 1/2 bottle cocktail sauce over.
Spread shrimp on top.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Stick crackers around sides.
Serve with knife.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken (3 to 5 pounds wings) and bake at 350°.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown onion and hamburger.
Add mustard and catsup to taste. Mix in chicken gumbo soup.
Simmer.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Dump undrained pineapple in pan and top with blueberries.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit. Sprinkle with nuts; cut margarine into pieces and sprinkle evenly over all.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
May use cherry or apple pie filling.

title: coca-cola chicken
directions: Mix together barbecue sauce, Coca-Cola and Texas Pete.
Pour over skinned chicken; let marinate overnight.
Bake for 1 hour, covered, at 350°.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Cream all of the sugar, powdered sugar, butter, oil and eggs together in a mixer, then add the rest of the ingredients.
You can add chocolate chips or M&M's or anything you want to the mix or just have them plain.
Mixture will be light in color and will be soft.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 175 cookies.

title: kid's favorite fourth of july jello
directions: Add salt and cream of tartar to the egg whites and beat until stiff.
Slowly add the sugar, beating well as you go along. Mixture will be thick and glossy.
Add vanilla at the end of beating.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheets, 1 inch apart.
Put in oven and turn oven off immediately.
Leave in oven for 3 to 5 hours (or overnight).

title: zucchini-honey bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; stir in pecans.
Peel zucchini, if desired.
Shred enough for 2 cups.
Combine with remaining ingredients; add to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cook in pan 10 minutes. Remove from pans and let cool on wire racks.
Freezes well.

title: chicken pan pie
directions: Cook chicken; cut into bite size pieces.
Place in bottom of a casserole dish.
Mix soup, broth and butter in saucepan; bring to a boil, then pour over chicken.
Mix together flour, baking powder and milk, then pour over top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: boiled cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage and add sugar and salt in saucepan. Add 1 cup of water and seasoning.
Cook over medium heat until tender.

title: beef burgers provencale
directions: Mix ground beef, shredded zucchini and bread crumbs into 8 (1/2-inch) thick patties.
Brown on both sides in a large nonstick skillet for 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in sliced zucchini and tomatoes. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 7 to 9 minutes. Turn patties and stir 2 to 3 times or until zucchini is crisp-tender.
Add potatoes and simmer 3 minutes longer or until patties are no longer pink in center.
Makes 4 servings.

title: orange julius drink
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender, cover and blend until smooth, about 30 seconds.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: granola
directions: Plant lemon seeds.
They make attractive houseplants and the leaves can be used for delicate flavoring.

title: yams
directions: Steam yams for 20 minutes, peel and cut in 1/2-inch chunks. In a shallow dish sprayed with Pam and sprinkled with brown sugar, add all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tender.

title: walnut raisin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. In a large bowl, combine sugar and margarine.
Using wooden spoon, beat in eggs and vanilla. Sift flour with soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Stir into egg mixture, alternating with milk.
Stir in apples, chopped nuts and raisins.
Turn into prepared pan. Bake 40 to 45 minutes until surface springs back when gently pressed with fingertip.
Let cool in pan on wire rack. Frost, if desired. Cut into 20 squares. Top each with walnut. Makes 20 servings.

title: 7 steps to heaven
directions: Crush graham crackers with powdered sugar and melted butter. Press into bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Layer chocolate chips (whole package), coconut, nuts, butterscotch chips (1 package), dates and then pour condensed milk over whole pan.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: amaretto cake
directions: Spread almonds on baking sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 325°.
Remove and set aside.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan. Sprinkle 1/2 cup almonds in bottom of pan.
In mixing bowl combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, oil, Amaretto, orange juice and almond extract.
Beat until fluffy.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pan and bake 1 hour at 325° or until tested done.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine butter and milk in pan; heat until butter melts.
Stir in cocoa and vanilla.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed until smooth.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt Hershey bars, marshmallows and milk in top of double boiler.
Cool.
Add whipped cream.
Put into crust.
Place in refrigerator.
Serve with small scoop of whipped cream or ice cream on each piece.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Mix dressing, macaroni, vegetables and tuna.
Season to taste with salt and black pepper.
Refrigerate.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 6 servings.
Prep time:
15 minutes plus refrigerating.

title: pepper chicken and rice
directions: Saute green and red peppers, onion and garlic in oil for approximately 7 minutes or until tender.
Add chicken.
Saute for 5 minutes or until no longer pink.
Stir in tomato sauce and red pepper seasoning.
Cook, covered, for 5 minutes.
Stir in rice and serve. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: yummy yams
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until tender; peel and mash.
Combine other ingredients; top with marshmallows.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese, milk and vanilla in medium bowl on low speed until smooth. Gradually add in powdered sugar, 1 cup at a time, until smooth and of spreading consistency.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans. Beat on medium speed of electric mixer until smooth.
Chill 2 hours.
Shape into ball and roll in pecans.

title: biblical cake
directions: Follow Solomon's advice for making good boys and you will have a good cake.
(Proverbs 23:14, first clause).
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: bread loaves
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly mix flour, yeast, sugar and salt. Add water and margarine; stir until well blended, about 1 minute. Add 1 1/2 cups flour; stir vigorously for 2 minutes. Add additional

1 1/2 cups to 2 cups flour to make a soft dough. Turn dough out onto lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes. Spray dough with Pam; cover with bowl. Let rest 10 minutes. Punch down; divide into 2 pieces. Roll each piece to 11 x 7 rectangle. Roll up tightly from short end. Pinch seam to seal; place seam side down in loaf pan, sprayed with Pam. Cover; let rise in warm, draft-free place until doubled in size, 1 hour and 15 minutes. Bake
in 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool on wire rack.

title: date balls
directions: Put cereal, dates and nuts through
meat grinder; add honey, butter and lemon juice and mix well.
Shape into small balls and roll in confectioners sugar.
May be topped with pecan halves. Makes 30.

title: cheese spread
directions: Stir all ingredients together and use.

title: no-cooking banana split pie
directions: Mix together and press into the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish (glass will work best).
Chill 1 hour.

title: texas taco casserole
directions: Brown and drain beef and onions.
Add tomato sauce; simmer 5 minutes.
Place 6 cups of chips in a 4-quart casserole.
Sprinkle 2 cups cheese over top.
Pour on the meat sauce.
Top with remaining chips.
Place remaining 2 cups cheese over.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Take pineapple and bring to boil.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O.
Let set until cool enough to touch with your finger, then add buttermilk and put in refrigerator until it begins to jell. Stir in Cool Whip and place in large baking dish.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: In large, oiled, shallow pan, mix popcorn and nuts.
Mix other ingredients in saucepan, stirring, and bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Pour over corn mixture.
Stir well.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Stir while cooling.
Cover tightly to store.
Enjoy.

title: dried beef spread
directions: Combine all ingredients except almonds.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot on Triscuits.

title: impossible buttermilk pie
directions: Grease pie plate. Heat oven to 350°. Beat all ingredients until smooth (30 seconds in blender on high). Pour into plate. Bake until knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: timbales
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into buttered casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour and sugars.
Beat until well blended.
Blend in butter. Add chips and walnuts.
Bake 1 hour.

title: jambalaya salad
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Cook on the grill until just done.
Don't overcook or it will be dry.
Cook shrimp and sausage on grill.
Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
If shrimp are large, cut in half crosswise.
Slice sausage into 1/4-inch slices.
In a bowl, combine chicken, shrimp and sausage.
Add peppers, onion and rice and toss to combine.
In a bowl, combine tomato sauce, vinegar, olive oil, sugar, garlic, salt, cumin and Tabasco sauce.
Whisk to combine well.
Pour over chicken mixture and toss to combine well.
Serve at room temperature or chill. Serve on lettuce leaves and garnish with chopped parsley.
Yield: 12 cups.

title: scallops
directions: In a saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter or olive oil and add fresh dill, minced scallion, salt and hot pepper sauce.
When mixture begins to bubble, add bay scallops and cook until tender. Prior to serving, add dry white wine.
Blend well, then serve with rice or pasta.

title: bunny patch dessert
directions: Slice cake into 10 slices.
Line bottom of 12 x 8-inch baking dish with cake slices.
Top with pie filling and all of the whipped topping.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until ready to serve.
Tint coconut pale green with food coloring.
Sprinkle over center of whipped topping.
Decorate with jelly beans, Easter candies and decorations.

title: biryani rice
directions: Wash chicken; place in a pot with the mastica, water and salt. Cook for 40 minutes or until tender.
Remove the chicken pieces and set aside.
Beat the eggs and corn flour, then beat in yoghurt. Add the spices and 1/2 tablespoon salt to the yoghurt.
Set aside. Saute the onions in the oil until golden, then remove from the oil. Place the onions on the chicken then place the potatoes on top of the chicken.
Pour the yoghurt over the potatoes and set aside. Pour 8 cups of the chicken broth in a pot.
Wash the rice and add to the broth with the oil the onions were fried in.
Set aside until the rice absorbs all the liquid.

title: ragu hot dish
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cheese.
Place in casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes covered.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: moist cornbread muffins
directions: Beat sugar and eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and soda. Add yogurt and melted butter.
Stir until batter is evenly moistened.
Makes 12 muffins.
Bake at 400° until tops are light brown, 18 to 20 minutes.

title: dilly bread
directions: Mix dry ingreiments 'n add other...beat reel gud...kiver wid a warm damp cloth...let rise to double in a warm spot fur an hour...work down 'n put in well-greased pan...let rise agin fur 'bout 45 minutes...brush top wid melted buttah 'n salt 'n slide in a 350° oven fur 'bout 50 min...iffn loaf browns too fast, kiver with foil fur the last 20 minutes.
Take out 'n cool on rack

title: 1961 pepper relish
directions: Chop peppers, onions and cabbage.
Pour boiling water over them and let stand in water for 20 minutes.
Drain well.

title: 8-day cucumber pickle *
directions: First Day: Wash and cut up cucumbers.
Put in stone jar. Cover with cold water and let stand 24 hours.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in large buttered casserole. Sprinkle top with buttered Pepperidge Farm stuffing.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: tom's homemade biscuits
directions: In large bowl, put flour and shortening.
Blend until it seems it is only flour again.
Add buttermilk, stirring in, folding and mixing until it becomes a ball and does not stick to sides of bowl.
Put ball on floured surface; knead until it becomes soft and manageable.
Roll out to about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut out and place in greased pan.
Bake in a 425° oven until brown.
Yields 10 biscuits.

title: very easy dip
directions: Place cream cheese and the onions in a food processor and process thoroughly until it is a lovely pale green color.

title: snowballs
directions: Cut up dates; add oleo, egg and sugar.
Mix together in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, about 3 minutes.
Remove from stove; add nuts and Rice Krispies.
Mix in well.
Spread on cookie sheet, lightly greased, to cool enough for handling while still warm.
Take by spoonfuls and roll into balls, then in coconut.
Makes about 45.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Mix and place in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: civil war pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs.
Gradually stir in the flour and vanilla.
Mix real well.
Beat with spoon until smooth.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in a pan.
Bring to a rolling boil and boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Add oats, one cup at a time.
Mix together and drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Allow cookies to cool before moving.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add parsley flakes, basil, salt, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Stir.
Cook noodles until tender.
Drain.
Combine cottage cheese with eggs, parsley and Parmesan cheese.
Place layer of noodles, cheese mixture and meat in a baking dish.
Repeat layers.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: four bean salad
directions: Drain all cans of beans.
Rinse the red kidney beans.
Mix together in a large bowl with onion sliced and separated into rings.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add applesauce, then sifted dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth and fold in raisins and nuts.
Bake in waxed paper lined pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Alternate flour and milk to batter.
Add flavoring last.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bran candy
directions: Boil all ingredients except bran to soft ball stage.
Cool to room temperature.
Add bran.
If desired, 1/2 cup raisins, dates or nuts may be added.
Beat until stiff enough to knead.
Turn onto board dusted with powdered sugar.
Knead until smooth.
Shape into a roll and slice.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon and cloves; set aside. Cream shortening and sugar.
Add 1 egg; beat until light and fluffy.
Combine and add applesauce and baking soda.
Mix well. Add dry ingredients, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in walnuts and raisins; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 8 dozen cookies.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Spray 15 x 10-inch pan with Pam.
Mix cheese, crumbs and spices together in small bowl.
Dip chicken in butter; coat with cheese mixture.
Place in single layer in pan and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown meat; drain grease and add rest of ingredients.
Simmer for at least 1 hour.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix mayonnaise with water. Add to dry mixture; add vanilla and mix.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cucumber au gratin
directions: Cook cucumbers in just enough salted, boiling water to cover for 5 minutes; drain well.
Melt butter in saucepan; add flour, stirring until blended.
Add milk gradually; cook and stir until smooth.
Add bouillon cube.
Add onion; stir until dissolved. Season with salt and pepper.
Add cheese; simmer, stirring constantly until melted.
Add cucumbers; pour into greased small casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes until brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts.
Shape mixture into a ball. Roll ball in pecans.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: lemon torte
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix ingredients together; pat into bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until brown.

title: golden graham s'mores
directions: Grease rectangular pan.
Heat corn syrup, margarine and chocolate chips to boiling in 3-quart saucepan, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal in a large bowl; toss until completely coated with chocolate. Fold in marshmallows, 1 cup at a time.
Press mixture evenly in pan with buttered back of spoon.
Let cool 1 hour and cut into squares.
Makes 24 squares.

title: breakfast chili rellenos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Oil bottom of square or small rectangle glass cake pan.
Place whole chili rellenos at bottom of pan, unfolding them and covering entire bottom.
Spread out Monterey Jack cheese over chilies, covering them completely.
Crack eggs into a bowl; add milk and whip until mixed.
Pour on top of cheese. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake in oven until top is golden brown, approximately 20 minutes.
Garnish with picante sauce and sour cream.

title: strawberry sundaes in pastry
directions: Bake puff pastry shells according to package directions.
Just before serving, scoop ice cream into baked puff pastry shells. Drizzle with strawberry topping and sprinkle with nuts.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine first four ingredients in large salad bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar well, then toss with salad. Refrigerate one hour.
Serve.

title: cabbage creole
directions: In heavy skillet, cook bacon, bell pepper and onion until bacon is crisp.
Add tomato sauce, honey, seasoning and mustard. Simmer slowly for 10 minutes.
Add cabbage; simmer 15 minutes longer.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti as directed on package. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: beer and sauerkraut chocolate cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with beer.
Stir in sauerkraut.
Pour into greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cherry cheesecake dessert
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in butter flavoring.
Crush graham crackers into fine crumbs.
Mix crumbs with melted butter.
Press into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix softened (room temperature) cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread over graham cracker layer.
Top with cherry pie filling 1 hour before serving. Refrigerate to chill pie filling.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Marinate cut up chicken in 1/2 cup soy sauce and 1/2 cup sherry.
Cut up broccoli and mushrooms in bite-size pieces.
Fry chicken on top of stove until brown.
Add mushrooms, broccoli and almonds.
Serve over rice.

title: pork tenderloin with mustard sauce(serves 8)
directions: Combine first three ingredients in an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish; add tenderloins.
Cover and refrigerate at least two hours, turning meat occasionally.
Remove from marinade; place on a rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Serve with mustard sauce.

title: cherry, strawberry or blueberry cheese cake
directions: Melt butter in an oblong pan.
Mix flour and nuts together; add butter and press into pan.
Bake at 350° until light brown. Cool.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Line muffin tins with Saran Wrap.
Fill with salad.
Cover and freeze.
After frozen, may take out of pan, store in Ziploc bags and serve as needed.

title: spicy oven pork chops
directions: About 1 1/4 hours before serving:
In large roasting pan, mix soy sauce, sherry and water.
Place pork loin blade chops in soy sauce mixture, turning each chop to coat well.
Bake in 375° oven 40 minutes.
With pastry brush, baste chops occasionally with soy sauce mixture in pan.

title: easy banana-nut bread
directions: Mix eggs and oil well. Stir in banana and vanilla. Add baking mix, sugar and walnuts. Mix well. Stir in chocolate chips if desired. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. Cool in pan 5 to 10 minutes, then remove from pan and let cool completely on a wire rack.

title: school rolls
directions: Scald the milk.
Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Add shortening, sugar and salt to milk; cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 cup flour and beat.
Add yeast and 1 well beaten egg; mix well.
Add flour to make dough easy to handle; knead.
Put into greased bowl; cover with damp cloth.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Punch down; cover and let rise again.
Shape into rolls.
Let rise.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°.

title: mashed potato salad(from 1975 edition)
directions: Pare potatoes; cover with boiling water and bring to a boil. Cover and boil until tender; drain.
Put through a food mill or mash your favorite way; there should be about 4 cups.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Taste and add more salt if desired.
Serve warm, garnished with parsley and extra olives, or serve cold, garnished with lettuce and extra olives.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Follow directions on Rice-A-Roni.
Use chicken broth in place of water.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until rice is done, approximately 30 minutes.

title: hot ham sandwiches
directions: Mix all together and spread on rolls.
Wrap in foil (separately).
Put on cookie sheet and heat at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Can be made ahead and store in refrigerator or freezer. Makes about 18 sandwiches.

title: oven beef stroganoff
directions: Layer in covered ovenproof dish or roaster. Bake 3 hours at 250°. Add 8 to 12 ounces sour cream and serve with cooked noodles. Good to leave on Sunday morning.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and
fruit
cocktail until Jell-O dissolves. Add milk and Cool Whip;
blend together.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together.
Roll in very small balls.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 100 balls.

title: grandma talton's hush puppies
directions: Put
into sifter and sift all together, then stir extra with spoon.
Add
enough buttermilk to coat but make a stiff, sticky mixture.
Put
in a preheated deep fryer by spoonfuls. Good with fish or any seafood.

title: cake and cheesecake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs and blend.
Add milk and vanilla; stir.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture; blend well.
Turn into greased 10 inch pie plate, 2 inch deep.
Spread batter over bottom and sides, spreading thinner on sides.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Place broccoli in 10 x 13-inch casserole.
Combine the rest of the ingredients and pour over broccoli.
Crush Cheez-Its or Better Cheddars and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Combine sugar, buttermilk, syrup and soda.
Cook slowly in a heavy pot until the mixture forms a soft ball, about 20 minutes. Use a candy thermometer (235°).
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and pecans.
Beat until smooth and creamy using a wooden spoon.
Drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper.
If candy does not harden within 10 minutes of dropping, it can be cooked a few minutes more.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Layer broccoli, cheese, onion and bacon.
Cover with mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar (mixed together).
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Allow to sit in refrigerator for 2 to 6 hours.
Stir and serve.

title: microwave sunday glazed carrots
directions: Wash and cut carrots into 1/2-inch diagonal slices.
Place in 1-quart casserole with butter and brown sugar.
Cover and microwave on High for 9 to 11 minutes, stirring after 5 minutes. Mix water and cornstarch until smooth.
Stir into carrot mixture. Add pecans. Cover and microwave on High for 2 to 4 minutes, until thickened. Stir before serving.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: italian stew
directions: Heat cooking oil in frying pan.
Brown beef.
Transfer to large pot.
Peel and cut onions in quarters.
Brown in frying pan. Transfer to pot.
Measure oregano, rosemary, chili, salt and flour into medium bowl.
Stir well.
Add tomato paste, water and cut up canned tomatoes.
Mix together and add to meat.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Add carrots and celery to meat.
Simmer, covered, 45 minutes until vegetables and meat are tender.
Cook macaroni as directed on package. Drain.
Add to meat mixture.
Serves 8.

title: cinnamon apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Arrange apple slices in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour water over top.
Combine cake mix, brown sugar, melted margarine and cinnamon.
Stir until well blended. Sprinkle mixture over apple slices.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, oleo, and sugar.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
Blend cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip, spread on cooled crust. Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and stir in frozen strawberries. When partially set, pour over second layer and refrigerate.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into pound cake pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: larina's peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar and white Karo on high 4 minutes.
Add peanuts. Stir.
Cook on high 3 to 5 minutes until light brown; will be very hot.
Stir in vanilla and butter.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes more.
Stir in baking soda.
Spread on buttered pan to cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together in blender the cottage cheese and yogurt.
Boil squash until tender; drain and set aside.
Saute celery, onions and green pepper until tender.
Mix with squash.
Add crackers, yogurt mixture, cheese and seasonings.
Stir to mix.
Bake in a casserole dish at 350° for 50 minutes.
Should be brown on top. Makes 6 servings.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: In skillet, cook tortillas, one at a time, in hot oil for 5 seconds on each side.
Place 2 tablespoons of cheese and 1 tablespoon of onion on each tortilla.
Roll up.
Place seam side down in 11 x 17-inch baking dish.
In saucepan, melt butter; blend in flour.
Add chicken broth and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture bubbles and thickens.
Stir sour cream, chicken and peppers in.
Cook until heated through but do not boil.
Pour over tortillas.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top; return to oven only to melt cheese.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage.
Drain excess grease.
Mix all ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish sprayed with nonstick spray.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Drain fruit, keeping juice.
Add water to make 2 cups and heat to boiling.
Dissolve gelatin in this and chill until slightly thickened.
Mix softened cream cheese and mayonnaise and beat in gelatin.
Prepare Dream Whip and gradually fold in gelatin.
Set aside 1 cup of this.
Add drained fruits, nuts and sauce.
Pour into glass dish and let set.
Frost with reserved topping. Refrigerate several hours or may be frozen and removed from refrigerator 1 hour before serving.

title: butter or sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine, add eggs and other dry ingredients and vanilla.
Chill dough at least 1 hour before rolling out on a floured board.
The batter is rich so if it picks up a little flour on the rolling pin, it will make no difference.
Use a simple butter frosting for the trim on the cookies.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 375°.

title: creamy corn scallop
directions: Combine soup, onion and pepper.
In 1-quart casserole, arrange alternate layers of corn, soup mixture and crackers; dot with butter or oleo.
Bake in a 400° oven for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Keep it covered in a container in the refrigerator for up to six weeks.

title: banana nut bread
