directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and mashed bananas (add soda to bananas and beat well).
Add the sugar and butter mixture.
Add the flour and salt; mix well, then add pecans.

title: honey bee cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine, brown sugar, honey and egg in a bowl on medium speed until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop the dough by teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until set and light brown around edges (surfaces of cookies will appear shiny), 7 to 9 minutes.
Let stand 3 to 5 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: dried fruit soup(dziovintu vaisiu sriuba)
directions: Soak dried fruit.
Cook all but the starch about 1 hour.
Make paste of starch and add to soup.
Bring to boil.
May be garnished with thin orange slices floating on top or top with Cool Whip. Serve hot or cold.

title: squash casserole
directions: Clean, slice and boil squash until tender.
Drain squash and mix with other ingredients.
Bake in buttered casserole dish at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: rolled apples
directions: Cut crescent roll squares in half like crescent rolls.
Roll up apple slices and lay flat in pan.
Cover each with butter (melted) and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Pour 1/4 cup orange juice in bottom of pan, not on top.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Can serve with ice cream.

title: coca cola salad
directions: Heat cherries, sugar and water.
Let boil 2 minutes.
Pour over jello and add the coke.
Let set until it starts to jell then add pineapple and pecans.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix oleo, flour, 2 tablespoons sugar and nuts.
Press into oblong pan.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Bake 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Beat together powdered sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust and top with pie filling. Refrigerate.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: In large baking dish, layer the deboned chicken.
Mix soups, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Top with the cracker mix.
Pour over with oleo.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: egg rolls
directions: Chop vegetables.
Add pork and shrimp; saute until pork is cooked.
Combine cornstarch, soy sauce, sesame oil, garlic, onion and peanut butter.
Add to cooked vegetables for thickening.
Put in egg roll skins (1 to 2 tablespoons).
Use egg white to seal.

title: holiday ham
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Trim fat on ham to the shank. Place ham on foil and rub with the mixed ingredients.
Pour over ham any remaining mixture.
Wrap the ham in the foil and place in a covered roaster.
Bake at 400° for 2 1/2 or 3 hours.
Garnish with spiced apples, pears, apples or pineapple.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, oleo and salt; stir well.
Boil 5 minutes.
Stir in soda and flavorings.
Stir in popcorn.
Add nuts, if desired.
Put in roaster and bake at 250° for 1 hour; stir every 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: cranberry pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple.
Blend in cranberry sauce and cold water.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan until set.

title: philippine red snapper
directions: Peel onion and chop fine.
Seed green pepper and chop.
Chop celery and carrot.
Place fish fillets on large plate.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and salt.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Place fillets in a 9 x 13-inch bake pan, discarding excess lemon juice.
Heat olive oil in 10-inch frypan over medium heat.
Saute onion, green pepper, celery and carrot 5 minutes, stirring with fork.
Add tomatoes, ketchup, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Pour vegetables over fillets.
Bake 35 minutes at 400°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: festive chicken
directions: Add all ingredients and mix together. Simmer until heated and most of the liquid is absorbed or bake for 14 minutes in moderate oven at 350°.

title: cheddar cheese appetizer
directions: Grate the cheese, using the medium grater.
Cut the onion, including the greens, making sure they are cut fine.
Add the chopped onion and mayonnaise to the grated cheese.
Mix and let it stand overnight for blending of flavors.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover the bottom of pan with the cubed bread.
Cover this layer with cheese and pork sausage. Beat the eggs and combine with the milk and dry mustard.
Pour over the meat and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, bake in a 350° oven for 60 minutes, uncovered.
Serve with muffins and fresh fruit.

title: chicken almond puff
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and soup until smooth.
Stir in chicken.
Unroll one can of rolls into 2 long rectangles on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press perforations to seal. Place 1/2 chicken mixture over each rectangle, staying away from edges.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Unroll second can of rolls and place over chicken.
Go along edges with fork to seal edges and pinch top perforation gently together.
Bake about 20 minutes, until golden brown.
Slice to serve.
Makes 3 to 4 servings per rectangle; 6 to 8 servings per recipe.

title: layered gazpacho salad
directions: Make Lemon-Garlic Vinaigrette. Place lettuce in large glass bowl. Layer tomatoes, cucumbers, bell pepper and onion on lettuce. Pour vinaigrette over onion. Cover and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours to blend flavors.

title: best sourdough bread
directions: The night before, mix together 1 package of yeast, 1 cup water and 1 cup of flour.
Let set in a warm place overnight.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix together the pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Layer bottom of an 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan with whole graham crackers and half of pudding mixture.
Add another layer of crackers and remaining pudding mixture.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes with water (about 4 cups).
Add celery and onion.
Cook covered until tender, about 20 minutes.
Mash all potato pieces.
Stir together butter and flour.
Add to potato mixture, stirring all the while.
Add milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Continue heating until bubbly.
Stir often.
It tends to stick.

title: skillet cookies
directions: When cool, form in small balls and roll in coconut.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Mash avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix.
Spread bean dip on platter.
Top with avocados.
Layer with sour cream and taco mixture.
Next, spread onion, tomatoes and olives.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion in melted margarine.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to onion.
Heat until cheese melts.

title: a.b.c. brownies
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in sugar.
Bring to a boil. Turn off heat and cool for 5 to 10 minutes.
Rapidly stir eggs, being careful not to cook them.
Add vanilla.
In a bowl, combine flour and baking powder.
Stir into sugar and egg mixture.
Pour batter into greased 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with almonds and chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: hoagie sausage sandwiches
directions: In a large frying pan, saute onions and peppers in a tablespoon of oil until tender.
Add crushed tomatoes, spices and salt and pepper to taste.
Put sausage in a large baking pan. Stick several times with a fork.
Add about 1/2 inch of water to the bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° until sausage is done; drain water.
After draining water off of sausage, pour sauce over, then cover with tinfoil and put back in oven.
Cook slowly at about 300°.
The longer it cooks, the better it is, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients; let stand 2 hours and drain.
Mix together the remaining 6 ingredients; cook this to a boil.
Add both mixtures and cook 20 minutes.
Put in pint jars and seal.
Delicious with hot dogs and hamburgers.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Cream butter with brown sugar in a small bowl.
Add flour and nuts.
Mix well to make a crumb mixture.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Press remainder into bottom of an 8-inch square pan. Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned. Blend sugar with cream cheese in small bowl until smooth.
Add egg, milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat well.
Spread over baked crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cool; cut into small squares.
Makes 36 squares.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Put first 5 ingredients together into large saucepan and bring to a rolling boil, stirring occasionally.
Boil 2 minutes, then add oats and vanilla.
Mix well and drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper.
Let set or place in refrigerator until hardened.

title: peanut butter meteors
directions: In medium saucepan, stir together brown sugar, peanut butter and evaporated milk.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly, until brown sugar is dissolved and peanut butter is melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool until firm.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: potato fluff
directions: Beat all ingredients together and bake uncovered at 350° until top is browned.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix milk, sour cream and cream cheese with chili powder. Spread on platter.
Layer lettuce, onions and tomatoes.
Sprinkle each layer with garlic salt.
Add cheese as topping.
Serve with taco chips (serve this on round platter).

title: marinated cucumber salad
directions: In a medium container, combine vinegar, water, oil, salt, pepper and sugar.
Cover tightly.
Shake vigorously for 15 seconds.
Add cucumber, onion, radishes and parsley.
Gently stir vegetables in marinade to coat.
Cover tightly.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or up to 2 days.

title: salsa
directions: Make sure you seed your peppers. Combine tomatoes, peppers, onions, salt, garlic and vinegar. Bring mix to boil; place spice bag in mix. Cook 30 minutes until thickens. Take spice bag out; add honey and tomato paste. Makes 6 pints.

title: cajun pasta(this is not for the fainthearted!)
directions: * This can be obtained in specialty food stores where they make their own sausage, etc.

title: viennese ribbon cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour the bottom and side of jelly roll pan (15 X 10).
Measure butter, sugar, vanilla, eggs, salt and flour into mixing bowl.
Beat 3 minutes on medium speed. Spread 1/3 of mixture into prepared pan.
Repeat, baking three total pans about 7 minutes each; cool.
Mix sour cream and nuts. On two layers spread 3 Tbsp. raspberry jam; layer of sour cream mixture; and 2 Tbsp. apricot jam.
Stack layered cakes on top of each other; leaving the top layer plain.
Cut off edges and leave in freezer overnight.
Frost with creamy frosting and sprinkle with decorated sugar.

title: corned beef dip
directions: Remove top and insides from bread (reserve for dipping).
Mix well all other ingredients and place in hollowed out loaf.
Break up reserved bread to use for dipping.
You can also use crackers with this dip.

title: moist pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Stir in vanilla.
Save 1/2 cup of batter for icing.
Bake in a lightly greased and floured tube pan at 300° for about 1 1/2 hours until done.

title: brownie oatmeal gems
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, stir chocolate and butter over low heat just until chocolate melts.
Remove from heat.
Stir in syrup, eggs and salt.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and
blend.
Then
add
rest
of ingredients.
Put in greased baking pan (13 x 9-inches).
Cook for 1/2 hour in 350° oven or until done.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well. Then mix the 1/4 cup melted margarine with the corn flakes.
Cover the other ingredients. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook and drain onion and squash.
Mix sugar, melted oleo and milk.
Stir these in the squash and onion.
Stir in egg.
Bake at 325° until lightly browned.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, cut up in small pieces.
Cook noodles, onion and celery in broth (about 4 cups) until all liquid has been soaked up.
Add chicken, soup and cheese to hot mixture.
Bake in moderate oven for 35 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and water in pan; bring to boil at 250°.
Add 1 tablespoon margarine and peanuts to mixture and bring to 310°. Remove from heat.
Add salt, soda and 1 tablespoon margarine. Pour into pie pans.
Cool.
Remove.
Put onto waxed paper and finish cooling.

title: chunky chili
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Drain well. Add the rest of the ingredients. Add about 3 cups of water and simmer for several hours.

title: chocolate-walnut frosting
directions: Smooth
and
creamy
for
devil's food or any chocolate cake. Melt
butter
and
chocolate
together
over hot water. Stir hot milk into sugar and salt;
add vanilla, add chocolate mixture, beating until thick.
Spread on cool cake.
Decorate sides
with chopped
walnuts; arrange walnut halves on top to complete.

title: easy chicken dinner
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain well.
Arrange in greased baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, salad dressing and lemon juice; pour over top.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and cheese over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: archie's rice
directions: Saute the onion, garlic and tomato in the olive oil.
Dump in the rice and cook until shiny, about 5 minutes.
Add the remaining 6 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Cover and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: classic macaroni salad
directions: Combine first 6 items, then add remaining items.
Cover, chill and serve.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Brown beef with onion and bell pepper.
Drain well.
In a bowl, combine the remaining ingredients with the cooked beef. Pour into a casserole dish and bake at 350 for 30 minutes.
Let sit 10 to 15 minutes after taking out of the oven before serving.

title: easy minestrone soup
directions: Heat oil in a Dutch oven.
Saute garlic, onion and celery for 5 minutes.
Stir in beef broth, tomato paste, tomatoes, macaroni, kidney beans, cabbage and vegetables; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients, except Parmesan cheese.
Cook 15 minutes longer and then garnish with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 24 generously.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Combine milk and water; add pudding mix and beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in all but about 1/2 cup of Cool Whip.
Spoon about 1 cup pudding mixture into trifle bowl.
Top with 1/3 of wafers (stand some up around edge and sprinkle crushed over top of mixture).
Add about 1/3 bananas (dip into lemon juice first). Continue to layer pudding, wafers and bananas.
Top with Cool Whip and decorate with banana slices.
Chill before serving.
I sometimes add a few strawberries around edge of trifle bowl for decoration.
You may want to add a few to the whipped cream on top also.

title: party pull-apart bread
directions: Brown sausage; pour off excess grease.
Add bell pepper and onion.
Turn off stove; set aside.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Grease Bundt pan.
Layer bottom of pan with sausage mixture.
Cut biscuits into fourths; dip into melted butter.
Place can of biscuit fourths on top of sausage mixture.
Layer again with sausage mixture and another can of biscuit fourths.
Repeat process; end with meat mixture on top.
Pour remaining butter over top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes, or until brown. Serve hot.

title: homemade ribbon
directions: Mix and then mix with 3/4 cup water.
Lay fabric out flat and brush with the mixture until completely wet. Let lay flat until dry.
Fabric will be very stiff.
Cut into desired widths for ribbon.
Will not ravel.

title: cheese dollars(appetizer)
directions: Cream butter, gradually adding flour and Rice Krispies.
Add cheese and Tabasco.
Roll into balls and flatten.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: good and easy cake
directions: Mix together ingredients for 2 minutes. Bake for 40 minutes or until done.

title: rick's flaming bananas
directions: In a medium frying pan, melt butter and sugar.
Slice banana lengthwise and crosswise into chunks.
Toss gently in sauce to warm.
Add rum and banana liqueur to bananas.
Heat on high for one minute and ignite.
Divide ice-cream among 4 parfait or wine glasses.
Spoon over ice-cream.

title: lace cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oatmeal and flour (add salt, if desired).
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate, covered, 4 hours or overnight.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on unbuttered foil on cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 12 minutes or until slightly browned. Cool on foil before removing.

title: layered chicken enchiladas
directions: Brown peppers, onions and garlic.
Add chicken (bite size pieces) and continue to brown. Drain fat.
Add chili powder and salt. Stir. Set aside. Blend cream cheese, soup and lemon juice. Set aside. In crock-pot, layer tortillas, meat mixture, cream cheese mixture and Cheddar cheese.
End with Cheddar cheese on top. Cover and cook on low about 4 hours.

title: coconut pie
directions: Heat milk in a double boiler until hot.
Do not boil.
Combine sugar cornstarch and salt in a mixing bowl.
Add hot milk, beat for 1 minute or until smooth.
Add eggs and mix will.
Pour mixture back into double boiler.
Stir occasionally until mixture begins to coat the sides of the pan, then stir constantly until thick.
Place in mixer bowl and add coconut and vanilla.
Beat on medium speed until cool.
Pour into pie shell and top with whipped cream. Refrigerate.

title: phili cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts.
After mixed, roll in nuts.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions in butter until transparent.
Add flour; mix well. Place onions in slow cooker.
Add beef stock and Tabasco.
Cover; cook on low 8 to 10 hours, or on high heat for 4 to 5 hours. Ladle soup into 6 ovenproof bowls.
Top each with slice of bread (or croutons); sprinkle with cheese.
Place in a 350° oven until cheese is bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Marinate 1 hour or more lean pork chops or chicken.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour or grill.
Best on pork chops 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.

title: bali hai punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in punch bowl; add pineapple and strawberries or any other fruit.

title: gabriel's peanut butter and ketchup soup(this is good and easy and totally vegetarian!)
directions: Cut sweet potatoes in thirds.
Boil 30 minutes. Remove skins and cut into bite-size pieces. Process onion and garlic in processor.

title: ham and swiss cheese casserole
directions: Saute butter and onion.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: italian cake
directions: Follow directions on Duncan Hines cake mix box.
In a bowl, blend until smooth Ricotta cheese, eggs, vanilla and sugar.
Pour this mixture on top of cake mix.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Blend together chocolate pudding and milk.
This mixture gets thick.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on top of cake after cake is very cold.

title: popsicles
directions: Dissolve jello, Kool-Aid and sugar in boiling water; add cold water. Pour into molds or cups and freeze.

title: cooked corn and red pepper saute
directions: In a skillet, heat oil.
Add onion, red pepper, garlic and tarragon.
Saute for 10 minutes, until vegetables are tender. Stir in corn, lemon rind and salt.
Cook for 2 minutes or until heated through.
Stir in lemon juice and red pepper sauce.
Serves 4.

title: burrito appetizers
directions: Spread heated beans on flour tortillas.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread over beans.
Sprinkle cheese over top. Roll and refrigerate 1 hour.
Slice and serve.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon, saving 2 tablespoons of liquid.
Mix salmon, egg and onion until sticky.
Add baking powder to salmon liquid, then stir into salmon mixture.
Heat Crisco in pan.
Form salmon mixture into patties.
Fry in heated Crisco until golden brown.

title: south carolina greens
directions: Saute onion, garlic, green pepper and celery.
Add to collard greens with water.
Cook slow for 45 minutes.

title: peach delight
directions: Mix Jell-O with 2 cups hot water.
Add cream cheese and mix with mixer.
Add peaches and 7-Up.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with mini-marshmallows.
Refrigerate.

title: steak with mushroom sauce
directions: Rub tenderloins with olive oil; salt and pepper them and set aside.
In a large skillet or electric skillet, heat butter over medium heat.
Add garlic, shallots and thyme, cooking in butter for 1 minute.
Turn heat up to medium-high and add tenderloins, browning on both sides to desired level of doneness.
Remove tenderloins to a plate set in a warm place.
Add mushrooms to skillet and saut until tender.
Pour in beef broth and Madeira and bring to a boil.
Let liquid reduce to half.
Add heavy cream and let heat thoroughly and thicken, stirring constantly.
Serve mushroom sauce over tenderloins, using extra sauce for potatoes or rice on the side.

title: greek baklava
directions: Combine nuts, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Brush a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan well with butter.
Separate 25 sheets of filo pastry from package.
Place under a smooth (not terry) damp towel to prevent drying.
Wrap remaining filo well.
Freeze for future use.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Stir flour and soda together. Set aside.
Cream the margarine and sugar together until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in vanilla, lemon extract and almond extract. Add flour mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Blend thoroughly after each addition.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool 20 minutes before removing from pan to completely cool.

title: zucchini and bell pepper frittata
directions: In
9-inch skillet, cook onion, zucchini and peppers in little oil.
Salt and pepper
to	taste.	In
a
bowl,
whisk together eggs, 1/3 cup
Parmesan
and parsley.
Add vegetables to mixture. In the skillet,
heat remaining oil.
Pour in egg mixture, distributing vegetables
evenly,
and
cook
Frittata without stirring until edge
is set and center soft.
Sprinkle remaining Parmesan over top.	Put
under broiler 4-inches from heat until cheese is
golden.	Cool.
Slide
out
onto serving plate.	Cut in wedges.
Serves 2.

title: hard-cooked eggs with mushrooms casserole
directions: Cut eggs in half. Remove yolks and put through sieve.
Add seasonings and 1/3 of the chopped mushrooms which have been sauteed in a small amount of butter.
Re-fill whites with yolk mixture.
Press 2 halves together.
Place in casserole.
Pour the cream sauce over them mixed with the remaining mushrooms. Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs to hard-boiled.
Prepare other ingredients in medium bowl.
Peel eggs.
Slice halfway across middle.
Take egg yolk (middle).
Mix into other ingredients.
Then spoon mixture into boiled egg white.
Yields 24 deviled eggs.
Sprinkle paprika on top.

title: brownie split(brownie pizza)
directions: Use a 15-inch baking stone.
Cut parchment paper to fit on top of stone.
The paper will have a tendency to roll.
Lay rolling side up.

title: salmon dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in oven in 9 x 13-inch pan until sizzling hot. Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour in pan.
Spread fruit over batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Beat with a fork water, vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and pepper. Add cucumber slices and toss.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: sour cream italian dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl, stirring well with a wire whisk. Cover and chill at least 2 hours before serving. Yield: 1 cup.

title: pennsylvania cheesecake
directions: Beat until smooth (high speed of mixer or food processor). Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until edges are brown. (Bake 35 to 40 minutes if using two 8 x 8-inch square pans.)
Remove from oven and let cool 10 minutes.
Spread sour cream mixture on top and place back in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix thoroughly the beef, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape firmly into 4 oval patties.
In skillet, brown patties; pour off fat. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover, cook over low heat for 20 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: mahogany cake
directions: Boil together 1/2 cup of the milk and the chocolate.
Let cool.
Beat sugar and butter until creamy.
Add the eggs, remaining milk (which has had the soda dissolved in it), lemon and vanilla extracts, the chocolate and flour.
Bake in layers, using any desired filling.
Bake at 350° until cake tests done.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Crush pretzels and put in the bottom of pan with the butter and 4 Tbsp. sugar.
Bake at 350 degrees for 7 - 8 minutes.
Cool.
Mix together cream cheese, Cool Whip and 1 c. sugar.
Spread over pretzels.
Combine boiling water and strawberry Jello.
Add frozen strawberries.
Mix and let stand 5 minutes.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Chill.

title: spaghetti alla carbonara
directions: Slice bacon into 1/2-inch strips and add to skillet.
Cook over low heat.
Do not overcook (bacon will further cook when added to spaghetti).
Pour off excess fat.

title: double apple coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly spray an 8 x 8-inch square pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Combine flour, cereal, 2/3 cup sugar, baking powder, 2 teaspoons of cinnamon and baking soda. Add and combine milk, applesauce and egg; mix just until moistened.
Stir in apple.
Pour batter into prepared pan.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Cream shortening or oil and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in banana.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to banana mixture and chocolate chips, mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin trifle
directions: Set aside 1/4 cup cake crumbs for top.
Divide remaining crumbs into 4 portions.
Sprinkle one portion in the bottom of a trifle bowl or 3-quart serving bowl.
In a large mixing bowl, combine pumpkin, spices, milk and pudding.
Mix until smooth.
Spoon half into a serving bowl.
Sprinkle with second portion of crumbs.

title: apple or zucchini strudel
directions: Cook zucchini and lemon juice together until tender.
Add 1 cup sugar, 1 tsp cinnamon and the nutmeg to zucchini mixture. Simmer for 1 minute.
Set aside.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie crust.
Store in refrigerator.
Allow 24 hours to set.

title: ginger meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except pineapple. Spread beef mixture evenly in ungreased loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour; drain.
Spoon pineapple over meat loaf.
Bake about 30 minutes longer or until no longer pink in center.

title: hot savory dip
directions: Put all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart microproof casserole. Cover and cook on Medium for 6 minutes.
Stir thoroughly halfway through cooking time.
Serve as a warm dip for meatballs/vegetables.
Keep warm on fondue burner.
Makes 2 cups.

title: chex party mix
directions: Heat oven to 250°. Melt butter in large roasting pan in oven. Stir in seasonings. Gradually stir in remaining ingredients until evenly coated. Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Store in an airtight container.

title: scatter-mix party mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in large roaster.
Cook in preheated 250° oven for one hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Store in airtight container when cool.

title: plain roll dough
directions: Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool until lukewarm.
Add yeast softened in water.
Add egg.
Gradually stir in flour to form soft dough.
Cover and let rise until doubled in size.

title: peg sargent's oatmeal lace cookies
directions: Line ungreased cookie sheet with aluminum foil; spoon drop 3 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: kim's favorite punch
directions: Heat sugar and part of water until sugar dissolves.
Add remaining water and Kool-Aid.

title: apple crackle
directions: Place apples in bottom of a greased 8-inch square pan.
In a bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake 30 minutes or until apples are golden.
Serves 4.
Delicious with ice cream or yogurt!

title: quick russian dressing
directions: Mix until well blended.
You won't believe this one.

title: relief society casserole
directions: Layer the first six ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste. Pour tomato soup and water (mixed) over layers.
Cover with foil. Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: quick garlic bread
directions: Break apart hot dog buns.
Butter insides like toast. Sprinkle garlic salt over each one.
Toast in toaster oven or broiler.
(One package buns make 16 mini breads.) Optional: Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix refried beans and taco seasoning.
Spread in an 8 x 10-inch pan.
Layer all ingredients in order given.

title: easy pancake syrup
directions: Microwave until butter melts.
Stir until it is one consistency.
Microwave again until almost boiling.

title: broccoli & cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli (as directed on pkg.) until done.
Do not over cook.
Crush the roll of Ritz Crackers.
(We like to use large ziploc bag.)
Saute crumbled crackers in pan with stick of butter. Put broccoli in separate pan and add velveeta cheese & melt (more or less according to taste).
Put broccoli & cheese in a baking dish.
Add sauteed Ritz Crackers on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350 degrees or until golden brown.

title: strawberry punch
directions: In punch bowl combine pineapple juice, sugar, lemonade concentrate and water.
Add ice cream; stir until blended.
Stir in ginger ale.
Serve at once.

title: pina colada dip
directions: Whisk ingredients in a small bowl.
Makes about 3/4 cup of dip.
This is good with fruit.

title: easy baked turkey
directions: Season inside and outside of turkey with salt and pepper. Dissolve paprika in water; blend in oil.
Baste turkey with oil mixture.
Place 2 heavy brown grocery bags together and brush inside of bag with remaining oil mixture, greasing well.
Place turkey in bag, breast side up; close end of bag tightly.
Place bag in baking pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 15 minutes per pound.
(Turkey will always be extremely tender and golden brown.)

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, mix sugar, syrup and peanuts. Cook on full power 7 1/2 minutes.
Stir 1/2 way through.
Remove from oven; stir in vanilla and butter.
Cook another 2 minutes on full power.
Remove quickly; add soda.
Stir and pour into a warmed, buttered cookie sheet.

title: quick cheese puffs
directions: Cut each biscuit into
quarters.
Roll
each
piece
in melted butter, then in
cheese mixture.
Place on baking sheet in 450° oven for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: kraut-stuffed goose
directions: Drain the sauerkraut.
Fry bacon pieces and remove them from the pan.
Saute the onion in bacon fat until tender.
Add the drained sauerkraut and cook for 10 minutes.
In a large bowl mix the sauerkraut, bacon pieces, onion, apples, potatoes, sage and seasoning.
Salt the goose inside and fill with sauerkraut mixture.
Place the goose on a rack, breast side up.
Roast at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, basting with the drippings every half hour.
When done (tender to a probing fork), let the goose sit at least 15 minutes before carving.
Remove the dressing and serve it separately.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake as directed adding 1 tsp. of coconut flavoring.
Bake as directed in 9 X 13 pan and cool.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Prepare lettuce and onion as for salad.
Cook bacon tender-crisp in bite-size pieces and crumble over lettuce and onion mixture.
Boil water, vinegar and sugar until sugar melts and pour over salad mixture.
Cover and let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: six weeks raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil.
Sift soda, salt and flour.
Add alternately with buttermilk to egg mixture, then add Raisin Bran cereal.
Store in airtight container up to 6 weeks in refrigerator.
When ready to bake, spoon batter into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: italian salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon; add eggs, bread crumbs and spices.
Mix well. Shape into loaf.
Place in a greased pan and add water.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake a little longer until browns.

title: orange refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Put next 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl, beat on No. 8 speed for 1 minute, scraping bowl while beating.
Stop mixer.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Add flour mixture and beat on No. 2 speed until well blended, about 1 1/2 minutes.
Scrape bowl.
Shape into rolls. Wrap in waxed paper; chill several hours.
Slice thin with a sharp knife.
Put on greased cookie sheets.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven about 12 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: giant bubble mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bucket.
Use large bubble wands to produce giant bubbles.
Fun for children of all ages!

title: rice pudding(puerto rico)
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given, rice, sugar, salt, milk, raisins, butter and eggs.
Pour mixture into a buttered baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add warm water. Knead until dough is soft and does not stick to bowl.
(If necessary, add more water.)

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook meat until light gray.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in casserole and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Rinse broccoli and mushrooms.
Cut broccoli into bite-size pieces.
Slice mushrooms up.
Cook bacon until crisp and crumble into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together and chill for a few hours before serving.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Mix shortening and milk until shortening is melted.
Mix beaten eggs, sugar and salt.
Add cold water, softening yeast in lukewarm water.
Combine all 3 mixtures and add flour.
Cover and put in refrigerator overnight.
Pinch off and make into rolls. Put in greased muffin tins and let rise until double.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place beans and cheese in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Top with French fried onion rings.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350° or melt cheese in microwave oven and add onion rings later.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
If compressed yeast is used, allow to stand 30 minutes.
Add salt, shortening, sugar and eggs. Add flour little at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition until the dough is just stiff enough to knead on lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Cover with a damp cloth. Set in a warm place (not too hot) and allow to rise until dough is double in bulk.
Work down.
Allow to rise 2nd time.
Turn onto a lightly floured board.
Roll out in circular shapes.
Cut into sections as you would a pie, having each section about 3-inches wide at the outer section toward the center.
Form into crescents.
Place in well oiled baking pans.
Cover and let rise until in treble bulk.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: easy one dish supper
directions: Brown hamburger and add carrots, potatoes, onion, bouillon cubes and water; cook until tender.
Add 2 tablespoons flour to a little water to thicken.
Serve immediately.

title: heartburn pizza
directions: Prepare pizza dough as directed on box.
Press dough on pizza pan.
Spread packaged sauce onto crust dough.
Sprinkle onion. Add browned ground beef and browned sausage and ham and sprinkle sweet and hot peppers.
Add mushrooms and olives.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese generously.
Place pepperoni slices on last. Bake 10 to 18 minutes at 350° or according to package directions. Pizza is ready to remove from oven when crust is baked.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in salt water and drain.
While they are cooking, fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan and crumble. Saute onion and pepper in bacon drippings.
Stir all ingredients together and serve hot.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes; cut in finger sized pieces.
Place in casserole; sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Bake, covered, at 425° for 50 minutes.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: chicken with olives and lemons(a popular moroccan tejine)
directions: Heat oil in a large heatproof casserole or Dutch oven.
Stir in next 7 ingredients.
Add chicken pieces and turn to coat with onion mixture. Arrange lemon wedges over the top.
Cover and simmer until very tender, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Turn occasionally.
Remove chicken to serving platter.
Arrange lemon wedges on top and keep warm. Cook liquid, stirring, in casserole over high heat until reduced to a thick sauce.
Add olives and heat through. Pour over chicken.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Drop cabbage leaves in boiling water a few minutes to soften. Remove. Drain and cool. Combine all ingredients except soup. Spoon mixture evenly into cabbage leaves and roll them up, tucking in sides before final end roll, to form a round envelope.
Place rolls in crock.
Pour the soup over all. Cover and cook for 6 to 8 hours at low heat or 3 to 4 at high.
Serves 4 to 6.
MMM Good.

title: crock-pot bean dinner
directions: Mix all together.
Cook in crock-pot on low for 4 to 5 hours.

title: non-cooked cookies
directions: Heat the first 3 ingredients until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well with nuts and coconut.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.

title: mushroom-noodle bake
directions: Cook mushrooms, onion and garlic in butter until onion is soft.
Cook noodles in boiling water until tender; drain.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl by tossing with two forks.
Bake in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: scampi(microwave)
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart glass casserole dish, cook butter on Roast for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add garlic; cook on High for 1 1/2 minutes or until butter is bubbly.
Mix in Parmesan cheese, parsley, lemon juice and shrimp.
Cook on High for 2 minutes or until shrimp are cooked.
Serves 4.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel, core and slice apples, very thin.
Mix all ingredients together, pour into frozen bottom crust, place top crust on and brush with butter then sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 1 hour or crust is golden brown.

title: turkey quesadillas
directions: Heat chopped onion in barbecue sauce over low heat until onion is soft.
Add shaved turkey and cook in sauce 10 minutes.
Spread turkey mixture over flour tortillas and cover with shredded cheese and another tortilla.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° until tortilla becomes slightly crisp (approximately 10 minutes).
Serve with garnish of chopped tomatoes, chopped scallions and a ball of sour cream.
Enjoy!

title: bro. leland's banana pudding
directions: Beat eggs in a saucepan; add sugar, cornstarch and milk.
Cook over boiling water until thick.
Stir once in a while so it won't burn!
Add vanilla flavoring.
Get a bowl, color of bowl doesn't matter.
Peel bananas (eat 1/2 of one to be sure it's ripe).
Put some vanilla wafers in bowl (munch a handful).
Slice bananas and cover the top of wafers.
Put another layer of wafers, ugh, go to store and buy another bag of wafers (these are gone).
While at the store, get more bananas.
Return from store and dump the rest in the bowl and eat the whole thing!!
